\h Genesis
\toc1 Genesis
\toc2 Genesis
\toc3 Gen.
\mt1 Genesis
\is1 Introduction
\ip The meaning of the English name \bk Genesis\bk* is вҖҳsourceвҖҷ or вҖҳbeginningвҖҷ. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳBereshitвҖҷ which is the first word in the Hebrew and means вҖҳIn the beginningвҖҷ. Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe first book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip This document describes the creation of space and of our planet and its contents, the origin of people, and the beginning of sin and suffering here in the world. This account also describes how God chose one particular people group and how he brought them to the land that he had promised them.
\ip This document has two main parts:
\ip 1. The making of world and the account of the first two people, and then the first ten generations of their descendants. We read about the foundations of human culture, beginning with Adam and Havvah (Eve) and their banishment from the garden, about Kayin (Cain) killing his brother Hevel (Abel), about Noah and the worldwide flood, and about the construction of the tower at Babel.
\ip 2. The lives of the ancestors of the Jewish people: Abraham the first ancestor became famous due to his faith and trust, and his obedience of God's commands. Following that is the account about his son Yitshak (Isaac), and his grandson Yacob (Jacob, also named вҖҳYisra'elвҖҷ or вҖҳIsraelвҖҷ), and then Yacob's twelve sons who became the founders of the twelve tribes of Yisra'el. That account also includes the part about Yacob's son Yosef and what happened him when he was sold into Egypt (Heb. Mitsrayim) by his brothers as a slave.
\ip We also read the accounts here about the various people groups that proliferated across the continent and formed into nations.
\ip There in final parts of this account, we're told about God's eternal promise of God to the people group that he chose. God doesn't forget his promises, but he also judges and punishes those who disobey him.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 God's creation of space and the earth \ior 1:1вҖ“2:25\ior*
\io1 The beginning of sin and suffering \ior 3:1-24\ior*
\io1 The accounts of Adam through to Noah \ior 4:1вҖ“5:32\ior*
\io1 Noah and the worldwide flood \ior 6:1вҖ“10:32\ior*
\io1 The tower at Babel \ior 11:1-9\ior*
\io1 The accounts of Shem through to Abraham \ior 11:10-32\ior*
\io1 The Hebrew patriarchs: Abraham, Yitshak, and Yacob \ior 12:1вҖ“35:29\ior*
\io1 The descendants of Esaw (Esau) \ior 36:1-43\ior*
\io1 Yosef and his brothers \ior 37:1вҖ“45:28\ior*
\io1 The Hebrews in Egypt \ior 46:1вҖ“50:26\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 The six days of creation
\rem /s1 Six Days of Creation and the Sabbath; The Account of Creation; The Beginning; The Story of Creation; The creation of the universe
\p
\v 1 In the beginningВҰ1, God\f + \fr 1:1 \ft As per common practice, we use вҖҳGodвҖҷ through the Hebrew scriptures for the word вҖҳelohimвҖҷ. Note that вҖҳelohimвҖҷ is a Hebrew language plural, and is translated more literally as вҖҳgodsвҖҷ in a few places. However the connected Hebrew verb translated вҖҳcreatedвҖҷ here is clearly a singular form, so the singular noun вҖҳGodвҖҷ fits better here and everywhere where вҖҳelohimвҖҷ is used with other verbs marked as being singular. The mysterious plurality of God is confirmed in v26 where вҖҳourвҖҷ is used to refer to him/them.\f* created the heavensВҰ5 and the earthВҰ7.
\v 2 The earthВҰ9 was formlessВҰ11 and empty and darknessВҰ13 covered the surface of the depth \add waters\add* and God's spiritВҰ18 was hoveringВҰ20 over the surface of the waters.
\v 3 ThenВҰ26 GodВҰ27 said, вҖңLet there be light,вҖқ andВҰ26 light came into existence,\x + \xo 1:3: \xt 2Cor 4:6.\x*
\v 4 andВҰ34 GodВҰ35 observed that the light was good. ThenВҰ36 he separatedВҰ42 the light from the darknessВҰ47.
\v 5 GodВҰ50 named the lightВҰ52 \em daytime\em*, and the darknessВҰ54 he named \em nighttimeВҰ56\em*. ThenВҰ49 eveningВҰ59 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ62 came, \add and that was the end of the\add* first day.
\p
\v 6 Then GodВҰ68 said, вҖңLet there be a \add вүҲlarge space\add*\f + \fr 1:6 \ft The Hebrew word here is sometimes translated вҖҳfirmamentвҖҷ (from the Latin Vulgate), or even вҖҳdomeвҖҷ, but God names it as вҖҳskyвҖҷ in v8 so it's obviously not intended to be anything solid-like.\f* in the middleВҰ71 of the waters, and let it separateВҰ74 the two lots of waters.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:6-8: \xt 2Pe 3:5.\x*
\v 7 SoВҰ79 GodВҰ80 made the \add вүҲlarge space\add* andВҰ79 separatedВҰ84 between the waters that were underneath from the waters that were above it.\f + \fr 1:6 \ft It's not clear how large or wide this separation is: if the waters below are the oceans (as distinct from subterranean water), then the waters above could be anything from rain clouds in the atmosphere, to water in space or at the edge of the universe or somewhere??? (Song/Psalm 148:4 refers to вҖҳthe waters that are above the heavens/skiesвҖҷ.)\f* EverythingВҰ81 happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 8 and he named the \add вүҲspace\add* \em sky\em*. ThenВҰ99 eveningВҰ105 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ108 came, \add and that was the end of\add* the secondВҰ110 dayВҰ109.
\p
\v 9 Then GodВҰ114 saidВҰ113, вҖңLet the watersВҰ116 underВҰ117 the sky be gatheredВҰ115 to one placeВҰ121, and let the dry groundВҰ124 appearВҰ123.вҖқ Everything happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 10 and he named the groundВҰ132 that appeared \em land\em*, and he named the gathered watersВҰ135 \add seas\add*, and he sawВҰ138 that \add what he had done\add* was goodВҰ142.
\v 11 ThenВҰ144 GodВҰ145 said, вҖңLet the land sproutВҰ146 vegetationВҰ148: every plantВҰ149 yielding seed, every fruit tree bearing its own fruit thatВҰ150 has its seed inside it, on the earth.вҖқ Everything happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 12 so the land started producing vegetationВҰ170, every plantВҰ171 producing its own seed, andВҰ168 every treeВҰ175 bearing fruitВҰ178 that has its seed inside it. AndВҰ188 GodВҰ187 sawВҰ186 that \add what he had done\add* was goodВҰ190.
\v 13 ThenВҰ192 eveningВҰ194 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ197 came, \add and that was the end of\add* the thirdВҰ199 dayВҰ198.
\p
\v 14 Then GodВҰ203 saidВҰ202, вҖңLet there be lights in the sky to separateВҰ208 daytime from nighttimeВҰ212, so they'll be signsВҰ214, and for \add indicating\add* seasonsВҰ215, and for \add tracking\add* daysВҰ216 and yearsВҰ217.
\v 15 They must function as lightsВҰ220 in the sky that shine \add lightВҰ223\add* on the earthВҰ226.вҖқ Everything happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 16 so GodВҰ232 made the twoВҰ235 large lightsВҰ236, the larger, brighter light to rule the dayВҰ243, and the smallerВҰ247 light to rule the nightВҰ249, and he \add also\add* made the starsВҰ251.
\v 17 HeВҰ254 put those lights in the sky to shine \add lightВҰ258\add* on the earthВҰ261,
\v 18 and to oversee the daytime and the nighttimeВҰ265, and to distinguish between the lightВҰ268 and the darknessВҰ270. AndВҰ273 GodВҰ272 sawВҰ271 that \add what he had done\add* was goodВҰ275.
\v 19 ThenВҰ277 eveningВҰ279 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ282 came, \add and that was the end of\add* the fourthВҰ284 dayВҰ283.
\p
\v 20 Then GodВҰ288 saidВҰ287, вҖңLet the watersВҰ290 be full of with swarmsВҰ289 of livingВҰ293 creaturesВҰ292, and let birds fly in the sky aboveВҰ296 the earthВҰ298.вҖқ
\v 21 SoВҰ305 God created the great seaВҰ309 creatures and every kind of livingВҰ315 creature that moves whichВҰ318 the watersВҰ320 swarmВҰ319 with, and every kind of winged bird. And God sawВҰ328 that \add what he had done\add* was goodВҰ332,
\v 22 and he blessedВҰ334 them, saying, вҖңBe fruitfulВҰ338 and multiply and fillВҰ340 the watersВҰ343 in the seas, and let the birds multiply on the earthВҰ347.вҖқ
\v 23 ThenВҰ349 eveningВҰ351 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ354 came, \add and that was the end of\add* the fifthВҰ356 dayВҰ355.
\p
\v 24 Then GodВҰ360 said, вҖңLet the land bring forth every kind of living creature: livestockВҰ366 and every crawling creature and every kind of living thing on the earthВҰ362.вҖқ Everything happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 25 so he made every kind of creature of the earthВҰ381, and every kind of livestock, and every kind of crawling creature on the ground. And GodВҰ377 sawВҰ393 that \add what he had done\add* was goodВҰ397.
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ399 GodВҰ400 saidВҰ399, вҖңLet us make man in our imageВҰ403, accordingВҰ404 to our likenessВҰ404, and let them rule over the fishВҰ406 in the seaВҰ407 and over the birds in the sky and over the livestock and over all the earth, and over every creature moving on the earth.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:26: \xt 1Cor 11:7.\x*
\v 27 ThenВҰ422 God created humankindВҰ427 in his image, \add yes,\add* created in the image of GodвҖ”male andВҰ422 femaleВҰ434 he created them.\x + \xo 1:27-28: \xt Gen 5:1-2.\x*
\v 28 ThenВҰ438 GodВҰ440 blessedВҰ438 them and told them, вҖңBe fruitfulВҰ444 and multiply, and fillВҰ446 the earth and take control of it. You're in charge of the fishВҰ452 in the seaВҰ453 and the birds in the sky and over every living thing that moves on the earth.вҖқ
\v 29 ThenВҰ464 GodВҰ465 said, вҖңLook, I've given you every plantВҰ473 throughout the whole earthВҰ483 that yields seed, andВҰ464 every tree that has fruitВҰ492 with a seed or seeds inside it. They will be yours for food,
\v 30 and to every living thing on the earth, and to every bird in the sky, and to everything moving on the earth thatВҰ515 has living breath in it, I've given every greenВҰ524 plantВҰ525 for food.вҖқ Everything happened \add exactly\add* as he commanded,
\v 31 and he sawВҰ531 everything that he'd made, and wow, it was \em very\em* goodВҰ541. ThenВҰ533 eveningВҰ545 came, and \add later\add* morningВҰ548 came, \add and that was the end of\add* the sixthВҰ550 dayВҰ549.
\c 2
\p
\v 1 So the heavensВҰ554 and the earthВҰ555 were completedВҰ553, along with everything in them.
\v 2 By the seventh day GodВҰ561 had finished his work, so he restedВҰ567 on the seventh day from all his work thatВҰ565 he'd done.\x + \xo 2:2-3: \xt Exo 20:11.\x*
\v 3 ThenВҰ576 GodВҰ577 blessedВҰ576 the seventhВҰ581 dayВҰ580 andВҰ576 declared it to be different from the other days, because on thatВҰ590 \add first Saturday\add*, he restedВҰ586 from all his work of creatingВҰ592.
\s1 The garden at Eden
\rem /s1 Adam and Eve
\p
\v 4 What follows tells\f + \fr 2:4 \ft This little formula is sometimes known as a вҖҳtoledothвҖҷ (or вҖҳtЕҚlЙҷdЕҚtвҖҷ, from the Hebrew word) and seems to mark a new section, but it's debated whether this part belongs at the bottom of the previous section, or at the top of the following section. We're assuming the later here.\f* \add more details about\add* the history of what God did when he createdВҰ601 the heavens and the earth:
\rem /s1 The Garden of Eden; The Man and Woman in Eden; Another Account of the Creation
\p During the time when Yahweh God\f + \fr 2:4 \ft This is the first occurrence of the Hebrew letters вҖҳЧҷЧ”Ч•Ч”вҖҷ (YHWH) in the Bible, which we find out later (in Exodus 3, also compiled by Mosheh/Moses) is God's actual name. Although the vowels which go with those four consonants have been lost over the millennia, most scholars believe вҖҳYahwehвҖҷ to be the best guess that we can make. (It's certainly NOT вҖҳJehovahвҖҷ, which was a historical mistake made by confusing the vowels of two different words.) Some older translations use \sc LORD\sc* which is NOT a translation of вҖҳЧҷЧ”Ч•Ч”вҖҷ (which means вҖҳI amвҖҷ), but which represents confusion over the more recent Jewish (but non-Biblical) custom of not pronouncing God's name (and which makes one wonder what's the use of telling people your name if they're then not allowed to use it).\f* made the earth and the heavens,
\v 5 there weren't yet any bushes growing on the earthВҰ615, and no plants had yet sprung up in the countrysideВҰ612, because YahwehВҰ625 GodВҰ626 had not yet made it rain, and nor were there any people yet to till the ground.
\v 6 HoweverВҰ643, a mist cameВҰ638 up from the ground andВҰ637 wateredВҰ642 the entireВҰ645 surfaceВҰ647 of the land.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ654 YahwehВҰ652 GodВҰ653 formedВҰ651 the \add first\add* man out of the dust on the ground and he breathed into his nostrilsВҰ662 the breath of lifeВҰ664, and the man became a living person.\x + \xo 2:7: \xt 1Cor 15:45.\x*
\p
\v 8 Now in the east, YahwehВҰ671 GodВҰ672 had plantedВҰ670 a gardenВҰ673 in EdenВҰ675, andВҰ670 he put the man thereВҰ678 that he had formedВҰ683.
\v 9 He \add also\add* caused all kinds of trees to grow thereвҖ”\add some\add* that are pleasant to look at and good for food. In the middleВҰ700 of the gardenВҰ701 was the tree of lifeВҰ699 and the tree of the knowledgeВҰ703 of good and evil\x + \xo 2:9: \xt Rev 2:7; 22:2,14.\x*
\p
\v 10 A riverВҰ707 flowed out of EdenВҰ710 to waterВҰ711 the gardenВҰ714, andВҰ707 thenВҰ707 from thereВҰ715 it split into fourВҰ718 rivers.
\v 11 The first river was named PishonВҰ723, and itВҰ724 winds aroundВҰ725 through the entireВҰ727 regionВҰ729 of HavilahВҰ730, whereВҰ731 there'sВҰ733 goldВҰ734.
\v 12 The goldВҰ736 from there is \add very pure\add*, and there's also \add a type of fragrant resin\add* and onyx \add gemstones\add* there.
\v 13 The secondВҰ748 riverВҰ747 was named GihonВҰ749, andВҰ745 itВҰ750 winds through the entireВҰ753 regionВҰ755 of CushВҰ756.
\v 14 The thirdВҰ760 river was named TigrisВҰ761, and it flowed east of the AsshurВҰ765 \add region\add*, and thenВҰ758 the fourthВҰ767 river was \add named\add* Frat.
\p
\v 15 YahwehВҰ772 GodВҰ773 tookВҰ771 the man and put him in the gardenВҰ778 at EdenВҰ774 to cultivate and maintain it
\v 16 andВҰ784 instructedВҰ784 him, вҖңYouВҰ785 can eat as much \add fruit\add* as you want from any treeВҰ792 in the gardenВҰ794,
\v 17 butВҰ798 you mustn't eat from the treeВҰ798 of the knowledgeВҰ799 of good andВҰ798 evil, because the dayВҰ806 you eat its \add fruit\add* you'll certainly die.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ812 YahwehВҰ813 GodВҰ814 saidВҰ812, вҖңIt's not goodВҰ817 for the man to be aloneВҰ820, so I'll make a suitable helperВҰ825 for him.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 NowВҰ838 YahwehВҰ829 GodВҰ830 \add ?had\add* formedВҰ828 every living thing of the countrysideВҰ837 and every bird of the sky from the ground, so he broughtВҰ843 them to the man to see what he would call them, and whatever the man calledВҰ855 each living creatureВҰ859, that would become its nameВҰ862.
\v 20 The man gave namesВҰ866 to all the \add various\add* livestock and to the birds of the sky and to every living creature in the countrysideВҰ874, butВҰ864 none of them was a suitable \add companion\add* to help him.
\p
\v 21 SoВҰ882 YahwehВҰ883 GodВҰ884 caused the man to go into a deep sleep, and thenВҰ882 while he was sleeping, he removed one of his ribs and closedВҰ894 up \add over\add* its place with fleshВҰ895.
\v 22 ThenВҰ902 YahwehВҰ899 GodВҰ900 used the rib whichВҰ905 he had takenВҰ907 from the man to form into a womanВҰ911, andВҰ898 he broughtВҰ912 her to the man,
\v 23 and the man said:
\q1 вҖңNow this is bone from my bonesВҰ922
\q2 and flesh from my flesh.
\q1 She'll be named вҖҳwomanВҰ927вҖҷ
\q2 because she came from a man.вҖқ
\m
\v 24 So that's why a manВҰ939 leavesВҰ937 his fatherВҰ942 and motherВҰ945, and becomes united to his wife, and the two of them become one being.\x + \xo 2:24: \xt Mat 19:5; Mrk 10:7-8; 1Cor 6:16; Eph 5:31.\x*
\p
\v 25 At that time, both the man andВҰ952 his wife were nakedВҰ954, butВҰ952 they had no sense of shame.
\c 3
\s1 The couple disobey God
\rem /s1 The Fall of Man; Human Disobedience; The Man and Woman Sin; The First Sin and Its Punishment
\p
\v 1 Now the snakeВҰ960 was the craftiestВҰ962 of all the \add вүҲwild\add* animalsВҰ964 thatВҰ966 YahwehВҰ968 God had created, andВҰ960 \add one day\add* he asked the womanВҰ973, вҖңDid God really command you to not eatВҰ980 \add fruit\add* from any of the trees in the gardenВҰ983?вҖқ\x + \xo 3:1: \xt Rev 12:9; 20:2.\x*
\p
\v 2 вҖңNo,вҖқ answered the womanВҰ986, вҖңweВҰ994 can eatВҰ994 the fruitВҰ990 from \add any\add* of the trees in the gardenВҰ993,
\v 3 except from the treeВҰ997 that is in the centre. He commanded \add us\add* to not eatВҰ1005 that fruitВҰ996 or even touchВҰ1008 it, because if we do, we will dieВҰ1012!вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ButВҰ1014 the serpent said to the womanВҰ1018, вҖңIt's not definite that you'll die.
\v 5 Actually, God knows that as soon as you eatВҰ1029 fruit from that tree, you'll understand new things, so that you will know \add what's\add* right and \add what's\add* wrong just like God does.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 The womanВҰ1040 saw that the tree's \add fruit looked\add* good to eat and that the tree itself was very attractive, plus she wanted \add to eat\add* the fruit so that it would make her wise. SoВҰ1039 she picked some of the fruit and ate it and she also gave \add some of it\add* to her husbandВҰ1059 \add who was there\add* with her, and he ate it \add too\add*.
\v 7 \add Immediately\add* they both had new understanding and they felt theirВҰ1065 nakednessВҰ1068. SoВҰ1063 they sewedВҰ1070 \add some\add* figВҰ1072 leaves together and made skirts for themselves.
\p
\v 8 \add Late that afternoon,\add* during the cool time of the dayВҰ1086, the man andВҰ1077 his wife heardВҰ1077 YahwehВҰ1081 God's voice as he walked in the garden, butВҰ1077 they hid from him behind some trees in the garden,
\v 9 so YahwehВҰ1098 GodВҰ1099 calledВҰ1097 out to the man, вҖң\add Adam,\add* whereВҰ1105 are you?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңI heardВҰ1111 you \add walking\add* in the gardenВҰ1112,вҖқ he replied, вҖңbutВҰ1107 I was scared because I was nakedВҰ1116, so I hid \add myselfВҰ1118\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңWho told you that you're nakedВҰ1125?вҖқ Yahweh God asked. вҖңHave you eatenВҰ1136 \add the fruit\add* that I told you not to eatВҰ1133?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңThe womanВҰ1140 that you put here beside me,вҖқ answered the man, вҖңshe gaveВҰ1145 me \add some\add* fruit from the treeВҰ1150 andВҰ1138 I ateВҰ1151 it.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ1153 YahwehВҰ1154 GodВҰ1155 asked the woman, вҖңWhat did you do?вҖқ\x + \xo 3:13: \xt 2Cor 11:3; 1Tim 2:14.\x*
\p вҖңThe snakeВҰ1163 tricked me, so I ate \add some of the fruit\add*,вҖқ the woman replied.
\s1 God's judgements after they disobeyed
\rem /s1 God Pronounces Judgment
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ1167 YahwehВҰ1168 GodВҰ1169 saidВҰ1167 to the snakeВҰ1173,
\q1 вҖңBecause you've done this you'll be cursedВҰ1177 more than all the livestock,
\q2 and more than every \add вүҲwild\add* animalВҰ1183.
\q1 \add Now\add* you'll move along on your bellyВҰ1187,
\q2 and you'll eatВҰ1190 dust all the rest of your lifeВҰ1194.
\q1
\v 15 I'll put hostilityВҰ1196 between you and the womanВҰ1201
\q2 between your descendants and hers.
\q1 He will crush your head
\q2 and you'll strike his heel.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:15: \xt Rev 12:17.\x*
\p
\v 16 To the womanВҰ1216 God saidВҰ1217,
\q1 вҖңI'll sharply increase your pain in childbirth.
\q2 You'll produce childrenВҰ1224 in pain.
\q1 Your desire will be for your husband
\q2 and he will rule over you.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 Then \add God\add* said to the man,\x + \xo 3:17-18: \xt Heb 6:8.\x*
\q1 вҖңBecause you did what your wife told you
\q2 and ateВҰ1243 from that treeВҰ1246
\q2 that I'd told you not to eat from,
\q1 then the ground will be cursedВҰ1253 because of you.
\q1 You'll have to work hard to get food from it
\q2 all the rest of your lifeВҰ1260.
\q1
\v 18 It'llВҰ1267 produce thornsВҰ1262 andВҰ1262 thistles for you
\q2 although you'll eatВҰ1266 the crops from the countrysideВҰ1270.
\q1
\v 19 You'll eat bread with sweat drops on your nose
\q2 untilВҰ1276 you return to the ground
\q2 because you were takenВҰ1283 out of the ground.
\q1 \add Yes,\add* you were \add created\add* from dust,
\q2 and you'll return back to dust.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ1293 the man named his wife вҖҳHavvahВҰ1297вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳlivingВҰ1304вҖҷ)\add* because she would become the motherВҰ1301 of all future people.
\v 21 ThenВҰ1306 YahwehВҰ1307 GodВҰ1308 made clothesВҰ1313 from \add animal\add* skins for AdamВҰ1309 and his wifeВҰ1310 and he dressed them.
\s1 The humans get expelled from the garden
\rem /s1 Adam and Eve Are Sent Out of the Garden
\p
\v 22 Then YahwehВҰ1318 GodВҰ1319 saidВҰ1316, вҖңSee, the man has becomeВҰ1322 like one of us, being aware of goodВҰ1326 and evil. ButВҰ1316 now, he mustn't \add be allowed\add* to reach out his handВҰ1333 and also takeВҰ1334 \add fruit\add* from the treeВҰ1336 of lifeВҰ1337 and eatВҰ1338 it and liveВҰ1339 foreverВҰ1340.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:22: \xt Rev 22:14.\x*
\v 23 SoВҰ1342 YahwehВҰ1343 GodВҰ1344 expelled \add them\add* out of the gardenВҰ1345 in EdenВҰ1347 to workВҰ1348 the soil from which \add Adam\add* had been takenВҰ1353.
\p
\v 24 After he expelled them, he placed sentries on the east side of the gardenВҰ1362 in EdenВҰ1364, as well as a fiery swordВҰ1370 that swung around in every direction to guardВҰ1372 the pathВҰ1375 to the treeВҰ1376 of lifeВҰ1377.
\c 4
\s1 Kayin (Cain) murders Hevel (Abel)
\rem /s1 Cain Murders Abel; Cain, Abel, and Seth; Cain and Abel
\p
\v 1 Then Adam \add вүҲslept with\add* his wife Havvah \add (EveВҰ1384)\add*, and she conceivedВҰ1386 and \add in due course \add* gave birthВҰ1387 to Kayin (CainВҰ1390). вҖңYahwehВҰ1396 \add вүҲhas enabled me to produce\add* a man,вҖқ she said.
\v 2 \add Eventually\add* she also gave birthВҰ1399 to Kayin's brother, Hevel \add (AbelВҰ1405)\add*. Hevel became a shepherd, while Kayin became a crop farmer.
\v 3 Some \add months\add* later, Kayin broughtВҰ1419 some of what he'd grown in the ground as an offeringВҰ1423 to YahwehВҰ1424,
\v 4 and also Hevel broughtВҰ1427 the best portions from some of the firstbornВҰ1431 of his flockВҰ1432. Now YahwehВҰ1435 was pleased with Hevel and his offering,\x + \xo 4:4: \xt Heb 11:4.\x*
\v 5 butВҰ1443 heВҰ1450 didn'tВҰ1449 even look towards Kayin and his offering. Kayin got very angry and his face showed his displeasure.
\v 6 ThenВҰ1457 YahwehВҰ1458 saidВҰ1457 to Kayin, вҖңWhy are you so angry? And why are you frowning like that?
\v 7 If you do what's right, won'tВҰ1469 you be honoured? ButВҰ1474 if you don'tВҰ1469 do what's right, sinВҰ1478 is crouchingВҰ1479 in the doorway wanting to have you, butВҰ1474 you have the control over it.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add One day,\add* Kayin spoke to his brother HevelВҰ1491 when they were \add out\add* in the countrysideВҰ1495, and thenВҰ1487 Kayin attacked him and killedВҰ1502 him.\x + \xo 4:8: \xt Mat 23:35; Luk 11:51; 1Yhn 3:12.\x*
\p
\v 9 \add Later\add* YahwehВҰ1505 asked Kayin, вҖңWhere's your brother HevelВҰ1510?вҖқ
\p вҖңI don'tВҰ1513 knowВҰ1514,вҖқ he replied, вҖңIt's not my job to look after my brother.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңWhat have youВҰ1521 done?вҖқ Yahweh asked. вҖңYour brother'sВҰ1524 bloodВҰ1523 is calling out to me from the ground.\x + \xo 4:10: \xt Heb 12:24.\x*
\v 11 SoВҰ1531 now you're cursedВҰ1532 andВҰ1531 banished from the soil thatВҰ1537 your brother'sВҰ1546 bloodВҰ1545 soaked into as a result of your actions.
\v 12 Whenever you till \add and plant\add* the ground, itВҰ1556 will no longer produce good yields for you. You'll be a fugitive and wanderingВҰ1561 \add refugee\add* on the earthВҰ1564.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖңMy punishment is more than I can bear,вҖқ Kayin \add complained\add* to YahwehВҰ1570.
\v 14 вҖңLook, you're now driving me \add away\add* from the ground \add I've been cultivating\add* to somewhere where you won't be able to see me. I'll be a wanderingВҰ1585 \add refugee\add* on the earthВҰ1587, and anyone who finds me will kill me.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңVery well,вҖқ, replied Yahweh andВҰ1604 declared, вҖңIf anyoneВҰ1600 killsВҰ1600 Kayin, thenВҰ1594 that person will receive a sevenВҰ1602 times greater \add sentence\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ1594 Yahweh marked Kayin so that no one who found him would kill him,
\v 16 and KayinВҰ1617 left Yahweh'sВҰ1619 presence and settled in the land of NodВҰ1623 to the east of EdenВҰ1626.
\s1 Kayin's descendants
\rem /s1 Beginnings of Civilization; The Descendants of Cain
\p
\v 17 Then Kayin slept with his wife and she conceivedВҰ1633 and gaveВҰ1634 birthВҰ1634 to Hanoch (EnochВҰ1637). Then Kayin founded a townВҰ1640 and named it Hanoch after his son.
\v 18 \add Eventually\add* HanochВҰ1649 fathered Irad, and Irad fathered Mehuyael, and Mehuyael father Methushael, and Methushael fathered Lemech (LamechВҰ1667).
\v 19 Lemech had twoВҰ1673 wivesВҰ1674: the first was named AdahВҰ1677 andВҰ1678 the secondВҰ1679 was TsillahВҰ1680 (Zillah).
\v 20 AdahВҰ1683 gaveВҰ1682 birthВҰ1682 to Yaval (JabalВҰ1686) who became the ancestor of people who live in tents andВҰ1692 rear cattle.
\v 21 His brother's nameВҰ1694 was Yuval (JubalВҰ1696) and he became the ancestor of people who play stringed and wind instrumentsВҰ1704.
\v 22 TsillahВҰ1706 gave birth to Tuval-Kayin (TubalВҰ1713-CainВҰ1714) who forged all \add kinds of\add* tools out of bronzeВҰ1719 andВҰ1706 iron. His sisterВҰ1721 was \add named\add* NaamahВҰ1725.
\v 23 ThenВҰ1727 Lemech said to his wives:
\q1 вҖңAdahВҰ1730 andВҰ1727 TsillahВҰ1731, listenВҰ1732 to me.
\q2 My wives, take notice of my words;
\q1 I killed a man who had woundedВҰ1741 me;
\q2 I killed a young man who hurt me.
\q1
\v 24 If \add killers of\add* Kayin would be sentenced sevenВҰ1752 times as much,
\q2 then \add anyone who kills me\add* should be sentenced \em seventy-seven\em* times as much.вҖқ
\s1 Shet's descendants
\rem /s1 Seth and Enosh
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ1754 AdamВҰ1755 slept with his wife againВҰ1756 and she bore a son and named him Shet (SethВҰ1766) \add (which means вҖҳgivenвҖҷ)\add* because she had said, вҖңGodВҰ1771 has given me anotherВҰ1773 son in placeВҰ1774 of HevelВҰ1775 who was killedВҰ1777 by Kayin.вҖқ
\v 26 \add Eventually\add* Shet also had a son andВҰ1780 named him EnoshВҰ1791. That was when \add people\add* began using Yahweh'sВҰ1796 name \add вүҲwhen they prayed for help\add*.
\c 5
\s1 Adam's (important) descendants
\rem /s1 From Adam to Noah; Adam's Descendants to Noah and His Sons; The Descendants of Adam
\r (1 Chr. 1:1-4)
\p
\v 1 This is the list of Adam'sВҰ1802 descendantsВҰ1801. When GodВҰ1805 had createdВҰ1804 humankindВҰ1806, he made them in his own likenessВҰ1807.\x + \xo 5:1-2: \xt Gen 1:27-28.\x*
\v 2 He createdВҰ1814 them as male and femaleВҰ1813, and he blessedВҰ1815 them and named them вҖҳhumansВҰ1821вҖҷ.\x + \xo 5:2: \xt Mat 19:4; Mrk 10:6.\x*
\v 3 When AdamВҰ1827 was 130 years old, he had \add a son\add* who was like him in many ways, and he named him Shet (SethВҰ1838).
\v 4 After Shet's birth, AdamВҰ1843 lived \add another\add* 800 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ1853 and daughtersВҰ1854.
\v 5 SoВҰ1856 AdamВҰ1860 livedВҰ1863 a totalВҰ1857 of 930 years, andВҰ1856 \add thenВҰ1856\add* he diedВҰ1869.
\p
\v 6 When Shet was 105 yearsВҰ1876 old, he had \add a son named\add* EnoshВҰ1882.
\v 7 After Enosh'sВҰ1891 birth, SethВҰ1886 livedВҰ1884 \add another\add* 807 yearsВҰ1893 and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ1898 and daughtersВҰ1899.
\v 8 SoВҰ1901 ShetВҰ1906 lived a totalВҰ1902 of 912 years, andВҰ1901 \add thenВҰ1901\add* he diedВҰ1913.
\p
\v 9 When EnoshВҰ1917 was 90 years old, he had \add a son named\add* KenanВҰ1923.
\v 10 After Kenan'sВҰ1931 birth, EnoshВҰ1926 livedВҰ1925 \add another\add* 815 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ1939 and daughtersВҰ1940.
\v 11 SoВҰ1942 EnoshВҰ1946 lived a totalВҰ1943 of 905 yearsВҰ1948, andВҰ1942 \add thenВҰ1942\add* he diedВҰ1952.
\p
\v 12 WhenВҰ1960 KenanВҰ1956 was 70 years old, he had \add a son named\add* MahalalelВҰ1962.
\v 13 AfterВҰ1968 Mahalalel'sВҰ1970 birth, KenanВҰ1965 livedВҰ1964 \add another\add* 840 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ1977 and daughtersВҰ1978.
\v 14 SoВҰ1980 KenanВҰ1984 lived a totalВҰ1981 of 910 yearsВҰ1986, andВҰ1980 \add thenВҰ1980\add* he diedВҰ1990.
\p
\v 15 When MahalalelВҰ1994 was 65 yearsВҰ1996 old, he had \add a son named\add* YaredВҰ2002 (Jared).
\v 16 After Yared'sВҰ2010 birth, MahalalelВҰ2005 livedВҰ2004 \add another\add* 830 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ2017 and daughtersВҰ2018.
\v 17 SoВҰ2020 MahalalelВҰ2024 lived a totalВҰ2021 of 895 years, andВҰ2020 \add thenВҰ2020\add* he diedВҰ2031.
\p
\v 18 When YaredВҰ2036 was 162 years old, he had \add a son named\add* Hanoch (EnochВҰ2045).
\v 19 After Hanoch'sВҰ2054 birth, YaredВҰ2049 livedВҰ2047 \add another\add* 800 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ2059 and daughtersВҰ2060.
\v 20 SoВҰ2062 YaredВҰ2067 lived a totalВҰ2063 of 962 years, andВҰ2062 \add thenВҰ2062\add* he diedВҰ2074.
\p
\v 21 When HanochВҰ2078 was 65 years old, he had \add a son named\add* Metushalah (MethuselahВҰ2085).
\v 22 After Metushalah's birth, HanochВҰ2088 walkedВҰ2087 with GodВҰ2091 for 300 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ2101 and daughtersВҰ2102.
\v 23 SoВҰ2104 HanochВҰ2108 lived a totalВҰ2105 of 365 years.
\v 24 HanochВҰ2117 walkedВҰ2116 with God, andВҰ2116 \add thenВҰ2116\add* he was not \add there\add*, because God tookВҰ2124 him \add away\add*.\x + \xo 5:24: \xt Heb 11:5; Yud 14.\x*
\p
\v 25 When Metushalah was 187 years old, he had \add a son named\add* LemekВҰ2139 (Lamech).
\v 26 After Lemek'sВҰ2147 birth, Metushalah livedВҰ2141 \add another\add* 782 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ2155 and daughtersВҰ2156.
\v 27 SoВҰ2158 MetushalahВҰ2162 lived a totalВҰ2159 of 969 years, andВҰ2158 \add thenВҰ2158\add* he diedВҰ2169.
\p
\v 28 When LemekВҰ2174 was 182 years old, he had a son
\v 29 andВҰ2183 he named him NoahВҰ2187 \add (whichВҰ2197 sounds like the Hebrew word for вҖҳreliefвҖҷ) because\add* he said, вҖңThis son will give us relief from the difficult work thatВҰ2197 we have to do because YahwehВҰ2199 has cursedВҰ2198 the ground.вҖқ
\v 30 After Noah'sВҰ2208 birth, LemekВҰ2203 livedВҰ2201 \add another\add* 595 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ2216 and daughtersВҰ2217.
\v 31 SoВҰ2219 LemekВҰ2224 lived a totalВҰ2220 of 777 years, andВҰ2219 \add thenВҰ2219\add* he diedВҰ2231.
\p
\v 32 After NoahВҰ2236 was 500 years old, he had \add sons whose names were\add* Yafet (JaphethВҰ2252), ShemВҰ2246, and Ham.\f + \fr 5:32 \ft Gen 10:21 indicates that Yafet was the eldest, and Gen 9:24 indicates that Ham was the youngest.\f*
\c 6
\s1 Humankind's evil
\rem /s1 Noah and the Flood; Human Wickedness; The Wickedness of Humankind; The Flood; The flood and the tower of Babel
\p
\v 1 WhenВҰ2255 people beganВҰ2257 to multiply on the earth's surfaceВҰ2262, andВҰ2264 theyВҰ2265 were having daughtersВҰ2264,\x + \xo 6:1-4: \xt Yob 1:6; 2:1.\x*
\v 2 God'sВҰ2272 sonsВҰ2269 sawВҰ2268 that men's daughtersВҰ2274 were beautiful, andВҰ2268 they tookВҰ2279 any that they wanted for themselves as wivesВҰ2281.
\v 3 ThenВҰ2286 YahwehВҰ2287 saidВҰ2286, вҖңMy Spirit won'tВҰ2288 tolerate people forever, because theyВҰ2297 are physical beings, therefore their \add remainingВҰ2290\add* time will be 120 years.вҖқ
\v 4 The NEFILIM were on the earthВҰ2305 in those daysВҰ2306 and also afterВҰ2309 that, when the sonsВҰ2314 of GodВҰ2315 wentВҰ2313 to the daughtersВҰ2318 of humankindВҰ2319 and they bore children for them. INVESTIGATE They were the mighty \add warriorsВҰ2326\add* of longВҰ2325 agoвҖ”those famous menВҰ2326.\x + \xo 6:4: \xt Num 13:33.\x*
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ2332 YahwehВҰ2331 sawВҰ2330 that the humankind'sВҰ2335 wickedness on the earthВҰ2336 was extensive, and that everyВҰ2344 inclinationВҰ2339 of their inner thoughtsВҰ2340 was only evil all dayВҰ2346 long.\x + \xo 6:5-8: \xt Mat 24:37; Luk 17:26; 1Pe 3:20.\x*
\v 6 SoВҰ2353 YahwehВҰ2349 regretted that he had made humankindВҰ2355 on the earthВҰ2356 andВҰ2348 he was deeply saddened,
\v 7 so he saidВҰ2362, вҖңThis humankind that I created, I will completely destroy them from the surfaceВҰ2372 of the ground, along with the animalsВҰ2377, and crawling creatures and the birds of the sky, because I regretВҰ2386 that I made them.вҖқ
\v 8 However, YahwehВҰ2394 noticed Noah andВҰ2390 was pleased with him.
\s1 Noah makes a barge
\rem /s1 Noah; Noah Pleases God
\p
\v 9 This is the accountВҰ2398 of NoahВҰ2399: He was a manВҰ2401 who obeyed God, blamelessВҰ2403 among the people of his time and he walkedВҰ2409 around with God.\x + \xo 6:9: \xt 2Pe 2:5.\x*
\v 10 NoahВҰ2414 had threeВҰ2415 sonsВҰ2416: Yafet (JaphethВҰ2425), ShemВҰ2419, andВҰ2423 HamВҰ2422.
\p
\v 11 Now GodВҰ2430 noticed that \add humankind\add* was corrupt andВҰ2427 very violentВҰ2433.
\v 12 \add Yes,\add* GodВҰ2436 looked at the earth, andВҰ2435 wow, all the living creatures on the earth had corruptedВҰ2441 their behaviour.
\p
\v 13 So GodВҰ2457 told NoahВҰ2458, вҖңI've decided to put an endВҰ2459 to all people on earth because the earth is filled with violenceВҰ2469 because of them. So listen, I myself am going to destroyВҰ2472 all of them, along with the earth.
\v 14 Make yourselfВҰ2478 a wooden chest\f + \fr 6:14 \ft The reader might have expected the word вҖҳarkвҖҷ here, but sadly the Latin word вҖҳarcaвҖҷ meaning вҖҳlarge box, chestвҖҷ led to the English word вҖҳarkвҖҷ being invented, and why we can't use it here, is that now for most English readers, they picture a large boat in their minds when they hear that word. If you think about the вҖҳark of the covenantвҖҷ that uses the same word, hopefully you can understand how anything like a вҖҳboatвҖҷ is the wrong word picture, hence we've gone back to translating the actual Hebrew word here.\f* out of cypress. Build rooms inside it, and seal it both inside and outsideВҰ2491 withВҰ2492 resin.
\v 15 TheseВҰ2497 are the dimensions for it: 140m long, 23m wide, andВҰ2506 14m high.
\v 16 It must have a roof, butВҰ2514 the last half a metre between the sides and the roof should remain open. Put the doorВҰ2520 inВҰ2522 its side, and build lowerВҰ2524, middle, and upper decks.
\v 17 You seeВҰ2530, I'm going to floodВҰ2534 the earth with waterВҰ2535 to destroyВҰ2539 every creature that breathesВҰ2546. Everything that's on the earth will dieВҰ2554.
\v 18 \add ButВҰ2556\add* I'llВҰ2557 make an agreement with you, so you must go into this chest along with your wifeВҰ2567 and sonsВҰ2566 and their wivesВҰ2568,
\v 19 and you must take a pair, male and femaleВҰ2588, of everythingВҰ2573 that lives into the chest to keepВҰ2585 aliveВҰ2585 with you.
\v 20 Pairs of every kind of bird and animal, including every kind of creature that moves on the ground, will comeВҰ2603 to you so that you keepВҰ2605 them aliveВҰ2605,
\v 21 and you must takeВҰ2608 with you some of every different kind of food and store it in there for you and them to eat.
\v 22 SoВҰ2623 NoahВҰ2624 did \add that\add* exactly as GodВҰ2629 had specified.\x + \xo 6:22: \xt Heb 11:7.\x*
\c 7
\s1 The global flood
\rem /s1 The Flood Covers the Earth; The Flood; The Great Flood
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ2635 saidВҰ2634 to NoahВҰ2636, вҖңGo into the ark, you and all your householdВҰ2642, because I've seenВҰ2649 that you're the \add only\add* one who obeys me inВҰ2652 this generationВҰ2652.
\v 2 Take in seven male and female pairs of every kind of вҖҳcleanВҰ2671вҖҷ animal, and one male and female pair of the вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ animals,
\v 3 as well as seven male and femaleВҰ2683 pairs of every kind of flying bird \add in order\add* to preserve their kinds on the earthВҰ2691.
\v 4 Seven days from now I'll send fortyВҰ2702 days and nightsВҰ2705 of rain on the earthВҰ2701, and I'll eliminate every livingВҰ2711 thingВҰ2711 that I've made that's \add still\add* on the ground.
\v 5 SoВҰ2718 NoahВҰ2719 did everything that YahwehВҰ2724 had instructedВҰ2723 himВҰ2723 to do.
\p
\v 6 Noah was 600 years old when the floodВҰ2732 covered the earthВҰ2737,
\v 7 and he wentВҰ2739 into the \add wooden\add* chest along with his wife, his \add three\add* sonsВҰ2741 and their wivesВҰ2743, \add in order\add* to escape from the floodwatersВҰ2752.\x + \xo 7:7: \xt Mat 24:38-39; Luk 17:27.\x*
\v 8 вҖҳCleanвҖҷ and вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ animals, the birdsВҰ2766, and everything thatВҰ2761 lived on the ground
\v 9 cameВҰ2777 to Noah in male and femaleВҰ2785 pairs and wentВҰ2777 into the chest, just like GodВҰ2788 had instructedВҰ2787 Noah.
\v 10 ThenВҰ2793 when the sevenВҰ2794 daysВҰ2795 were up, waterВҰ2796 \add started\add* to floodВҰ2797 the earthВҰ2801.
\p
\v 11 When NoahВҰ2810 was 600 years old (and around the beginning of May), deep underwater geysers inВҰ2811 the ocean started spouting out water, and the skiesВҰ2827 began to drop heavy rain\x + \xo 7:11: \xt 2Pe 3:6.\x*
\v 12 that continued day andВҰ2830 nightВҰ2838 for fortyВҰ2835 days.
\v 13 That was the very dayВҰ2841 that NoahВҰ2844 and Yafet and Shem and HamВҰ2847 and their wivesВҰ2855 had all entered the \add wooden\add* chest.
\v 14 They had with them every kind of livingВҰ2866 creature, including every kind of livestock and every \add other\add* kind of creature that lives on the land, and every kind of bird \add and\add* everything \add else\add* that flies.
\v 15 They had come to NoahВҰ2893 \add in order\add* to enter the chestвҖ”two by two of every creature with the breathВҰ2905 of lifeВҰ2906.
\v 16 SoВҰ2908 \add pairs of\add* males and femalesВҰ2910 of every creature enteredВҰ2908 just as GodВҰ2918 had instructedВҰ2916 \add NoahВҰ2917\add*, thenВҰ2908 YahwehВҰ2920 \add closedВҰ2919 the door and\add* theyВҰ2914 were shut in.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ2933 the floodВҰ2924 came onto the earth for fortyВҰ2925 days, andВҰ2923 the waterВҰ2931 rose so that the \add wooden\add* chest was liftedВҰ2932 up right off the land.
\v 18 The water continued to rise and get deeper on the earthВҰ2946, and the chest floatedВҰ2947 along on top of the water.
\v 19 \add Eventually\add* the water on the earthВҰ2960 got so deep thatВҰ2966 all the highВҰ2965 mountainsВҰ2964 everywhere under the sky were under waterвҖ”
\v 20 \add in fact\add* the waterВҰ2978 rose over seven metres aboveВҰ2976 the tops of them.
\v 21 \add By\add* thenВҰ2982 every living creature that lived onВҰ2991 the earth had drownedвҖ”birdsВҰ2991, livestock, animalsВҰ2993, every creature that swarmsВҰ2996 upon the earth, andВҰ2982 all humankindВҰ3002.
\v 22 Everything that \add had\add* the breath of the spirit of lifeВҰ3009 inВҰ3013 its nostrilsВҰ3010, everything that \add lived\add* onВҰ3013 dry land, diedВҰ3014.
\v 23 That's how \add Yahweh\add* completely annihilated every livingВҰ3021 creature off the earthВҰ3043, including humankindВҰ3029 and livestock and crawling creatures and \add even\add* the birds. Everything was annihilated except for NoahВҰ3048 and those withВҰ3051 him inВҰ3051 the \add floating\add* chestВҰ3051,
\v 24 andВҰ3053 the earthВҰ3057 remained in full flood for 150 days.
\c 8
\s1 Waiting for the land to dry
\rem /s1 The End of the Flood; The Flood Recedes; The Flood Subsides
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ3062 GodВҰ3063 considered NoahВҰ3066 and all the livingВҰ3070 things and all the livestock thatВҰ3076 were withВҰ3078 him inВҰ3078 the \add floating\add* chestВҰ3078, and he caused a windВҰ3081 to pass over the earthВҰ3084, and the watersВҰ3086 \add started to\add* subsideВҰ3085
\v 2 and the underwater geysers and the rain was stopped.
\v 3 ThenВҰ3099 the water steadily recededВҰ3104 from the earthВҰ3102 andВҰ3099 after five months the water had gone down \add enough\add*
\v 4 that by October the \add wooden\add* chest was left sitting onВҰ3114 one of the AraratВҰ3123 mountainsВҰ3122.
\v 5 The waterВҰ3125 continued to recedeВҰ3128 untilВҰ3129 December when the tops of the mountainsВҰ3137 became visible.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ3139 after another fortyВҰ3141 days, NoahВҰ3144 openedВҰ3143 a windowВҰ3147 near the \add top\add* of the chest
\v 7 and he released a ravenВҰ3155 which kept flying out and returningВҰ3158 untilВҰ3159 the land started to dry out.
\v 8 ThenВҰ3166 NoahВҰ3167 \add also\add* released a doveВҰ3169 to seeВҰ3171 if the land was really out of the waterВҰ3173,
\v 9 butВҰ3178 the dove didn'tВҰ3178 find anywhere to land so it returnedВҰ3186 to the window because the surfaceВҰ3196 of the earthВҰ3199 was still wet, and he stretched out his arm and broughtВҰ3203 the dove back inside.
\v 10 NoahВҰ3217 waitedВҰ3210 another week andВҰ3210 thenВҰ3210 he released the doveВҰ3219 againВҰ3211
\v 11 and it returned to him in the eveningВҰ3228 and wow, it had a freshВҰ3233, green oliveВҰ3232 leaf in its beak. SoВҰ3224 now NoahВҰ3236 knewВҰ3235 that the land was out of the waterВҰ3240.
\v 12 ThenВҰ3250 he waitedВҰ3244 another week, andВҰ3244 released the doveВҰ3252 \add again\add*, butВҰ3244 this time it didn'tВҰ3253 come back to him.
\p
\v 13 So it was when Noah was 601 years old (in the monthВҰ3269 of WHAT MONTH onВҰ3262 the first day of the \add Jewish\add* new yearВҰ3266) the land was still drying out. So Noah made an opening in the top of the \add wooden\add* chest andВҰ3261 sawВҰ3280 that the land surfaceВҰ3283 \add there\add* was \add almost\add* dry.
\v 14 By the end of the next month, the land was fully dry.
\p
\v 15 Then GodВҰ3297 said to NoahВҰ3300,
\v 16 вҖңLeave the \add wooden\add* chest along with your sonsВҰ3309 and each of your wivesВҰ3310.
\v 17 Take out all the livingВҰ3317 creatures that are withВҰ3324 you, including the birdsВҰ3324 and livestock, and everything that crawls (CHECK FOR WORD CONSISTENCY) onВҰ3324 the ground, so that they'll proliferate and increase their numbers \add all\add* over the earthВҰ3337.
\v 18 SoВҰ3344 NoahВҰ3346 wentВҰ3344 outside, along with his sonsВҰ3347 andВҰ3348 each of their wivesВҰ3349.
\v 19 EveryВҰ3354 livingВҰ3356 creature, every crawling thingВҰ3359 and every bird, everything moving on the earthВҰ3367, wentВҰ3369 outside kind by kind.
\s1 Noah's sacrifice and Yahweh's promise
\rem /s1 Noah Offers a Sacrifice; God's Promise to Noah
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ3374 NoahВҰ3375 builtВҰ3374 an altar to YahwehВҰ3377, and he tookВҰ3378 \add some\add* of every kind of clean animal and every kind of clean bird, and he offered \add them as\add* burntВҰ3387 offerings onВҰ3388 the altar.
\v 21 \add WhenВҰ3390\add* YahwehВҰ3391 smelt the pleasingВҰ3395 aromaВҰ3394, he saidВҰ3396 \add to himself\add*, вҖңI'll never curseВҰ3404 the ground because of humankind again, even though the humankind's hearts are inclinedВҰ3412 from their youthВҰ3416 \add to do\add* evilВҰ3415 \add things\add*. And I'll never again \add destroyВҰ3421\add* everyВҰ3424 livingВҰ3426 thing again like I've \add just\add* done.
\p
\v 22 As long as the earthВҰ3434 \add continues to\add* exist,
\q1 seedtime and harvestВҰ3436 time,
\q1 coldВҰ3437 and heat,
\q1 summerВҰ3439 and winterВҰ3440,
\q1 dayВҰ3441 and nightВҰ3442,
\q1 will never \add stop happening\add*.
\c 9
\s1 God's agreement with Noah
\rem /s1 God's Covenant With Noah; The Covenant with Noah
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ3446 GodВҰ3447 blessedВҰ3446 NoahВҰ3450 and his sonsВҰ3453 and saidВҰ3454 to them, вҖңBe fruitfulВҰ3456 and multiply and fillВҰ3458 the earthВҰ3461.\x + \xo 9:1: \xt Gen 1:28.\x*
\v 2 \add Now\add* every living creature on the earthВҰ3470 will be afraid and terrified of you, including every bird \add that flies\add* in the sky, along withВҰ3476 every creature that moves on land, and all the fish in the ocean. I have put them \add all\add* under yourВҰ3463 authority.
\v 3 \add From now on\add* every creature thatВҰ3490 is aliveВҰ3493 and moves can be eaten as foodвҖ”just like I \add previously\add* provided you greenВҰ3497 plantsВҰ3498 for food, now I provide you everything \add for food\add*вҖ”
\v 4 the only exception is meat withВҰ3508 it's lifeВҰ3508 bloodВҰ3509 \add still\add* inВҰ3508 it.\x + \xo 9:4: \xt Lev 7:26-27; 17:10-14; 19:26; Deu 12:16,23; 15:23.\x*
\v 5 Also, I will certainly require bloodВҰ3516 as payment for people's livesВҰ3517: if anyone murders another person, I require that the murderer must die, andВҰ3513 even if an animalВҰ3522 kills a human being, I require that itВҰ3523 must die.
\v 6 \add YesВҰ3545,\add* if anyoneВҰ3535 shedsВҰ3535 human blood, the others must shed the murderer's blood, because GodВҰ3543 made human beings inВҰ3538 his imageВҰ3542.\x + \xo 9:6: \xt Exo 20:13; Gen 1:26.\x*
\v 7 \add SoВҰ3549 thenВҰ3549,\add* be fruitfulВҰ3550 and multiplyвҖ”have children onВҰ3556 the earthВҰ3553 and become numerous.\x + \xo 9:7: \xt Gen 1:28.\x*
\p
\v 8 Then GodВҰ3560 saidВҰ3559 to NoahВҰ3563 and his sonsВҰ3566,
\v 9 вҖңNow listen, I am making an agreement with you andВҰ3577 your future descendantsВҰ3579,
\v 10 and \add it's also\add* with every living creatureВҰ3585 that is with you: with the birdsВҰ3589, the livestockВҰ3590, and every living thing on the earth with you, from all that cameВҰ3597 out of the \add wooden\add* chest to every \add future\add* living thing on the earth.
\v 11 My agreement that I'm establishingВҰ3603 with youВҰ3607 is that all living things will never die from a flood again. \add That's right,\add* I will never \add use\add* a flood again to destroyВҰ3622 everything on the earthВҰ3623.вҖқ
\v 12 ThenВҰ3625 GodВҰ3626 added, вҖңThis is how I'll show everyoneВҰ3638 that I've made this agreement with you andВҰ3625 with all the livingВҰ3641 creaturesВҰ3640 that are with you, along with all future generationsВҰ3644:
\v 13 I'llВҰ3650 place my rainbow among the cloudsВҰ3651, and it'll be a signВҰ3653 of the agreement betweenВҰ3655 me and \add all life\add* onВҰ3651 the earthВҰ3657.
\v 14 SoВҰ3659 whenever IВҰ3660 cause clouds to form \add in the sky\add* andВҰ3659 a rainbow is visible in the clouds,
\v 15 thenВҰ3669 I'llВҰ3670 rememberВҰ3669 my agreement that's betweenВҰ3674 me and you and every kind of living creatureВҰ3679, and a floodВҰ3689 will never againВҰ3687 destroyВҰ3690 everything living.
\v 16 SoВҰ3695 whenever a rainbow appears among the cloudsВҰ3697, I'll seeВҰ3698 itВҰ3698 and rememberВҰ3699 my permanent agreement withВҰ3697 everyВҰ3705 livingВҰ3708 creatureВҰ3707 thatВҰ3712 lives \add and will live\add* onВҰ3697 the earthВҰ3715.вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ3717 GodВҰ3718 saidВҰ3717 to NoahВҰ3721, вҖң\add The rainbow\add* is the signВҰ3723 of the agreement thatВҰ3726 I have establishedВҰ3727 betweenВҰ3728 me andВҰ3717 every living thing on the earthВҰ3736.вҖқ
\s1 Noah's children
\rem /s1 Noah's Sons; The Sons of Noah; Noah and His Sons
\p
\v 18 Noah'sВҰ3742 sonsВҰ3740 who cameВҰ3743 out of the \add wooden\add* chest \add after the flood\add* were YafetВҰ3749 (Japheth), ShemВҰ3747, and Ham. (Ham became Canaan'sВҰ3753 fatherВҰ3752).
\v 19 They were Noah'sВҰ3759 three sonsВҰ3757 and from them the whole earthВҰ3764 became populated.
\p
\v 20 \add After a while,\add* NoahВҰ3767, who was a farmer, plantedВҰ3770 \add some grape\add* vines,
\v 21 and \add in due course\add* he drankВҰ3773 some of \add his\add* wine and got drunkВҰ3777, and he \add fell asleep\add* naked in his tent.
\v 22 Then HamВҰ3784 (Canaan'sВҰ3786 father) saw his father's nakednessВҰ3788 then went outsideВҰ3794 and told his brothersВҰ3793 \add what he'd seen\add*.
\v 23 SoВҰ3796 ShemВҰ3797 and YafetВҰ3798 tookВҰ3796 a robe, and holding it between their shouldersВҰ3805 they walkedВҰ3807 backwards into the tent and coveredВҰ3809 their father'sВҰ3812 nakedness. (TheirВҰ3806 facesВҰ3813 were towards the tent entrance, so they didn'tВҰ3817 see his nakedness.)
\v 24 \add Eventually,\add* NoahВҰ3821 woke up from his drunken sleep andВҰ3823 found out what his youngestВҰ3831 son (Ham) had done to him
\v 25 and saidВҰ3833, вҖңMay CanaanВҰ3835 be cursedВҰ3834 and become a slaveВҰ3836 of slavesВҰ3837 to his brothersВҰ3839!вҖқ
\v 26 ThenВҰ3841 he added, вҖңPraise YahwehВҰ3843 who's Shem's godВҰ3844. May CanaanВҰ3847 become Shem's slaveВҰ3848.
\v 27 May GodВҰ3852 expand Yafet's territory andВҰ3858 may heВҰ3851 live inВҰ3855 Shem'sВҰ3857 tentsВҰ3855. May CanaanВҰ3859 also become a slaveВҰ3860 of Yafet.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 After the floodВҰ3867, NoahВҰ3865 livedВҰ3863 another 350 years,
\v 29 andВҰ3874 so he was 950 years old when he diedВҰ3885.
\c 10
\s1 Noah's grandchildren and their clans
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Noah's Sons; Nations Descended from Noah; The Table of Nations
\r (1 Chr. 1:5-23)
\p
\v 1 These are the generations of Noah'sВҰ3892 sons, YafetВҰ3895 (Japheth), ShemВҰ3893, and HamВҰ3894, and their descendants born to them afterВҰ3899 the floodВҰ3900:
\s2 Yafet's (Japheth's) descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Japheth
\rem /s2 The Japhethites
\p
\v 2 Yafet's (Japheth'sВҰ3903) sonsВҰ3902 were GomerВҰ3904, MagogВҰ3905, MadaiВҰ3906, YavanВҰ3907, TubalВҰ3908, MeshechВҰ3909, and TirasВҰ3910.
\v 3 Gomer'sВҰ3913 sonsВҰ3912 were AshkenazВҰ3914, RifathВҰ3915, andВҰ3912 TogarmahВҰ3916.
\v 4 Yavan'sВҰ3919 sonsВҰ3918 were ElishahВҰ3920 and TarshishВҰ3921, and KittimВҰ3922\f + \fr 10:1 \ft These names ending with вҖҳ-imвҖҷ (the Hebrew plural) are possibly the names of the ensuing \em tribes\em* (e.g., вҖҳKittitesвҖҷ) and not the individuals. (Similarly for v13-14.)\f* and DodanimВҰ3923.
\v 5 From \add all\add* those \add descendants\add*, people spread out into areas near the coastВҰ3927, each group with their own languageВҰ3931, and with \add all\add* the clansВҰ3932 making up their nations.
\s2 Ham's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Ham
\rem /s2 The Hamites
\p
\v 6 Ham'sВҰ3936 sonsВҰ3935 were CushВҰ3937, EgyptВҰ3938 \add (Hebrew: Mitsrayim)\add*, PutВҰ3939, andВҰ3935 CanaanВҰ3940.
\v 7 Cush'sВҰ3943 sons were SebaВҰ3944, HavilahВҰ3945, SabtahВҰ3946, Raamah, and SabtekahВҰ3948. ThenВҰ3942 Raamah'sВҰ3947 sons were ShebaВҰ3951 and DedanВҰ3952.
\v 8 Cush was \add also\add* the fatherВҰ3955 of NimrodВҰ3958 who became a mightyВҰ3962 \add warrior\add* on the earthВҰ3963.
\v 9 Nimrod also became a terrific hunter \add noticed\add* by Yahweh, so people saidВҰ3976, вҖңLike Nimrod, a terrific hunter \add noticed\add* by Yahweh.вҖқ
\v 10 His kingdomВҰ3985 began in \add the cities of\add* BabelВҰ3986, ErechВҰ3987, Accad, andВҰ3983 CalnehВҰ3989, \add all\add* in the ShinarВҰ3991 regionВҰ3990.
\v 11 From that area he \add extended\add* to AsshurВҰ3998\f + \fr 10:11 \ft Known to us as вҖҳAssyriaвҖҷ.\f* where he builtВҰ3999 \add the cities of\add* NinevehВҰ4002, RehobotВҰ4005-Ir, CalahВҰ4009,
\v 12 and ResenВҰ4013, between NinevehВҰ4015 and the large cityВҰ4019 of CalahВҰ4017.
\p
\v 13 MitsrayimВҰ4022 fatheredВҰ4023 LudimВҰ4026, AnamimВҰ4029, LehabimВҰ4032, NaftuhimВҰ4035,
\v 14 PathrusimВҰ4039, and CasluhimВҰ4042 (who the PhilistinesВҰ4046 cameВҰ4044 from), and CaftorimВҰ4049.
\p
\v 15 CanaanВҰ4052 fatheredВҰ4053 TsidonВҰ4056 his firstbornВҰ4057, then HetВҰ4060,\f + \fr 10:15 \ft The ancestor of the Hittites.\f*
\v 16 YebusiВҰ4064, EmoriВҰ4067, GirgashiВҰ4069.
\v 17 HiviВҰ4073, ArqiВҰ4076, SiniВҰ4079,
\v 18 ArvadiВҰ4083, TsemariВҰ4086, andВҰ4081 HamatiВҰ4089. Later on, the Canaan clansВҰ4092 spread in all directions
\v 19 and their borderВҰ4096 went from SidonВҰ4098 toward GerarВҰ4100 as far as GazaВҰ4103, and thenВҰ4095 toward Sodom, AmorahВҰ4106 \add (Gomorrah)\add*, AdmahВҰ4107, and Tsevoim, as far as LashaВҰ4111.
\v 20 Those are Ham'sВҰ4116 descendants accordingВҰ4118 to their clansВҰ4117, languagesВҰ4118, regions, and nationsВҰ4120.
\s2 Shem's descendants
\rem /s1 Descendants of Shem
\rem /s2 The Semites
\p
\v 21 ShemВҰ4123 (the younger brotherВҰ4134 of YafetВҰ4135) also had \add some\add* sonsВҰ4131 andВҰ4123 became the ancestor of all the descendants of EberВҰ4133.
\v 22 Shem'sВҰ4139 sonsВҰ4138 were ElamВҰ4140, AsshurВҰ4141, ArpachshadВҰ4142, LudВҰ4143, andВҰ4142 AramВҰ4144.
\v 23 Aram'sВҰ4147 sonsВҰ4146 were UzВҰ4148, HulВҰ4149, GetherВҰ4150, andВҰ4146 MashВҰ4151.
\v 24 Arpachshad fathered Shelah, thenВҰ4153 Shelah fathered EberВҰ4162.
\v 25 Eber's two sons were Peleg andВҰ4164 YoktanВҰ4177. (Peleg'sВҰ4170 name \add means вҖҳdivisionвҖҷ,\add* because it was during his lifetime that the earthВҰ4174 was dividedВҰ4173.\f + \fr 10:25 \ft Often believed to refer to the division of languages after the building of the tower described in chapter 11.\f*)
\v 26 Yoktan fatheredВҰ4180 AlmodadВҰ4183, ShelefВҰ4186, HazarmavethВҰ4189, YerahВҰ4192,
\v 27 HadoramВҰ4196, UzalВҰ4199, DiklahВҰ4202,
\v 28 ObalВҰ4206, AbimaelВҰ4209, ShebaВҰ4212,
\v 29 OfirВҰ4216, HavilahВҰ4219, andВҰ4214 YobabВҰ4222. (All of those were the sonsВҰ4226 of YoktanВҰ4227.)
\v 30 They lived in the area from MeshaВҰ4231 thenВҰ4229 to Sefar in the easternВҰ4235 hills.
\v 31 Those are Shem'sВҰ4240 descendants according to their clansВҰ4241, languagesВҰ4242, regions, and nationsВҰ4244.
\p
\v 32 All of those are the clansВҰ4247 of Noah'sВҰ4250 sons, accordingВҰ4251 to their generations and nations, and from them the nations spread out across the earthВҰ4256 afterВҰ4257 the floodВҰ4258.
\c 11
\s1 The tower at Babel
\rem /s1 The Tower of Babel; The Tower of Babylon
\p
\v 1 Now the whole world had a single languageВҰ4265 and the same wordsВҰ4267,
\v 2 and as they migrated from the east, they discovered a plainВҰ4274 in the ShinarВҰ4276 regionВҰ4275 and settled thereВҰ4278.
\v 3 ThenВҰ4280 they saidВҰ4280 to each other, вҖңCome on, let's make bricks and cure them with fire.вҖқ SoВҰ4280 they had bricks instead of stonesВҰ4293, and they had tar for mortarВҰ4297.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ4299 they saidВҰ4299, вҖңCome on, let's buildВҰ4302 a cityВҰ4305 for ourselves and a towerВҰ4306 with itsВҰ4307 top in the sky, and let's make a reputation for ourselves, so that we don't get scatteredВҰ4315 all over the whole earthВҰ4321.вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ4323 YahwehВҰ4324 came down to see the cityВҰ4328 andВҰ4329 the towerВҰ4331 thatВҰ4332 the humansВҰ4335 were building
\v 6 and he saidВҰ4337, вҖңLook, they're \add just\add* one peopleВҰ4340 group, and they all speak the same languageВҰ4342. This is only the beginningВҰ4346 of what they can do \add together\add*вҖ”soon they'll be capable of doing anything they plan to do.
\v 7 Come on then, let's go down and confuseВҰ4360 theirВҰ4362 language so that they won'tВҰ4364 be able to understandВҰ4365 each other's words.вҖқ
\v 8 SoВҰ4372 thenВҰ4370 theyВҰ4380 stoppedВҰ4380 buildingВҰ4381 the cityВҰ4382 andВҰ4370 YahwehВҰ4371 caused them to scatterВҰ4370 over the whole world.
\v 9 That'sВҰ4401 why they named the city вҖҳBabelВҰ4389вҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳmixed-upвҖҷ)\add* because it was there that YahwehВҰ4394 mixed up everyone's languageВҰ4395 and then scatteredВҰ4400 them over the whole world.
\s1 Shem's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Shem; From Shem to Abram; Descendants of Shem
\r (1 Chr. 1:24-27)
\p
\v 10 This is the record of Shem'sВҰ4412 descendants: Two years afterВҰ4423 the floodВҰ4424, when Shem was 100 years old, he had \add a son named\add* Arpakshad.
\v 11 After Arpakshad was born, ShemВҰ4428 livedВҰ4426 \add another\add* 500 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4438 and daughtersВҰ4439.
\p
\v 12 When ArpakshadВҰ4442 was thirty-fiveВҰ4445 years old, heВҰ4443 had \add a son named\add* Shalah.
\v 13 After Shalah was born, Arpakshad livedВҰ4452 \add another\add* 403 yearsВҰ4460 and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4465 and daughtersВҰ4466.
\p
\v 14 When Shalah was thirtyВҰ4471 years old, heВҰ4470 had \add a son named\add* EberВҰ4476.
\v 15 After EberВҰ4485 was born, ShelahВҰ4480 livedВҰ4478 \add another\add* 403 yearsВҰ4487 and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4492 and daughtersВҰ4493.
\p
\v 16 When EberВҰ4498 was thirty-fourВҰ4500 years old, he had \add a son named\add* PelegВҰ4505.
\v 17 After PelegВҰ4514 was born, EberВҰ4509 livedВҰ4507 \add another\add* 430 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4521 and daughtersВҰ4522
\p
\v 18 When PelegВҰ4527 was thirtyВҰ4528 years old, he had \add a son named\add* ReuВҰ4533.
\v 19 After ReuВҰ4542 was born, PelegВҰ4537 livedВҰ4535 \add another\add* 209 yearsВҰ4544 and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4548 and daughtersВҰ4549.
\p
\v 20 When ReuВҰ4553 was thirty-twoВҰ4555 years old, he had \add a son named\add* SerugВҰ4560.
\v 21 After SerugВҰ4568 was born, ReuВҰ4563 livedВҰ4562 \add another\add* 207 yearsВҰ4570 and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4574 and daughtersВҰ4575.
\p
\v 22 WhenВҰ4583 SerugВҰ4579 was thirtyВҰ4580 years old, he had \add a son named\add* NahorВҰ4585.
\v 23 AfterВҰ4591 NahorВҰ4593 was born, SerugВҰ4588 livedВҰ4587 \add another\add* 200 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4597 and daughtersВҰ4598.
\p
\v 24 WhenВҰ4607 NahorВҰ4602 was twenty-nineВҰ4604 years old, he had \add a son named\add* TerahВҰ4609.
\v 25 AfterВҰ4615 TerahВҰ4617 was born, NahorВҰ4612 livedВҰ4611 \add another\add* 119 years and had \add other\add* sonsВҰ4625 and daughtersВҰ4626.
\p
\v 26 After TerahВҰ4631 was seventyВҰ4632 years old, he had \add sons whose names were\add* AbramВҰ4637, NahorВҰ4640, and HaranВҰ4643.
\s1 Terah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Terah; Descendants of Terah; The Family of Terah
\p
\v 27 This is the record of Terah's descendants: Terah's sons were AbramВҰ4652, NahorВҰ4655, and Haran and Haran had \add a son named\add* LotВҰ4663.
\v 28 While his fatherВҰ4671 was still alive, HaranВҰ4666 diedВҰ4665 in the land where he was born, in \add the city of\add* UrВҰ4674 where the Chaldeans lived.
\v 29 Meanwhile AbramВҰ4678 married SaraiВҰ4686 and Nahor married Milcah. (Milcah and \add her sister\add* IscahВҰ4699 were the daughtersВҰ4692 of \add Nahor'sВҰ4679 brother\add* HaranВҰ4694.)
\v 30 However, SaraiВҰ4702 wasn't able to get pregnant \add so they\add* didn'tВҰ4704 have any childrenВҰ4706.
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ4708 one day, TerahВҰ4709 gathered his son Abram and his grandson LotВҰ4716 (who was Haran'sВҰ4719 son), and his daughter-in-lawВҰ4725 SaraiВҰ4724 (who was Abram'sВҰ4712 wifeВҰ4726), and they \add all\add* left from \add the city of\add* UrВҰ4731 (where the Chaldeans livedВҰ4740), to travel to the regionВҰ4734 of CanaanВҰ4735, \add butВҰ4708\add* when they arrived at \add the city of\add* Haran, they \add decided to\add* live thereВҰ4741.
\v 32 ThenВҰ4743 when TerahВҰ4746 was 205 yearsВҰ4748 old, he \add diedВҰ4751\add* there in HaranВҰ4753.
\c 12
\s1 God commissions Abram to go
\rem /s1 Abram's travels; The Call of Abram; God's Call to Abram
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ4757 saidВҰ4756 to AbramВҰ4760, вҖңYou must leave your land and your relatives and your father's houseВҰ4766 and goВҰ4761 to the land thatВҰ4771 I'll show you.\x + \xo 12:1: \xt Acts 7:2-3; Heb 11:8.\x*
\v 2 I'll bless you and make you into a greatВҰ4776 nationВҰ4775. I'll make you famous and you'll be a blessing \add to others\add*.
\v 3 I'll bless everyone who blesses you, butВҰ4783 I'll curse anyone who curses you. All the families on the earth will be blessed because of you.\x + \xo 12:3: \xt Gal 3:8.\x*
\p
\v 4 SoВҰ4793 Abram left \add there\add* just as YahwehВҰ4798 had told him, andВҰ4793 LotВҰ4801 \add also\add* went with him. Abram was seventy-fiveВҰ4807 yearsВҰ4806 old when he left \add the city of\add* HaranВҰ4810.
\v 5 He tookВҰ4812 his wife SaraiВҰ4816 and his nephew LotВҰ4820 and all theirВҰ4828 possessions thatВҰ4829 they had accumulatedВҰ4830 and the peopleВҰ4833 who they had acquiredВҰ4836 in HaranВҰ4837, and they set out to goВҰ4839 to the land of CanaanВҰ4841.
\p WhenВҰ4812 they arrived in the Canaan regionВҰ4840,
\v 6 they continued travelling as far as the city of ShekemВҰ4851, to Moreh'sВҰ4854 oak treeВҰ4853. (The Canaanites were still living in that region at that time.)
\v 7 ThenВҰ4859 Yahweh came to Abram and told him, вҖңI'll giveВҰ4866 this land to yourВҰ4865 descendants.вҖқ SoВҰ4859 Abram builtВҰ4871 an altarВҰ4873 thereВҰ4872 \add and made a burnt offering\add* to Yahweh, who had appeared to him.\x + \xo 12:7: \xt Acts 7:5; Gal 3:16.\x*
\v 8 ThenВҰ4878 from there he went on to the hills to the east of Beyt-El (Beyt-ElВҰ4882) and pitchedВҰ4885 his tents, with Beyt-El on the west and AiВҰ4892 on the east. He builtВҰ4894 an altarВҰ4897 to Yahweh there, and \add sacrificed and\add* prayed to Yahweh
\v 9 before continuingВҰ4906 \add southВҰ4907 down\add* towardВҰ4907 the NegevВҰ4904 \add desert\add*.
\s1 Abram goes to Egypt
\rem /s1 Abram in Egypt; Abram and Sarai in Egypt
\p
\v 10 \add OneВҰ4918 time when\add* there was \add a drought causing\add* a severe food shortage, AbramВҰ4914 \add and his household\add* travelled \add west\add* across to EgyptВҰ4915 \add (MitsrayimВҰ4915)\add* to stay there.
\v 11 Just before they arrived in Mitsrayim, \add Abram\add* saidВҰ4929 to his wife SaraiВҰ4932, вҖңListen, you're a very beautifulВҰ4940 womanВҰ4939,
\v 12 so when the Egyptians seeВҰ4948 you they'll sayВҰ4951, вҖҳThis is his wife,вҖҷ andВҰ4945 they'll killВҰ4954 me butВҰ4945 let you liveВҰ4957.
\v 13 \add Please\add* tell them that you're my sisterВҰ4962 so they'll treat me well because of you and let me live.вҖқ\x + \xo 12:13: \xt Gen 20:2; 26:7.\x*
\v 14 SoВҰ4973 that's what happened when theyВҰ4977 entered MitsrayimвҖ”the Egyptians \add indeed\add* noticedВҰ4977 that Sarai was very beautifulВҰ4984,
\v 15 and \add when\add* Far'oh's \add (Pharaoh'sВҰ4991)\add* officialsВҰ4990 sawВҰ4988 her, so theyВҰ4988 told him \add about her beauty\add*, and she was takenВҰ4997 into Far'oh's \add palace\add*.
\v 16 He treated AbramВҰ5002 well \add (thinking he was the brother)\add*, so he \add was given\add* flocks and herds, male and female donkeys, male and female slaves, and camelsВҰ5015.
\p
\v 17 \add ButВҰ5017\add* YahwehВҰ5018 directed terrible plaguesВҰ5023 onto Far'ohВҰ5022 andВҰ5025 his householdВҰ5027 \add because of his taking\add* Abram'sВҰ5033 wifeВҰ5032 SaraiВҰ5031.
\v 18 SoВҰ5035 Far'ohВҰ5036 calledВҰ5035 for AbramВҰ5037 andВҰ5035 saidВҰ5038, вҖңWhat's this you've done to me? Why didn'tВҰ5045 you tell me that she's your wifeВҰ5050?
\v 19 Why did youВҰ5054 sayВҰ5054, вҖҳShe's my sisterВҰ5055,вҖҷ so that I took her in as a wife? Now then, here's your wife. Take her andВҰ5061 get out of here.вҖқ
\v 20 ThenВҰ5067 Far'ohВҰ5069 commandedВҰ5067 his \add officers\add*, and they sentВҰ5071 Abram and his wife away and everything that belonged to him.
\c 13
\s1 Abram and Lot part ways
\rem /s1 Abram and Lot Separate
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ5084 AbramВҰ5085 left EgyptВҰ5086 with his wife and everything that belonged to him, and \add their nephew\add* LotВҰ5094. \add They returned\add* to the Negev
\v 2 and \add now\add* Abram had become very wealthyВҰ5099, withВҰ5101 \add both\add* livestockВҰ5101, and silverВҰ5102 and goldВҰ5103.
\v 3 ThenВҰ5105 they continued \add north\add* through the NegevВҰ5107 as far as Beyt-El, to the placeВҰ5115 whereВҰ5116 his tents had been atВҰ5122 the beginningВҰ5122вҖ”between Beyt-El andВҰ5105 AiВҰ5128вҖ”
\v 4 to the placeВҰ5132 where he'd previously built an altarВҰ5133,\x + \xo 13:4: \xt Gen 12:8.\x* and AbramВҰ5141 \add sacrificed and\add* prayed to YahwehВҰ5143 there.
\p
\v 5 Now LotВҰ5147, who was travelling with AbramВҰ5151, also had flocks and herdsВҰ5155 and tentsВҰ5156,
\v 6 butВҰ5158 the land couldn't supportВҰ5160 them \add all\add* while they stayedВҰ5163 together. BecauseВҰ5161 \add the needs of\add* theirВҰ5168 combined assets were so \add demanding\add*, they couldn't all \add thrive\add* in one place
\v 7 and that led to strife between Abram'sВҰ5182 and Lot'sВҰ5187 herdsmen. Also, the CanaanitesВҰ5188 and the PerizzitesВҰ5189 were livingВҰ5191 in the land at that time.
\p
\v 8 SoВҰ5194 AbramВҰ5195 saidВҰ5194 to LotВҰ5198, вҖңLet's not have quarrelling between youВҰ5205 and I, or between yours herdsmenВҰ5207 and mine, because we're \add relatives\add*.
\v 9 Isn't the whole land available to you? So let's separateВҰ5221. If you go to the left then I'll go right, or if you go to the right then I'll go left.вҖқ
\v 10 LotВҰ5235 looked \add all around\add* and sawВҰ5239 that all the plain of the YordanВҰ5245 \add river valleyВҰ5244\add* was well-wateredВҰ5248 through towards Tso'ar, \add just\add* like Yahweh's gardenВҰ5259 \add had been\add* before he destroyedВҰ5251 SodomВҰ5255 and Amorah \add (GomorrahВҰ5258)\add*, and like the land of EgyptВҰ5263.\x + \xo 13:10: \xt Gen 2:10.\x*
\v 11 LotВҰ5270 choseВҰ5267 all of the YordanВҰ5275 plain for himself, and so he travelled to the east and they separatedВҰ5279 from each other.
\v 12 \add So\add* AbramВҰ5284 settled in the land of CanaanВҰ5288, and LotВҰ5289 settled in the citiesВҰ5291 of the plainВҰ5292 and movedВҰ5293 his tents as far as SodomВҰ5296.
\v 13 \add However,\add* the people of SodomВҰ5299 were extremely wickedВҰ5300, \add constantly\add* disobeying YahwehВҰ5302.
\s1 God promises Abram the land
\rem /s1 Abram Moves to Hebron
\p
\v 14 After LotВҰ5313 had left, Yahweh told AbramВҰ5309, вҖңLook all around youВҰ5324 towards the northВҰ5326, the southВҰ5327, the east, andВҰ5305 the west,
\v 15 because all that land that you can see, I'llВҰ5332 giveВҰ5342 itВҰ5342 to you and to your descendants to have forever.\x + \xo 13:15: \xt Acts 7:5.\x*
\v 16 I'll make your descendants \add as numerous\add* as dust \add particles\add*. Your descendants will only be able to be countedВҰ5360 if someone's able to count all the dust \add particles\add* on the earth.
\v 17 \add So,\add* go and \add start\add* walking throughout the landвҖ”through its lengthВҰ5373 and its width, because I'm giving itВҰ5377 \add all\add* to you.вҖқ
\v 18 \add SoВҰ5379\add* AbramВҰ5380 movedВҰ5379 his tents and wentВҰ5381 and settled by the terebinth trees atВҰ5383 MamreВҰ5384 (near HebronВҰ5386), and he builtВҰ5387 an altarВҰ5390 to YahwehВҰ5391 thereВҰ5389.
\c 14
\s1 Five kings defend against four attackers
\rem /s1 Lot's Captivity and Rescue; Abram Rescues Lot
\p
\v 1 At the time when AmrafelВҰ5396 was king of ShinarВҰ5399, AriochВҰ5400 was king of EllasarВҰ5402, KedorlaomerВҰ5403 was king of ElamВҰ5405, and TidalВҰ5406 was king of the GoyimВҰ5408,
\v 2 they went to war against Bera king of SodomВҰ5416, BirshaВҰ5419 king of Amorah \add (GomorrahВҰ5421)\add*, ShinabВҰ5422 king of AdmahВҰ5425, ShemeberВҰ5426 king of TsevoimВҰ5428, and the king of BelaВҰ5432 (also known as Tso'ar).
\v 3 Those latter five kings joinedВҰ5440 forces in the SiddimВҰ5444 valley (also known as the Salt Sea valley).
\v 4 They had been subject to King KedorlaomerВҰ5455 for twelve years, butВҰ5456 in the thirteenth yearВҰ5459 they rebelledВҰ5460.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ5462 in the fourteenth yearВҰ5464, KedorlaomerВҰ5466 and the kingsВҰ5467 who were withВҰ5462 him wentВҰ5465 and attacked the RefaimВҰ5473 in AshterothВҰ5474-Karnaim, and the ZuzimВҰ5478 in HamВҰ5479, and the EmimВҰ5481 in Shaveh-KiriathaimВҰ5483,
\v 6 andВҰ5485 the HoritesВҰ5487 inВҰ5488 the hill countryВҰ5488 of Se'irВҰ5489 as far as ElВҰ5491 ParanВҰ5492, whichВҰ5493 is near the wildernessВҰ5496.
\v 7 ThenВҰ5498 \add those four kings\add* turnedВҰ5498 back and wentВҰ5499 to En MishpatВҰ5503 (also called KadeshВҰ5505) and theyВҰ5499 attacked the entireВҰ5509 territories of the AmalekitesВҰ5512 and also the AmoritesВҰ5516, who were living inВҰ5518 Hazezon Tamar.
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ5521 the king of SodomВҰ5524, the king of Amorah \add (GomorrahВҰ5526)\add*, the king of AdmahВҰ5528, the king of TsevoimВҰ5530, and the king of BelaВҰ5533 (also called ZoarВҰ5536) went out into the SiddimВҰ5541 Valley and arranged \add their troops\add* for battleВҰ5539
\v 9 against KedorlaomerВҰ5544 king of ElamВҰ5546, TidalВҰ5547 king of GoiimВҰ5549, AmrafelВҰ5550 king of ShinarВҰ5552, AriochВҰ5553 king of EllasarВҰ5555вҖ”five kingsВҰ5557 \add defending themselves\add* against the four.
\v 10 Now the SiddimВҰ5563 Valley had many tar pits, and when the kings of SodomВҰ5571 and AmorahВҰ5572 \add (Gomorrah)\add* fled, theyВҰ5578 fell into the pits, \add butВҰ5562\add* the rest fled up into the hills.
\v 11 ThenВҰ5580 \add the four attacking kings\add* tookВҰ5580 all the \add peoples'\add* possessionsВҰ5585 from SodomВҰ5586 and AmorahВҰ5587 \add (Gomorrah)\add* and all theirВҰ5592 food and left.
\s1 Abram rescues Lot
\p
\v 12 Abram'sВҰ5605 nephew LotВҰ5598 andВҰ5595 all his possessionsВҰ5601 also got taken because he was livingВҰ5608 inВҰ5609 \add the city of\add* SodomВҰ5609,
\v 13 \add butВҰ5611\add* someone who escapedВҰ5612 came and reported \add this news\add* to Abram the HebrewВҰ5615. \add At that time,\add* Abram was \add still\add* livingВҰ5617 by the terebinth trees of MamreВҰ5619 the AmoriteВҰ5620, the brother of EshcolВҰ5622 and the brother of AnerВҰ5624, and the three of them had formed an alliance \add together\add*.
\v 14 WhenВҰ5637 AbramВҰ5632 heard that his nephew had been takenВҰ5634 captiveВҰ5634, he led out his 318 trainedВҰ5639 menВҰ5639 who'd \add all\add* been born in his houseВҰ5641, andВҰ5631 he pursuedВҰ5646 his enemies as far as \add the town of\add* DanВҰ5649.
\v 15 During the nightВҰ5654, Abram split in his slaves into groups and they attacked \add the four kings and their soldiers\add* and pursuedВҰ5658 them to HobahВҰ5661 (northВҰ5663 of DamascusВҰ5664).
\v 16 They were able to bring back all the possessions, as well as his nephew LotВҰ5674 and his possessions, and also the womenВҰ5681 and the \add other\add* peopleВҰ5684 \add who'd been captured\add*.
\s1 Malki-Tsedek blesses Abram
\rem /s1 Melchizedek Blesses Abram; Abram Blessed by Melchizedek
\p
\v 17 After \add Abram\add* returnedВҰ5692 from \add defeatingВҰ5693\add* KedorlaomerВҰ5696 andВҰ5699 his allied kingsВҰ5701, the king of SodomВҰ5689 wentВҰ5686 out to meet \add Abram\add* in ShavehВҰ5707 valley (also called the king'sВҰ5710 valley) .
\rem /s1 Melchizedek blesses Abram
\v 18 ThenВҰ5712 Malki-Tsedek \add (MelchizedekВҰ5712)\add* the kingВҰ5715 of SalemВҰ5716 broughtВҰ5717 out breadВҰ5718 andВҰ5712 wineвҖ”he was a priestВҰ5721 to the most high GodВҰ5722.\x + \xo 14:18-20: \xt Heb 7:1-10.\x*
\v 19 \add @Malki-Tsedek\add* blessed \add AbramВҰ5728\add*, saying:
\q1 вҖңMay Abram be blessed by the most high GodВҰ5729,
\q1 the owner of heavenВҰ5732 andВҰ5725 earthВҰ5733.
\q1
\v 20 Praise the most high GodВҰ5736,
\q1 who enabled you to defeat your enemiesВҰ5741.вҖқ
\m ThenВҰ5735 \add Abram\add* gaveВҰ5743 to \add Malki-Tsedek\add* a tenthВҰ5746 of everything \add heВҰ5740 had recovered\add*.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ5749 the kingВҰ5750 of SodomВҰ5752 saidВҰ5749 to AbramВҰ5755, вҖңGive my people back to me, butВҰ5749 keep the possessions for yourself.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \add ButВҰ5765\add* AbramВҰ5766 saidВҰ5765 to the kingВҰ5769 of SodomВҰ5770, вҖңI promise by YahwehВҰ5775, most high GodВҰ5776, the owner of heavenВҰ5779 andВҰ5765 earthВҰ5780,
\v 23 that I won't takeВҰ5791 anything of yours, not even the strap of a sandalВҰ5788, so that you won't \add be able to\add* sayВҰ5798 that it was you who made me wealthyВҰ5800.
\v 24 I'll \add take\add* nothing, except what the youngВҰ5809 \add fighters\add* have eatenВҰ5808, and the share of the other men who went with me: AnerВҰ5815, EshcolВҰ5816, and MamreВҰ5817. Let them take theirВҰ5820 share.вҖқ
\c 15
\s1 God agreement with Abram
\rem /s1 The Lord's Covenant with Abram; God's Covenant With Abram; God's Covenant with Abram; The Lord's covenant with Abram
\p
\v 1 After those events, YahwehВҰ5830 spoke to Abram inВҰ5834 a visionВҰ5834, telling him, вҖңDon't be afraid, Abram, because I'll protect you and I'll generously and richly rewardВҰ5843 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖңMyВҰ5856 masterВҰ5849 YahwehВҰ5850,вҖқ replied AbramВҰ5848, вҖңwhat will youВҰ5853 giveВҰ5853 me, since we have no childrenВҰ5858 andВҰ5847 it's EliezerВҰ5865 (\add my chief slave\add* from DamascusВҰ5864) who'll inherit all my possessions?вҖқ
\v 3 ThenВҰ5867 he continuedВҰ5867, вҖң\add YesВҰ5868,\add* youВҰ5872 haven't givenВҰ5872 me a child so wow, my heir is a slave from my householdВҰ5877!вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ5881 listen, Yahweh'sВҰ5884 wordВҰ5882 came to \add Abram\add* saying, вҖңThat man won'tВҰ5887 be your heir, butВҰ5881 on the contrary, it'll be your biological son.вҖқ
\v 5 Then \add Yahweh\add* took \add Abram\add* outsideВҰ5901 and said, вҖңLook up at the sky and see if you can count the starsВҰ5908.вҖқ Then he said to him, вҖңYour descendants will be like that.вҖқ\x + \xo 15:5: \xt Rom 4:18; Heb 11:12.\x*
\p
\v 6 \add Abram\add* believedВҰ5920 inВҰ5921 Yahweh, andВҰ5922 \add Yahweh consideredВҰ5922 that faith of Abram's as an act of obedience\add*.\x + \xo 15:6: \xt Rom 4:3; Gal 3:6; Jam 2:23.\x*
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ5926 Yahweh told \add Abram\add*, вҖңI'm Yahweh who broughtВҰ5931 you out of UrВҰ5932 (where the Chaldeans lived) so I could giveВҰ5934 you this land to possessВҰ5940 it.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңMy masterВҰ5943 YahwehВҰ5944,вҖқ Abram asked, вҖңhow will I knowВҰ5946 that I will possessВҰ5948 itВҰ5948?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңBring me a three-year-old heiferВҰ5954,вҖқ Yahweh replied, вҖңand a three-year-old she-goat and a three-year-old ram and a turtledoveВҰ5960 and a youngВҰ5961 pigeonВҰ5961.вҖқ
\v 10 SoВҰ5963 \add Abram\add* brought all those to \add Yahweh\add*, and thenВҰ5963 heВҰ5985 cut the animals (butВҰ5963 not the birdsВҰ5982) inВҰ5973 half down the middle and laid the halves oppositeВҰ5978 to each other.
\v 11 ThenВҰ5993 \add some\add* birdsВҰ5988 of prey flew down to the carcassesВҰ5991, \add butВҰ5987\add* AbramВҰ5994 shooed them away.
\p
\v 12 Later as the sunВҰ5997 was goingВҰ5998 down, AbramВҰ6003 fell into a deep sleepВҰ5999, and it suddenly became completely dark and he became terrified,\x + \xo 15:12: \xt Yob 4:13-14.\x*
\v 13 and \add Yahweh\add* saidВҰ6011 to AbramВҰ6012, вҖңKnow for certainВҰ6013 that your descendants will be strangers in a land that doesn't belong to them, and they'll serve the \add rulers of that land\add* and \add those rulers\add* will persecute them for 400 years.\x + \xo 15:13: \xt Exo 1:1-14; Acts 7:6.\x*
\v 14 \add ButВҰ6031 just as certain\add*, I'llВҰ6038 punish the nationВҰ6034 that they serveВҰ6036 andВҰ6031 afterВҰ6039 that they'll comeВҰ6042 out withВҰ6043 many possessionsВҰ6043.\x + \xo 15:14: \xt Exo 12:40-41; Acts 7:7.\x*
\v 15 And \add as for\add* you, you'll goВҰ6047 to your ancestorsВҰ6050 inВҰ6051 peaceВҰ6051вҖ”you'll be buriedВҰ6052 atВҰ6051 a goodВҰ6054 old age.
\v 16 ThenВҰ6056 in the fourthВҰ6057 generationВҰ6056 \add your descendants\add* will come back here, because the Amorites' sins won'tВҰ6061 be completeВҰ6063 untilВҰ6066 thenВҰ6056.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ6070 the sun went down and darkness came, and wow, there was a smoking fire pot and a flaming torchВҰ6078 thatВҰ6080 passedВҰ6081 betweenВҰ6082 those \add animal halves\add*.
\v 18 On that dayВҰ6086 YahwehВҰ6089 made an agreement with AbramВҰ6092, saying, вҖңI've given this land to your descendantsВҰ6095, from Egypt'sВҰ6102 river to the famous EuphratesВҰ6109 River.\x + \xo 15:18: \xt Acts 7:5.\x*
\v 19 \add That includes the land of \add* the KenitesВҰ6113, the KenizzitesВҰ6116, the KadmonitesВҰ6118,
\v 20 the HittitesВҰ6122, the PerizzitesВҰ6125, the RefaimВҰ6128,
\v 21 the AmoritesВҰ6132, the CanaanitesВҰ6135, the GirgashitesВҰ6138, andВҰ6130 the YebusitesВҰ6141.вҖқ
\c 16
\s1 Hagar and her son Yishma'el
\rem /s1 The Birth of Ishmael; Hagar and Ishmael
\p
\v 1 Now Abram'sВҰ6146 wifeВҰ6145 SaraiВҰ6144 hadn't been able to give him any childrenВҰ6148, butВҰ6144 she had an Egyptian slave named HagarВҰ6154,
\v 2 so Sarai saidВҰ6156 to Abram, вҖңListen, YahwehВҰ6165 has preventedВҰ6164 me from having childrenВҰ6166 so pleaseВҰ6163 sleep with my slaveВҰ6172. Perhaps I can have a family through her.вҖқ Abram agreed to what Sarai had suggested.
\v 3 SoВҰ6182 SaraiВҰ6183, the wife of Abram, took HagarВҰ6189, her Egyptian slaveВҰ6191, after Abram had livedВҰ6195 ten yearsВҰ6194 in the land of CanaanВҰ6198, andВҰ6182 gave her to Abram her husbandВҰ6202 as a wife for him.
\v 4 SoВҰ6206 he slept withВҰ6216 HagarВҰ6209 andВҰ6206 she got pregnantВҰ6210, butВҰ6206 once she realisedВҰ6211 that she began to despise herВҰ6215 mistressВҰ6215.
\p
\v 5 SoВҰ6218 SaraiВҰ6219 \add complained\add* to AbramВҰ6222, вҖңThis is all your fault. I let you sleep withВҰ6228 myВҰ6223 slaveВҰ6227, butВҰ6218 now that she's pregnant she looks down onВҰ6228 me. May YahwehВҰ6235 judgeВҰ6234 betweenВҰ6236 me andВҰ6218 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңListen,вҖқ AbramВҰ6241 replied, вҖңShe's \em yourВҰ6252\em* slaveВҰ6246 to do what she's told. Do whatever youВҰ6252 think best.вҖқ So Sarai started mistreatingВҰ6253 Hagar, and so she ran away.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ6258 Yahweh'sВҰ6260 messengerВҰ6259 foundВҰ6258 herВҰ6258 inВҰ6265 the wildernessВҰ6265 atВҰ6265 a springвҖ”the spring beside the road to ShurВҰ6270,
\v 8 and \add asked\add* her, вҖңHagarВҰ6273, Sarai's slave, where have you comeВҰ6279 from and where are you goingВҰ6281?вҖқ
\p вҖңI am running away from Sarai, my mistressВҰ6285,вҖқ she \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ6289 Yahweh'sВҰ6292 messengerВҰ6291 \add instructed\add* herВҰ6299, вҖңReturn to yourВҰ6296 mistressВҰ6296 andВҰ6297 do whatever she tells you,вҖқ
\v 10 thenВҰ6301 added, вҖңI'll give you so many descendants that they won'tВҰ6310 even be able to be countedВҰ6311 because there'll be so many.вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ6314 the messengerВҰ6316 told her,
\q1 вҖңListen here: you'reВҰ6318 pregnantВҰ6319 and will give birth to a son,
\q1 and you'll nameВҰ6323 him вҖҳYishma'elВҰ6324вҖҷ (\add which means вҖҳGod hearsвҖҷ)\add*
\q2 because YahwehВҰ6317 has heard yourВҰ6331 cries of misery.
\q1
\v 12 He'll be a wild donkeyВҰ6335 of a manВҰ6336
\q2 and he'll be hostile to everyone
\q2 and everyone will be against him.
\q1 He'll \add live\add* right inВҰ6338 front of his brothersВҰ6347.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ6350 \add Hagar realised that it was YahwehВҰ6353\add* who had spokenВҰ6360 to her \add andВҰ6350 saidВҰ6360\add*, вҖңYou're вҖҳThe God who sees meвҖҷ,вҖқ because sheВҰ6360 \add thought\add*, вҖңDid I reallyВҰ6361 just see the back of the \add God\add* who sees me?вҖқ
\v 14 So that's why that well between KadeshВҰ6378 andВҰ6379 BeredВҰ6380 is \add now\add* calledВҰ6370 вҖҳThe well of the living one who sees meвҖҷ.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ6382 HagarВҰ6383 gaveВҰ6382 birthВҰ6382 to a son for Abram, andВҰ6386 Abram named him Yishma'elВҰ6395.\x + \xo 16:15: \xt Gal 4:22.\x*
\v 16 AbramВҰ6410 was eighty-sixВҰ6400 yearsВҰ6403 old when HagarВҰ6406 bore Yishma'elВҰ6409 for him.
\c 17
\s1 Circumcision as a confirmation of the agreement
\rem /s1 The Sign of the Covenant; Abram Is Named Abraham; Circumcision, the Sign of the Covenant; The Covenant of Circumcision
\p
\v 1 \add Many years later\add* when AbramВҰ6414 was ninety-nine years old, YahwehВҰ6422 appearedВҰ6421 to him and said, вҖңI'm the all-powerful GodВҰ6430. Obey me and don't disobey
\v 2 and I'llВҰ6442 establish my agreement withВҰ6443 you and will cause you to have very many descendants.вҖқ
\v 3 ThenВҰ6446 AbramВҰ6447 \add knelt down with his face to the ground\add* andВҰ6451 GodВҰ6453 told him,
\v 4 вҖңListen, my agreement with you is that you'll become the fatherВҰ6461 of many nationsВҰ6463,
\v 5 so you'll no longer be calledВҰ6467 вҖҳAbramВҰ6472вҖҷ, butВҰ6465 \add now\add* your name will be вҖҳAbrahamВҰ6475вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳfather of many nationsвҖҷ)\add* because I'm making you the father of many nations.\x + \xo 17:5: \xt Rom 4:17.\x*
\v 6 I'llВҰ6484 make you \add and your descendants\add* very fruitfulВҰ6483 so that they form nationsВҰ6488 and some of them will become kingsВҰ6489.
\p
\v 7 I'll establishВҰ6493 my agreement with you and your future descendants for all the following generationsВҰ6502. It will be an agreement that never ends, that I'll be the your godВҰ6507 and GodВҰ6507 of your future descendants.\x + \xo 17:7: \xt Luk 1:55.\x*
\v 8 I'll giveВҰ6511 this land that you're staying inвҖ”the entireВҰ6520 regionВҰ6517 of CanaanВҰ6523вҖ”to you and yourВҰ6518 descendants as a permanent possessionВҰ6524, and I'll be their godВҰ6528.вҖқ\x + \xo 17:8: \xt Acts 7:5.\x*
\rem /s1 The Sign of Circumcision
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ6530 GodВҰ6531 told AbrahamВҰ6534, вҖң\add For your part,\add*, you andВҰ6530 your descendants afterВҰ6542 you throughoutВҰ6543 \add all\add* theirВҰ6543 generationsВҰ6543 must follow the requirements of our agreement.
\v 10 This is the agreement thatВҰ6547 you and all your future descendants are to follow: everyВҰ6556 maleВҰ6558 among you must be circumcisedВҰ6554.\x + \xo 17:10: \xt Acts 7:8; Rom 4:11.\x*
\v 11 ThisВҰ6561 removal of the foreskinВҰ6563 will be a \add physical mark confirming\add* the agreement betweenВҰ6567 me andВҰ6564 youВҰ6568.
\v 12 All maleВҰ6578 babies must be circumcisedВҰ6574 when they're eightВҰ6572 daysВҰ6573 old. This includes all those born in your own houseВҰ6581, as well as any that have been boughtВҰ6582 from foreignersВҰ6588 even if they're not your \add biological\add* descendants.
\v 13 \add Yes,\add* they definitely must be circumcised either way if they're born in your houseВҰ6598 or purchased \add as slaves\add*. This way, my agreement will be manifested in your physical bodies as a never-ending agreement.
\v 14 Any males who isn'tВҰ6611 circumcisedВҰ6613 must be excluded from his peopleВҰ6621 because he will have brokenВҰ6625 my agreement.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Sarai Is Named Sarah
\p
\v 15 GodВҰ6629 \add also\add* told AbrahamВҰ6632, вҖңAs for your wife Sarai, don'tВҰ6635 call her Sarai \add anymore\add*, because from now on her name will be вҖҳSarahВҰ6643вҖҷ
\v 16 and I will bless her, and I'll also giveВҰ6649 you a son from her. \add Yes,\add* I'll bless her and she'll become \add the mother of\add* nationsВҰ6655вҖ”kingsВҰ6656 of peoplesВҰ6657 will come from her.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 AbrahamВҰ6662 fell to his knees and he laughedВҰ6666 and saidВҰ6667 to himself, вҖңHow can a hundredВҰ6670 year old man father a childВҰ6681? And what about SarahВҰ6676 who's ninety-nineВҰ6679 years old having a baby!вҖқ
\v 18 ThenВҰ6683 AbrahamВҰ6684 saidВҰ6683 to GodВҰ6687, вҖңIf only \add you'd bless\add* Yishma'elВҰ6689 \add as my heir\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңNo,вҖқ GodВҰ6694 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңIt'll be your wifeВҰ6697 SarahВҰ6696 who gives you a son, and you'll nameВҰ6704 him вҖҳYitshakвҖҷ \add (or вҖҳIsaacВҰ6705вҖҷ, meaning вҖҳone who laughsвҖҷ)\add*. I'll establishВҰ6706 my agreement with him as a never-ending commitment to him and his descendants.
\v 20 \add ButВҰ6716\add* as for Yishma'elВҰ6716, I've heardВҰ6718 \add your request\add*. Listen, I'll blessВҰ6721 him and make him fruitfulВҰ6723 and giveВҰ6734 him very many descendants. He'll fatherВҰ6733 twelve rulers and I'll make him into a greatВҰ6736 nationВҰ6735,
\v 21 however, my agreement will be establishedВҰ6741 withВҰ6751 Yitshak, who SarahВҰ6748 will give birth to by this timeВҰ6749 next yearВҰ6751.вҖқ
\v 22 ThenВҰ6754 having finished speaking with AbrahamВҰ6760, GodВҰ6758 went up \add away\add* from him.
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ6762 AbrahamВҰ6763 tookВҰ6762 every maleВҰ6780 from his household and circumcisedВҰ6784 them that very dayВҰ6790, just as GodВҰ6795 had instructed him. ThatВҰ6783 included his son Yishma'elВҰ6766, all thoseВҰ6771 born inВҰ6781 his houseВҰ6772, and everyone bought withВҰ6781 his moneyВҰ6777.
\v 24 Abraham was ninety-nineВҰ6800 years old when he was circumcisedВҰ6803
\v 25 andВҰ6807 his son Yishma'elВҰ6807 was thirteen years old when \add AbrahamВҰ6815\add* circumcisedВҰ6814 him.
\v 26 \add So it was,\add* on that same dayВҰ6820, \add both\add* AbrahamВҰ6823 andВҰ6824 his son Yishma'elВҰ6824 were circumcisedВҰ6822
\v 27 andВҰ6833 all the \add other\add* males in his householdВҰ6830, whether born there or boughtВҰ6833 from foreignersВҰ6839, were circumcisedВҰ6840 with him.
\c 18
\s1 Abraham and Sarah are promised a son
\rem /s1 A Son Is Promised to Abraham; The Three Visitors; A Son Promised to Sarah; A Son Promised to Abraham and Sarah
\p
\v 1 Then \add one day\add* YahwehВҰ6846 appearedВҰ6844 \add again\add* to Abraham at the oak trees onВҰ6847 Mamre'sВҰ6848 \add land\add*, while \add Abraham\add* was sittingВҰ6850 at the entrance of his tent during the hottest part of the day.
\v 2 \add Abraham\add* looked up and \add was surprised\add* to see threeВҰ6861 menВҰ6862 standingВҰ6863 \add a short distance away\add*. He ranВҰ6866 from the tent opening to meet them and bowedВҰ6870 \add respectfully\add*,\x + \xo 18:2a: \xt Heb 13:2.\x*
\v 3 andВҰ6873 saidВҰ6873, вҖңMy mastersВҰ6874, if I've foundВҰ6878 favourВҰ6879 inВҰ6880 your eyesВҰ6880, pleaseВҰ6877 don'tВҰ6881 \add just carry onВҰ6880\add* past your slaveВҰ6886.
\v 4 Let me get some waterВҰ6893 so that you can wash yourВҰ6895 feetВҰ6895 and rest \add here\add* underВҰ6897 this treeВҰ6898.
\v 5 I'll go andВҰ6900 get some food so that you can refreshВҰ6904 yourselvesВҰ6905 before you leave, since you've come to your slaveВҰ6916.вҖқ
\p вҖңAlright, do as you have said,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ6923 AbrahamВҰ6924 hurriedВҰ6923 into the tent and told SarahВҰ6928, вҖңQuickly, \add grind\add* threeВҰ6931 measures of fine flour and kneadВҰ6935 it and make some breadВҰ6937.вҖқ
\v 7 HeВҰ6956 ranВҰ6942 to the herd and selected a tenderВҰ6948 and choiceВҰ6949 calf and tookВҰ6944 it to a slaveВҰ6953 who hurriedВҰ6954 to prepare it.
\v 8 ThenВҰ6958 he tookВҰ6958 yogurt and milk and the calf thatВҰ6964 had been preparedВҰ6965, and he set \add the meal\add* down in front of the \add visitors\add*, standingВҰ6970 \add there\add* underВҰ6972 the treeВҰ6973 by them while they ateВҰ6974.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ6976 theyВҰ6976 \add asked\add* himВҰ6977, вҖңWhere's your wife SarahВҰ6980?вҖқ
\p вҖңSee, over thereВҰ6983 inВҰ6984 the tent,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 10 вҖңI'll definitely return to youВҰ6989 here \add in the spring next year\add*,вҖқ the visitor continuedВҰ6986. вҖңYou see, your wife SarahВҰ6995 will have a son \add thenВҰ6986\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 18:10: \xt Rom 9:9.\x*
\p Now Sarah was at the openingВҰ6999 of the tent listeningВҰ6998, butВҰ6986 the visitor was facing the other direction.
\v 11 Abraham and Sarah were pretty old \add at this stage\add* and Sarah had passed the age of being able to have children,
\v 12 so \add when she heard that\add*, she laughedВҰ7015 to herself andВҰ7025 said, вҖңNow that \add my body's\add* worn out, will I have the pleasureВҰ7024 \add of a child\add*? \add Even\add* my master'sВҰ7025 \add too\add* old.вҖқ\x + \xo 18:12: \xt 1Pe 3:6.\x*
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ7028 YahwehВҰ7029 spoke to AbrahamВҰ7032, вҖңWhy is it that SarahВҰ7036 laughedВҰ7035, saying, вҖҳWill I reallyВҰ7039 have a childВҰ7040 when I'm old?вҖҷ
\v 14 Is anythingВҰ7046 too hard for Yahweh? I'll returnВҰ7048 \add here\add* to youВҰ7049 \add next year in the spring\add* andВҰ7052 SarahВҰ7052 will have a son.вҖқ\x + \xo 18:14: \xt Luk 1:37.\x*
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ7055 SarahВҰ7056 was afraidВҰ7063 andВҰ7064 deniedВҰ7055 it by saying, вҖңI didn'tВҰ7059 laugh.вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, because youВҰ7068 did laugh,вҖқ he saidВҰ7064.
\s1 Abraham bargains with Yahweh about Sodom
\rem /s1 Abraham Intercedes for Sodom; Judgment Pronounced on Sodom; Abraham Pleads for Sodom
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ7070 the \add three\add* menВҰ7072 got up \add to leave\add* and lookedВҰ7073 down toward SodomВҰ7077, and AbrahamВҰ7078 went with them to \add see\add* them off.
\v 17 ThenВҰ7083 Yahweh saidВҰ7084 \add to himself\add*, вҖңShould I hide what I'm aboutВҰ7090 to do from AbrahamВҰ7087?
\v 18 \add His descendants\add* are certainly going to become a greatВҰ7096 and mightyВҰ7097 nationВҰ7095, and all the nationsВҰ7101 of the earthВҰ7102 will be blessedВҰ7098 through him \add and them\add*,
\v 19 because I'm aware that he'll commandВҰ7108 his childrenВҰ7111 and his householdВҰ7114 afterВҰ7115 him, and they'll follow Yahweh's pathВҰ7117 by their rightВҰ7120 and just behaviour, so that Yahweh will bringВҰ7123 about for AbrahamВҰ7127 what he's said to him.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ7134 YahwehВҰ7135 saidВҰ7134, вҖңBecause there's \add so many people\add* crying out about SodomВҰ7137 and AmorahВҰ7138 \add (Gomorrah)\add*, and because theirВҰ7142 sinВҰ7142 is very grievous,
\v 21 I'll goВҰ7147 down \add there\add* now and seeВҰ7150 if what I've heard about them is true, and if not, I'll also find that out.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ7162 the \add other two\add* menВҰ7164 left and started descending towardВҰ7166 SodomВҰ7166, and AbrahamВҰ7167 was still standingВҰ7169 thereВҰ7163 in frontВҰ7170 of YahwehВҰ7171,
\v 23 so he wentВҰ7173 closer \add to Yahweh\add* andВҰ7175 asked, вҖңWill youВҰ7177 really destroy obedient people along with those who are evil?
\v 24 What if thereВҰ7184 were fifty people inВҰ7199 the city \add who've obeyed you\add*? Would you reallyВҰ7189 destroy the city and all itsВҰ7199 people and not save it for the sake of those fifty?
\v 25 Surely you wouldn't do anything like thatвҖ”killing the good people along with the evil ones, so that they all just get treated the same? Certainly you wouldn't do that? Wouldn't the one who judgesВҰ7217 the entireВҰ7218 world be more fair?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңIf I find fiftyВҰ7231 godlyВҰ7232 people inВҰ7230 SodomВҰ7230,вҖқ YahwehВҰ7226 answered, вҖңthenВҰ7225 I'll spareВҰ7235 the whole cityВҰ7234 for theirВҰ7239 sake.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖңListen, I've been bold enough to \add question\add* my masterВҰ7251, even though I'm \add just\add* dust andВҰ7241 ashesВҰ7254,вҖқ AbrahamВҰ7242 saidВҰ7243 again.
\v 28 вҖңSuppose they're five short of the fiftyВҰ7258? Would you destroy the whole cityВҰ7267 because of five?вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ7269 destroy it if I find forty-fiveВҰ7275 thereВҰ7274,вҖқ he replied.
\p
\v 29 Abraham continuedВҰ7282 to make his request, вҖңSuppose there's forty there?вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ7288 do it for the sake of the forty,вҖқ he agreed.
\p
\v 30 My masterВҰ7298, don'tВҰ7294 get angry butВҰ7293 let me speakВҰ7299,вҖқ Abraham said, вҖңsuppose thirty are foundВҰ7301 there?вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ7294 do it if I find thirty there,вҖқ he said.
\p
\v 31 вҖңListen, I've taken it upon myself to speakВҰ7318 to my masterВҰ7321,вҖқ Abraham asked again, вҖңsuppose twenty are foundВҰ7323 thereВҰ7324?вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ7327 do it for the sake of the twenty,вҖқ he agreed.
\p
\v 32 вҖңMy masterВҰ7337, don'tВҰ7333 get angry andВҰ7332 let me speakВҰ7338 one last timeВҰ7341,вҖқ Abraham added, вҖңsuppose ten are foundВҰ7343 thereВҰ7344?вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ7333 do it for the sake of the ten,вҖқ YahwehВҰ7337 conceded
\v 33 and thenВҰ7352 he left and AbrahamВҰ7353 returnedВҰ7361 home.
\c 19
\s1 Sexual depravity in Sodom
\rem /s1 Sodom and Gomorrah; The Depravity of Sodom; The Sinfulness of Sodom
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ7364 the twoВҰ7365 messengersВҰ7366 arrived at SodomВҰ7373 in the eveningВҰ7368, and Lot was sittingВҰ7370 at the city gate. WhenВҰ7364 Lot sawВҰ7374 them, he got up to meet them and knelt down in front of them withВҰ7368 his faceВҰ7380 to the groundВҰ7381.
\v 2 Then he said, вҖңListen, my mastersВҰ7387: Come withВҰ7404 me to your slave'sВҰ7393 home and wash your feetВҰ7396 and stay the night. Then you can get up earlyВҰ7397 and continue onВҰ7404 your wayВҰ7400.вҖқ
\p ButВҰ7383 they said, вҖңNo, rather we'll \add just\add* spendВҰ7394 the night inВҰ7404 the street.вҖқ
\v 3 However, Lot insisted, so they followed him \add off the main road\add* and wentВҰ7413 into his houseВҰ7416. ThenВҰ7407 heВҰ7421 prepared a feastВҰ7419 for them and bakedВҰ7421 unleavenedВҰ7420 breadВҰ7420, and they ateВҰ7422.
\p
\v 4 \add However,\add* before they \add went to bed\add*, the men of SodomВҰ7429 surroundedВҰ7430 the houseВҰ7433вҖ”there were youngВҰ7434 and old from all parts of the cityВҰ7427вҖ”
\v 5 andВҰ7443 they calledВҰ7443 out to LotВҰ7446, вҖңWhere are the menВҰ7450 who cameВҰ7453 to your place tonight? Bring them out to us so that we can вҖҳuseвҖҷ them.вҖқ\x + \xo 19:5-8: \xt Jdg 19:22-24.\x*
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ7461 LotВҰ7463 wentВҰ7461 out to them at the entranceВҰ7464 \add of the house\add* andВҰ7465 shut the doorВҰ7465 behindВҰ7467 himВҰ7467
\v 7 andВҰ7469 saidВҰ7469, вҖңMy brothersВҰ7473, don'tВҰ7470 do this evilВҰ7474.
\v 8 Listen, I've got twoВҰ7480 virgin daughtersВҰ7481. Please let me bringВҰ7487 them out to you and you can treat them however you like. ButВҰ7492 don'tВҰ7483 do anythingВҰ7502 to theseВҰ7498 menВҰ7497, because they've entered my house \add and so I'm responsible for them\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ButВҰ7512 they insisted, вҖңStand back!вҖқ Then they said \add to each other\add*, вҖңThis guy came to stay withВҰ7529 us, and now he's judging us. We'll treat you worse than them!вҖқ Then they started pushing hard against LotВҰ7530 and came closer to breakВҰ7533 down the doorВҰ7534.
\v 10 ButВҰ7536 the \add two visitors\add* reachedВҰ7536 out theirВҰ7540 handsВҰ7540 and pulled LotВҰ7544 into the houseВҰ7546 and shut the doorВҰ7549 \add again\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ7552 they struckВҰ7559 the men who were atВҰ7560 the entranceВҰ7557 of the houseВҰ7558 withВҰ7560 blindnessВҰ7560вҖ”\add all of them\add* from the lowly to the prominent menвҖ”so that they gave up trying to find the doorВҰ7567.\x + \xo 19:11: \xt 2Ki 6:18.\x*
\s1 Lot and family leave Sodom
\rem /s1 Lot Leaves Sodom; Sodom and Gomorrah Destroyed
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ7569 the menВҰ7570 saidВҰ7569 to LotВҰ7573, вҖңWho else belongs to you here, a son-in-lawВҰ7579 or your sonsВҰ7580 or your daughtersВҰ7581 or anyone else who belongs to you in the cityВҰ7586? Take them out from this placeВҰ7590,
\v 13 because we're \add aboutВҰ7594 to\add* destroy it. \add TheВҰ7609 people have repeatedly cried out to\add* YahwehВҰ7607, so he's sentВҰ7608 us to destroy the city.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ7612 LotВҰ7613 wentВҰ7612 out and spokeВҰ7614 to his \add future\add* sons-in-law who were \add engaged\add* to his daughtersВҰ7621, and he told them, вҖң\add HurryВҰ7633\add*, get out of this placeВҰ7627, because YahwehВҰ7632 is going to destroyВҰ7631 the cityВҰ7635!вҖқ ButВҰ7612 they thought he was just joking.
\p
\v 15 At dawn the next day, the \add two\add* messengersВҰ7645 urgedВҰ7644 LotВҰ7646, saying, вҖңGet up, takeВҰ7649 your wifeВҰ7652 andВҰ7641 your two daughtersВҰ7656 who are here, so that all of you won't be sweptВҰ7660 away inВҰ7646 the punishmentВҰ7661 of the cityВҰ7662.вҖқ
\v 16 WhenВҰ7664 Lot hesitatedВҰ7664, because of Yahweh'sВҰ7676 mercy for him, the men grabbed his hand and his wife's hand and the handsВҰ7672 of their daughtersВҰ7674, and led them out beyond the edge of the cityВҰ7681.\x + \xo 19:16: \xt 2Pe 2:7.\x*
\v 17 At that point \add one of them\add* told Lot, вҖңFlee for your lives! Don't \add turn around and\add* lookВҰ7694 behind you and don't stop anywhere \add down\add* in the plainВҰ7701. Escape \add up to\add* the hills so you don't get sweptВҰ7706 away!вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add ButВҰ7708\add* LotВҰ7709 \add argued\add*, вҖңNot right now, my mastersВҰ7714.
\v 19 Listen, you've been kind to me and show us mercy by savingВҰ7728 my lifeВҰ7731, butВҰ7723 I won'tВҰ7733 be able to make it to the hills because the disasterВҰ7740 will overtakeВҰ7739 me and I'll dieВҰ7741.
\v 20 Listen, there's a small townВҰ7746 nearby that I could flee to. Let me escapeВҰ7753 there. It's only small. Then my lifeВҰ7760 would be savedВҰ7759.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖңOkay thenВҰ7762,вҖқ the man replied, вҖңI'll also grant yourВҰ7766 request about this so I won'tВҰ7770 overthrowВҰ7771 the townВҰ7774 thatВҰ7775 you're talking about.
\v 22 HurryВҰ7778 up, escapeВҰ7779 there, because I am not able to do a thing untilВҰ7786 youВҰ7788 go there.вҖқ
\p That's why they \add renamed\add* the townВҰ7796 to вҖҳZoarВҰ7797вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳsmallвҖҷ)\add*.
\s1 The destruction of Sodom and Amorah (Gomorrah)
\rem /s1 The Destruction of Sodom and Gomorrah
\p
\v 23 The sunВҰ7799 had already risen by the time LotВҰ7804 \add and family\add* reached ZoarВҰ7806.
\v 24 ThenВҰ7808 YahwehВҰ7819 rained burning sulfurВҰ7816 down onto SodomВҰ7812 andВҰ7808 Amorah \add (GomorrahВҰ7815)\add*,\x + \xo 19:24-25: \xt Mat 10:15; 11:23-24; Luk 10:12; 17:29; 2Pe 2:6; Yud 7.\x*
\v 25 and he destroyed thoseВҰ7828 cities and all their inhabitantsВҰ7836 as well, as all of the plainВҰ7832 including all the vegetation.
\v 26 \add ButВҰ7841\add* Lot's wife who was following himВҰ7843 lookedВҰ7841 back andВҰ7844 she turned into a pillarВҰ7845 of salt.\x + \xo 19:26: \xt Luk 17:32.\x*
\p
\v 27 \add Meanwhile,\add* AbrahamВҰ7849 got up earlyВҰ7848 inВҰ7850 the morningВҰ7850 andВҰ7848 went to the placeВҰ7853 whereВҰ7854 he had stoodВҰ7856 before YahwehВҰ7861,
\v 28 and he lookedВҰ7863 down towardsВҰ7869 SodomВҰ7867 and AmorahВҰ7868 \add (Gomorrah)\add* and the land of the plainВҰ7875. From there he sawВҰ7876, wow, that smokeВҰ7879 was rising from the land like a furnaceВҰ7882 \add chimney\add*.
\v 29 SoВҰ7884 it was that when GodВҰ7886 destroyed the cities of the plainВҰ7890, he rememberedВҰ7891 AbrahamВҰ7895 andВҰ7884 had Lot removed out of the middle of the destruction when he destroyed the cities that Lot had been living inВҰ7885.
\s1 The sad origin of Moabites and Ammonites
\rem /s1 The Shameful Origin of Moab and Ammon; The Origin of the Moabites and Ammonites; Lot and His Daughters
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ7912 LotВҰ7913 and his two daughters left Zoar and settled up in the hills, because he was afraidВҰ7921 to stay in Zoar. SoВҰ7912 he lived in a cave \add up there\add* withВҰ7916 his two daughters.
\v 31 ThenВҰ7930 the older girl saidВҰ7930 to the youngerВҰ7934, вҖңDad's old andВҰ7930 thereВҰ7938 isn'tВҰ7938 a \add single\add* manВҰ7937 \add up here\add* to \add marry\add* us like happens to \add other women\add* in the world.
\v 32 So let's get Dad drunk and then we can lie with him, so that at least we can have some descendants throughВҰ7956 our fatherВҰ7951.вҖқ
\v 33 SoВҰ7960 thenВҰ7959, they got theirВҰ7962 father to drinkВҰ7959 wine that evening, and the oldest daughter went and lay withВҰ7964 her father, butВҰ7959 he wasn't aware of her coming or going.
\p
\v 34 Then the next dayВҰ7980, the older girl saidВҰ7981 to the youngerВҰ7985, Listen, last nightВҰ7997 I lay with my father. Let's get him drunk again tonight then you go lie with him so that we'll give life to descendants throughВҰ8002 our father.вҖқ
\v 35 SoВҰ8009 that next evening also, they got theirВҰ8011 fatherВҰ8011 to drinkВҰ8005 wine and the youngerВҰ8014 girl went and lay withВҰ8007 him, butВҰ8005 \add again\add* he wasn't aware of her coming or going.
\v 36 In that way, both of Lot'sВҰ8027 daughtersВҰ8025 got themselves pregnantВҰ8023 through theirВҰ8028 fatherВҰ8028.
\v 37 ThenВҰ8030 the eldest daughter gaveВҰ8030 birthВҰ8030 to a son andВҰ8033 she named him MoabВҰ8035 \add (which means вҖҳfrom my fatherвҖҷ)\add*. (He's the ancestorВҰ8037 of the Moabites to this dayВҰ8042.)
\v 38 The youngerВҰ8044 daughter also gave birth to a son andВҰ8044 she named him Ben-Ammi \add (which means вҖҳson of my peopleВҰ8057вҖҷ)\add*. (He's the ancestorВҰ8056 of AmmonitesВҰ8059 to this dayВҰ8062.)
\c 20
\s1 Abraham and Abimelech and Sarah
\rem /s1 Abraham Deceives Abimelech; Abraham and Abimelech; Abraham and Sarah at Gerar
\p
\v 1 Then AbrahamВҰ8067 travelled from thereВҰ8066 to the NegevВҰ8069 regionВҰ8068 and he settled between KadeshВҰ8073 and ShurВҰ8075, staying inВҰ8077 GerarВҰ8077 for a while.
\v 2 AbrahamВҰ8080 had told \add people\add* his wife Sarah was his sisterВҰ8085, so AbimelechВҰ8088 the kingВҰ8089 of GerarВҰ8090 sentВҰ8087 for Sarah andВҰ8091 tookВҰ8091 her.\x + \xo 20:2: \xt Gen 12:13; 26:7.\x*
\v 3 \add ButВҰ8096\add* GodВҰ8097 cameВҰ8096 to AbimelechВҰ8100 in a dreamВҰ8101 in the nightВҰ8102 andВҰ8096 told him, вҖңListen, you'reВҰ8105 \add as good as\add* dead because of that womanВҰ8109 you took because sheВҰ8113 is marriedВҰ8114 to a husbandВҰ8115.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Now AbimelechВҰ8117 hadn't gone near to her, so heВҰ8119 saidВҰ8121, вҖңMy masterВҰ8122, would youВҰ8127 destroy a nationВҰ8123 even though it's innocent?
\v 5 Didn't Abraham himself tell me that she was his sisterВҰ8134? And she herself also saidВҰ8141 that he was her brotherВҰ8142. I did this with a \add clear conscience\add* and with \add clean\add* handsВҰ8148.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ8152 GodВҰ8154 saidВҰ8152 to him inВҰ8155 the dreamВҰ8155, вҖңYes, I knowВҰ8158 that you did this withВҰ8155 a \add clear conscience\add* andВҰ8152 indeed I keptВҰ8165 you from sinningВҰ8170 against me. I didn'tВҰ8176 allow you to touchВҰ8179 herВҰ8180 for that reason.
\v 7 SoВҰ8182 now, return that man's wifeВҰ8184 because he's a prophetВҰ8189, and he'll pray for you and you'll live. ButВҰ8182 if you don'tВҰ8196 return her, be certain that you and all your people will surelyВҰ8201 die.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 SoВҰ8210 \add KingВҰ8218\add* AbimelechВҰ8211 got up earlyВҰ8210 inВҰ8212 the morningВҰ8212 and calledВҰ8213 for all of his slavesВҰ8216 \add to come\add*, and he explained the entireВҰ8220 situation to them and they were very scared.
\v 9 ThenВҰ8229 he sent for AbrahamВҰ8231 and asked him, вҖңWhat have you done to us? What did I do to you thatВҰ8252 you would cause all this trouble for me and my people? What you did to me should never have happened.вҖқ
\v 10 ThenВҰ8259 he asked again, вҖңWhatВҰ8268 were you thinking when you did that?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңBecause I thought that there'sВҰ8278 probably no one around here who \add obeys\add* GodВҰ8281,вҖқ replied AbrahamВҰ8274 вҖңso they might killВҰ8284 me because of my wifeВҰ8288.
\v 12 \add Besides that,\add* Sarah actually \em is\em* my \add half-\add*sister. We have the same fatherВҰ8296, butВҰ8290 different mothersВҰ8302, andВҰ8303 thenВҰ8290 itВҰ8303 was her that I took as a wife.
\v 13 \add Later\add* when GodВҰ8312 got me to leave my father'sВҰ8314 home, I saidВҰ8315 to her, вҖҳYou could do this one kindnessВҰ8318 do for me: Everywhere weВҰ8327 goВҰ8327, just tell them thatВҰ8319 he's yourВҰ8318 brotherВҰ8332.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ8335 \add KingВҰ8342\add* AbimelechВҰ8336 returnedВҰ8343 SarahВҰ8346 his wife to him and also gave him flocks and herds, and male and femaleВҰ8340 slaves,
\v 15 andВҰ8349 he told him, вҖңLook, my land is inВҰ8354 front of you. Settle wherever looks goodВҰ8354 to you.вҖқ
\v 16 ThenВҰ8358 heВҰ8359 saidВҰ8359 to Sarah, вҖңListen, I've given 1,000 pieces of silverВҰ8363 to your brotherВҰ8364. That's for you to demonstrate that you did nothing wrong, so that you're completely cleared.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ8378 AbrahamВҰ8379 prayedВҰ8378 to God, and God healedВҰ8383 AbimelechВҰ8387 and his wife and his slaveВҰ8391 women so that they could have childrenВҰ8392,
\v 18 because YahwehВҰ8398 had made everyВҰ8400 woman in Abimelech'sВҰ8404 householdВҰ8403 barren because of \add what had been happening to\add* Abraham'sВҰ8410 wifeВҰ8409, SarahВҰ8408.
\c 21
\s1 Yitshak's birth
\rem /s1 The Birth of Isaac; The early years of Isaac
\p
\v 1 \add In due course,\add* YahwehВҰ8421 visitedВҰ8414 SarahВҰ8417 just as he'd said and he did for her exactly what he'd said,
\v 2 so that SarahВҰ8428 conceivedВҰ8426 andВҰ8427 gaveВҰ8427 birthВҰ8427 to a son for AbrahamВҰ8436 in his old age at the very timeВҰ8432 \add of the year\add* that GodВҰ8437 had told him.\x + \xo 21:2: \xt Heb 11:11.\x*
\v 3 AbrahamВҰ8440 named their son Yitshak,
\v 4 andВҰ8457 he circumcisedВҰ8457 him when he was eightВҰ8465 daysВҰ8466 old, just as GodВҰ8470 had commandedВҰ8468 him.\x + \xo 21:4: \xt Gen 17:12; Acts 7:8.\x*
\v 5 Abraham was one hundredВҰ8475 years old when his son Yitshak was born,
\v 6 andВҰ8483 SarahВҰ8484 saidВҰ8483, вҖңGodВҰ8488 has brought laughter to me. Everyone who hearsВҰ8491 will laugh with me.вҖқ
\v 7 And she continuedВҰ8496, вҖңWho would have said to AbrahamВҰ8499 that SarahВҰ8502 would breastfeed childrenВҰ8501, yet I have \add given him\add* a son in his old age.вҖқ
\s1 Hagar is expelled with Yishma'el
\rem /s1 Hagar and Ishmael Are Sent Away
\p
\v 8 The childВҰ8510 grew and was weaned, and AbrahamВҰ8513 held a large feastВҰ8514 on the dayВҰ8516 Yitshak was weaned.
\p
\v 9 \add ButВҰ8522\add* SarahВҰ8523 noticedВҰ8522 that \add Yishma'el\add* (the son of HagarВҰ8528 the Egyptian who sheВҰ8532 had given birth to for AbrahamВҰ8533) was mockingВҰ8534,
\v 10 so \add Sarah\add* said to AbrahamВҰ8537, вҖңGet rid of that slave woman andВҰ8536 herВҰ8543 son, because that slave woman's son won'tВҰ8545 be inheritingВҰ8546 \add anything along\add* with my son Yitshak.вҖқ\x + \xo 21:10: \xt Gal 4:29-30.\x*
\v 11 Now this stressed out AbrahamВҰ8562 \add who also cared for that\add* son,
\v 12 butВҰ8567 GodВҰ8568 told him, вҖңDon't get distressed because of the boyВҰ8578 andВҰ8567 your slaveВҰ8581 woman. Listen to what Sarah'sВҰ8586 telling you, because it's inВҰ8575 Yitshak that your descendants will be called yoursВҰ8592.\x + \xo 21:12: \xt Rom 9:7; Heb 11:18.\x*
\v 13 \add ButВҰ8595\add* I'llВҰ8596 also make the descendants of the slaveВҰ8600 woman'sВҰ8600 son into a nationВҰ8601, because he's \add also\add* your \add son\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 AbrahamВҰ8608 got up earlyВҰ8607 the \add next\add* morningВҰ8610, and got some bread and a skin of waterВҰ8615 and helped HagarВҰ8619 put them onВҰ8610 her shoulderВҰ8623. ThenВҰ8607 he gaveВҰ8616 her the child and sentВҰ8627 her away, and she left and wanderedВҰ8629 inВҰ8610 the wildernessВҰ8630 around Be'er-ShevaВҰ8632.
\v 15 \add ButВҰ8640\add* when the waterВҰ8635 from the skin was gone, she threw the child underВҰ8643 one of the bushesВҰ8645,
\v 16 and she went and she went a short distance away (aboutВҰ8652 as far as a bow can shootВҰ8652 an arrow) and sat down there, because she said, вҖңI don'tВҰ8656 want to watch my child dieВҰ8659.вҖқ And as she sat atВҰ8659 a distance, she sobbed loudly.
\p
\v 17 Now God heard the boy's voice, so \add one of\add* God's messengersВҰ8676 calledВҰ8675 Hagar from heavenВҰ8684 andВҰ8669 saidВҰ8685 to her, вҖңWhat's the matter, Hagar? Don't be afraidВҰ8693, because God has heard the boy's voice over thereВҰ8705.
\v 18 Get up and get the boyВҰ8711 and hold on to himВҰ8721 by the handВҰ8715, because I'll make \add his descendants\add* into a greatВҰ8720 nationВҰ8719.вҖқ
\v 19 ThenВҰ8723 GodВҰ8724 \add enabled herВҰ8727 to see\add* a well, so she went and filledВҰ8732 the skin with water and gave the boyВҰ8740 a drink.
\p
\v 20 As the boyВҰ8746 grew up, GodВҰ8743 \add kept watch over\add* him, and he lived inВҰ8749 the wildernessВҰ8749 and became an \add expert withВҰ8749 the bow and arrow\add*.
\v 21 He settled in the ParanВҰ8756 wildernessВҰ8755, andВҰ8754 \add in due course\add* his motherВҰ8760 found an Egyptian girl for him to marry.
\s1 Abraham and Abimelech's agreement
\rem /s1 Abraham and Abimelech Make a Covenant; A Treaty with Abimelech; The Treaty at Be'er-Sheva; The Agreement between Abraham and Abimelech
\p
\v 22 \add One day\add* \add King\add* AbimelechВҰ8770 and FicolВҰ8771, the commanderВҰ8772 of his army, spoke to AbrahamВҰ8777, saying, вҖң\add We can see that\add* GodВҰ8779 is withВҰ8767 you inВҰ8767 everything you do.\x + \xo 21:22: \xt Gen 26:26.\x*
\v 23 SoВҰ8787 thenВҰ8787, swearВҰ8788 to me here by GodВҰ8790 \add that you won't treat\add* me or my childrenВҰ8796 or my descendants \add badly\add*, andВҰ8787 that'll you'll be kind to this country just as IВҰ8801 showed kindnessВҰ8798 to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңI swearВҰ8816 it,вҖқ AbrahamВҰ8814 replied.
\p
\v 25 \add ButВҰ8818\add* AbrahamВҰ8819 complainedВҰ8818 to Abimelech about a well of waterВҰ8827 thatВҰ8828 had been taken over by Abimelech'sВҰ8822 slavesВҰ8830.
\v 26 вҖңI don'tВҰ8835 knowВҰ8836 who did that,вҖқ AbimelechВҰ8834 respondedВҰ8833, вҖңandВҰ8833 you hadn't told me about it, so I've only just heardВҰ8853 about it today.вҖқ
\v 27 ThenВҰ8857 AbrahamВҰ8858 gaveВҰ8861 \add some\add* sheepВҰ8859 andВҰ8861 cattle to AbimelechВҰ8862 to confirm theirВҰ8864 agreement together,
\v 28 andВҰ8867 \add thenВҰ8867\add* he separated sevenВҰ8871 female lambs from the rest of the flockВҰ8873.
\v 29 вҖңWhyВҰ8880 did youВҰ8887 pen those sevenВҰ8883 lambs,вҖқ AbimelechВҰ8877 asked.
\p
\v 30 вҖңBecause I want youВҰ8899 to takeВҰ8896 them,вҖқ Abraham insisted. вҖңI want them to be the verification that it was \em me\em* who dug this well.вҖқ
\v 31 So that's why the placeВҰ8914 was named вҖҳBeerВҰ8916-ShevaвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳWell of the sevenвҖҷ or вҖҳWell of the oathвҖҷ)\add*, because that's where the twoВҰ8921 of them made theirВҰ8921 agreement.
\p
\v 32 SoВҰ8923 the agreement was made atВҰ8925 Be'er-ShevaВҰ8925, thenВҰ8923 AbimelechВҰ8928 and FicolВҰ8929, the commanderВҰ8930 of his army, got up and returnedВҰ8933 \add home\add* to the PhilistineВҰ8937 regionВҰ8936.
\v 33 ThenВҰ8939 \add Abraham\add* plantedВҰ8939 a tamariskВҰ8940 treeВҰ8940 thereВҰ8945 atВҰ8941 Be'er-Sheva, andВҰ8943 he prayed to YahwehВҰ8947, the godВҰ8948 of eternity.
\v 34 ThenВҰ8951 AbrahamВҰ8952 continued his stay in the PhilistineВҰ8954 regionВҰ8953 for quite some time.
\c 22
\s1 God tests Abraham over Yitshak
\rem /s1 Abraham's Obedience Tested; The Command to Sacrifice Isaac; Abraham Tested; God Commands Abraham to Offer Isaac
\p
\v 1 \add Several years later,\add* GodВҰ8963 \add decided to\add* test Abraham, calling him, вҖңAbraham.вҖқ\x + \xo 22:1-13: \xt Heb 11:17-19.\x*
\p вҖңHere I am,вҖқ he replied.
\p
\v 2 вҖңTake your son Yitshak who you loveВҰ8987, your only son,вҖқ God commanded him, вҖңand goВҰ8991 to the MoriahВҰ8997 regionВҰ8996 and sacrifice him thereВҰ8999 as a burntВҰ9000 offeringВҰ9000 on one of the mountainsВҰ9003 thatВҰ9004 I'll \add point out\add* to you.вҖқ\x + \xo 22:2: \xt 2Ch 3:1.\x*
\p
\v 3 SoВҰ9008 AbrahamВҰ9009 got up earlyВҰ9008 inВҰ9010 the morningВҰ9010 and saddledВҰ9011 his donkeyВҰ9014. Then he tookВҰ9015 twoВҰ9018 of his youngВҰ9019 menВҰ9019 withВҰ9010 him and his son Yitshak, and he cut \add some\add* firewood for the burntВҰ9026 offeringВҰ9026. Then they left to go to the placeВҰ9031 thatВҰ9032 GodВҰ9037 had told him.
\v 4 On the thirdВҰ9040 dayВҰ9039 AbrahamВҰ9042 \add looked up ahead\add* and he could see the placeВҰ9049 from a distanceВҰ9050,
\v 5 so he saidВҰ9052 to his youngВҰ9056 menВҰ9056, вҖңStay here by yourselves with the donkeyВҰ9063 while the boyВҰ9065 andВҰ9052 I goВҰ9066 over there to \add worshipВҰ9070 God\add*, thenВҰ9052 we'll comeВҰ9071 back to you \add here\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ9074 AbrahamВҰ9075 took the firewood for the burntВҰ9079 offeringВҰ9079 and put it on his son YitshakВҰ9083, and he carried the fireВҰ9089 pot and the knifeВҰ9092. ThenВҰ9074 the two of them went on togetherВҰ9095,
\v 7 and Yitshak asked his father AbrahamВҰ9101 his father, вҖңMy father?вҖқ
\p вҖңYes, son?вҖқ, he replied.
\p вҖңWe've got the fire and the wood,вҖқ, he continuedВҰ9097, вҖңbutВҰ9097 where'sВҰ9112 the lamb for the burntВҰ9114 offeringВҰ9114?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңGodВҰ9118 will provide the lamb for the burntВҰ9123 offeringВҰ9123 himself, my son,вҖқ AbrahamВҰ9117 answered, andВҰ9125 thenВҰ9116 the two of them continuedВҰ9116 on togetherВҰ9127.
\p
\v 9 Then they cameВҰ9129 to the placeВҰ9132 thatВҰ9133 GodВҰ9137 had told him, and AbrahamВҰ9140 builtВҰ9138 an altar thereВҰ9139 and arrangedВҰ9144 the firewood \add on it\add*. Then he tied up his son Yitshak and laid him on the altar on top of the wood.\x + \xo 22:9: \xt Jam 2:21.\x*
\v 10 ThenВҰ9161 AbrahamВҰ9162 tookВҰ9166 the knifeВҰ9169 andВҰ9161 raised his arm to kill his son,
\v 11 butВҰ9175 one of Yahweh'sВҰ9178 messengersВҰ9177 calledВҰ9175 to him from the sky andВҰ9175 said, вҖңAbraham! Abraham!вҖқ
\p вҖңHere I am.вҖқ he answered.
\p
\v 12 вҖңDon't lift up your handВҰ9193 againstВҰ9194 the boyВҰ9196,вҖқ \add the messenger\add* continuedВҰ9189. вҖңAnd don'tВҰ9190 do anythingВҰ9201 to him, because now I knowВҰ9206 that you \add respect andВҰ9189 obey\add* GodВҰ9210, since you haven't withheldВҰ9213 your son, your only son, from me.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ9222 Abraham raised his head and looked around, and wow, there was a ram was behindВҰ9231 him, caughtВҰ9232 by its hornsВҰ9234 inВҰ9233 the thicketВҰ9233. SoВҰ9222 Abraham wentВҰ9235 and grabbed the ram and sacrificed it as a burntВҰ9242 offeringВҰ9242 instead of his son.
\v 14 SoВҰ9246 AbrahamВҰ9247 named that placeВҰ9250 вҖҳYahweh will provideвҖҷ, andВҰ9246 to this dayВҰ9257 it's still saidВҰ9256, вҖңYahweh will provide onВҰ9258 his mountainВҰ9258.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ9262 the Yahweh'sВҰ9264 messengerВҰ9263 calledВҰ9262 AbrahamВҰ9267 from the sky a secondВҰ9268 time
\v 16 saying, вҖңIВҰ9275, YahwehВҰ9278, make this declaration by my \add authority and truth\add* that becauseВҰ9280 you did that and didn'tВҰ9287 withholdВҰ9288 your only son,\x + \xo 22:16-17: \xt Heb 6:13-14.\x*
\v 17 I'll blessВҰ9298 youВҰ9299 tremendously and I'll cause your descendants to be \add as numerous\add* as the starsВҰ9305 in the sky and as the sand on the beach, and your descendants will be victorious over theirВҰ9317 enemiesВҰ9317.\x + \xo 22:17: \xt Heb 11:12.\x*
\v 18 Because youВҰ9326 obeyed what I said, all the nationsВҰ9322 of the earthВҰ9323 will be blessedВҰ9319 through yourВҰ9320 descendants.вҖқ\x + \xo 22:18: \xt Acts 3:25.\x*
\v 19 ThenВҰ9329 Abraham returnedВҰ9329 to his youngВҰ9333 menВҰ9333 and they all continued onВҰ9343 \add home\add* togetherВҰ9336 to BeerВҰ9339-Sheva, and Abraham \add continued\add* living \add there\add*.
\s1 Nahor's descendants
\rem /s1 Nahor's Sons; The Descendants of Nahor; The Children of Nahor
\p
\v 20 Some time later, AbrahamВҰ9352 heard the news, Look, your brotherВҰ9362 Nahor'sВҰ9361 wife MilcahВҰ9356 has also given birthВҰ9355 to sonsВҰ9360:
\v 21 UzВҰ9366 his eldest \add son\add*, and BuzВҰ9370 his brother and KemuelВҰ9374, the fatherВҰ9375 of AramВҰ9376,
\v 22 KesedВҰ9380, HazoВҰ9383, PildashВҰ9386, YidlafВҰ9389, andВҰ9378 BethuelВҰ9391.вҖқ
\v 23 Those are the eightВҰ9398 sonsВҰ9398 that MilcahВҰ9401 gave birth to for Abraham'sВҰ9404 brotherВҰ9403 NahorВҰ9402, andВҰ9393 BethuelВҰ9393 went on to fatherВҰ9394 RebekahВҰ9397.
\v 24 \add In addition,\add* Nahor's slave-wife ReumahВҰ9408 also gaveВҰ9409 birthВҰ9409 to \add four sons:\add* TebahВҰ9415, GahamВҰ9418, TahashВҰ9421, andВҰ9406 MaacahВҰ9424.
\c 23
\s1 Sarah's death and burial
\rem /s1 Sarah Dies and Abraham Buys a Burial Ground; The Burial of Sarah; Sarah's Death and Burial; The Death of Sarah
\p
\v 1 SarahВҰ9429 went on to be 127 years old
\v 2 when she diedВҰ9440 in \add the city of\add* Kiriat-Arba (now \add called\add* HebronВҰ9445) in the CanaanВҰ9447 regionВҰ9446. AbrahamВҰ9449 wentВҰ9448 in \add by her bed\add* to weep andВҰ9440 mournВҰ9450 for her.
\p
\v 3 \add After a time,\add* AbrahamВҰ9455 got up from beside his deadВҰ9458 \add wife\add* andВҰ9454 he spokeВҰ9459 to the Hitties, \add requesting\add*,
\v 4 вҖңI'm a foreigner and just staying among you. Give me property for a burialВҰ9476 place \add on your land\add* so that I can buryВҰ9478 my deadВҰ9479 \add wife\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 23:4: \xt Heb 11:9,13; Acts 7:16.\x*
\p
\v 5 Those descendants of HetВҰ9485 replied to AbrahamВҰ9488, telling him,
\v 6 вҖңMy masterВҰ9494, listen to us. You're a \add вүҲgodly leaderВҰ9495\add* among us. \add Go ahead and\add* buryВҰ9501 your dead in the choicestВҰ9499 of our burial places. We've all agreed not to prevent you from buryingВҰ9514 your dead in any of our cemeteries.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ9517 AbrahamВҰ9518 stood andВҰ9517 bowedВҰ9519 to the HittitesВҰ9525 who were the land-owners,
\v 8 and \add asked\add* them, вҖңSinceВҰ9537 you're all allowing me to buryВҰ9536 my deadВҰ9539, listenВҰ9541 to me and intercedeВҰ9542 for me withВҰ9545 Zohar'sВҰ9548 son EfronВҰ9545,
\v 9 so thatВҰ9557 he'll \add sell\add* me Makpelah'sВҰ9556 cave which belongs to him andВҰ9550 which is atВҰ9561 the endВҰ9561 of his fieldВҰ9562. \add I'llВҰ9553 pay\add* full priceВҰ9563 if he'll give it to me to use as a burialВҰ9570 place.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 Now EfronВҰ9579 (a HittiteВҰ9580) was sittingВҰ9573 \add there\add* among Het'sВҰ9577 \add other\add* descendants, so he responded to AbrahamВҰ9583 while the other \add land-owners\add* were listening, along withВҰ9584 everyoneВҰ9575 else atВҰ9584 the cityВҰ9592 gateВҰ9590,
\v 11 вҖңNo, my masterВҰ9597. Listen to me: I'll \em give\em* you the fieldВҰ9599 and the cave that's in it. I give it to you in front of all these others, then you can buryВҰ9614 your dead.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ9617 AbrahamВҰ9618 bowedВҰ9617 before the peopleВҰ9620 of the land,
\v 13 andВҰ9623 he told EfronВҰ9626 while all the others were listening, вҖңButВҰ9623 if you would, please listenВҰ9637 to me. I'll \add pay\add* the \add value\add* of the fieldВҰ9640. Accept it from me, thenВҰ9623 I'll buryВҰ9643 my deadВҰ9646 thereВҰ9647.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 EfronВҰ9650 responded to AbrahamВҰ9651,
\v 15 вҖңMy masterВҰ9657, listenВҰ9658 to me. That land's worth 400 shekelsВҰ9662 of silverВҰ9664, butВҰ9666 that's nothing betweenВҰ9665 me and youВҰ9666. \add Just go ahead\add* and buryВҰ9673 yourВҰ9672 deadВҰ9672.вҖқ
\v 16 SoВҰ9675 AbrahamВҰ9676 accepted Efron'sВҰ9679 words andВҰ9675 weighedВҰ9680 out for Efron the price thatВҰ9686 he had mentioned inВҰ9688 the hearingВҰ9688 of Het'sВҰ9691 descendants: 400 shekelsВҰ9694 of silverВҰ9695 (the currency among the merchantsВҰ9697).
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ9699 Efron'sВҰ9702 field that was in MakpelahВҰ9704 which faced MamreВҰ9707 (including the field and the cave that was in it, and all the trees that were in the field that was within all of its surrounding borders) was deeded
\v 18 to Abraham as the new owner as witnessed by Het'sВҰ9729 descendants and everyoneВҰ9727 \add else\add* who had come to the cityВҰ9734 gateВҰ9732.
\v 19 ThenВҰ9736 afterВҰ9736 that, AbrahamВҰ9740 \add laid the body of\add* his wife SarahВҰ9743 to rest in the cave in Makpelah'sВҰ9749 fieldВҰ9748 facing MamreВҰ9753 (also called HebronВҰ9755, in the CanaanВҰ9757 regionВҰ9756).
\v 20 SoВҰ9759 the fieldВҰ9760 was deeded as propertyВҰ9766 to AbrahamВҰ9765 by Het'sВҰ9772 descendants, including the cave in it for a burialВҰ9768 place.
\c 24
\s1 Yitshak's marriage
\rem /s1 A Wife for Isaac; Isaac and Rebecca; Isaac and Rebekah; The Marriage of Isaac and Rebekah; Isaac Marries Rebekah
\p
\v 1 AbrahamВҰ9775 was now getting very old, and Yahweh had blessedВҰ9780 him inВҰ9784 everyВҰ9784 way.
\v 2 ThenВҰ9786 AbrahamВҰ9787 saidВҰ9786 to his oldest slaveВҰ9790 in his householdВҰ9792 who was in chargeВҰ9793 of everything that belonged to him, вҖңPlease put yourВҰ9802 handВҰ9802 underВҰ9803 my thighВҰ9804,
\v 3 and I want you to vow by Yahweh, the god of the heavensВҰ9809 and the god of the earthВҰ9811, that you won'tВҰ9813 select a wifeВҰ9816 for my son \add Yitshak\add* from any of the CanaaniteВҰ9819 women inВҰ9807 this area where we're livingВҰ9822.
\v 4 RatherВҰ9836, youВҰ9832 should goВҰ9832 \add back\add* to my countryВҰ9828 and to my relatives, and find a wifeВҰ9834 for \add him there\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңSuppose the womanВҰ9845 isn'tВҰ9842 willingВҰ9844 to come \add back\add* with me to this place?вҖқ the slaveВҰ9840 asked. вҖңShould I take your son back to the country that you cameВҰ9862 from?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖңMake sure that you don't take my son back thereВҰ9876,вҖқ AbrahamВҰ9867 answered.
\v 7 вҖңYahwehВҰ9878, the godВҰ9880 of the heavensВҰ9881, who tookВҰ9883 me from my father'sВҰ9885 houseВҰ9884 and from the land of my relatives, and who spokeВҰ9889 to me and who promised me, saying, вҖҳI'llВҰ9898 giveВҰ9898 this land to your descendants,вҖҷ he'll sendВҰ9904 his messengerВҰ9905 ahead of you, and you'll \add be guaranteed to\add* bring back a wifeВҰ9908 for my son from thereВҰ9910.
\v 8 IfВҰ9923 \add it turned out that\add* the womanВҰ9916 isn'tВҰ9914 willingВҰ9915 to come \add back\add* with you, thenВҰ9912 you're released from this vow \add to me\add*. \add ButВҰ9912 still in that case,\add* don'tВҰ9914 takeВҰ9927 my son back thereВҰ9928!вҖқ
\v 9 ThenВҰ9930 the slaveВҰ9931 put his handВҰ9934 underВҰ9935 the thighВҰ9936 of his masterВҰ9938 AbrahamВҰ9932 andВҰ9930 promised his \add that he'd follow those instructions.\add*.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ9946 the slaveВҰ9947 tookВҰ9946 tenВҰ9948 of his master's camelsВҰ9949 and \add loaded them with\add* all kinds of goodВҰ9955 thingsВҰ9955 from his master, and \add with his own slaves,\add* he travelled to the cityВҰ9966 of NahorВҰ9967 in the AramВҰ9962-NaharaimВҰ9963 \add region\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ9969 on that first eveningВҰ9978, he made the camelsВҰ9970 kneelВҰ9969 down outsideВҰ9971 the cityВҰ9972 by the well. It was the time that women come out to fetch waterВҰ9976,
\v 12 andВҰ9983 he prayed, вҖңYahwehВҰ9985, GodВҰ9986 of my master Abraham, pleaseВҰ9991 cause it to happenВҰ9989 right in front of me today that you show kindness toward my master Abraham.
\v 13 See, I'm standingВҰ10003 by this \add well\add*, andВҰ10008 the young women from the cityВҰ10010 will be comingВҰ10011 out \add here\add* to fetch waterВҰ10013.
\v 14 Let it be that if I say to a young woman, вҖҳPlease let me have a drink from your water jar,вҖҷ and she says, вҖҳSure, and I'll also get more for your camelsВҰ10029,вҖҷ let her be the one you have appointedВҰ10032 for your slaveВҰ10033 Yitshak. And by \add finding\add* her, I'll know that you've shown kindness toward my masterВҰ10043.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Now before he'd even finishedВҰ10049 speakingВҰ10050, thenВҰ10045 wow, RebekahВҰ10052 arrived with her \add empty\add* water jar on her shoulderВҰ10067. (She was Bethuel'sВҰ10056 daughterвҖ”Bethuel being the son of Abraham'sВҰ10063 brotherВҰ10062 NahorВҰ10061 andВҰ10045 his wifeВҰ10060 MilcahВҰ10059.)
\v 16 The young woman was very beautiful and a virginВҰ10073 who hadn't slept with a manВҰ10074. She wentВҰ10077 down to the well and filledВҰ10079 herВҰ10080 jar and cameВҰ10081 \add back\add* up.
\v 17 The slaveВҰ10084 ranВҰ10083 to meet herВҰ10085 andВҰ10086 saidВҰ10086, вҖңCan I have a smallВҰ10089 drinkВҰ10087 of waterВҰ10091 from yourВҰ10092 jar.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖңDrink, my masterВҰ10096,вҖқ she saidВҰ10094 and quicklyВҰ10097 loweredВҰ10098 her jar to her hands and gaveВҰ10103 himВҰ10103 a drinkВҰ10095,
\v 19 andВҰ10107 after she'd finished givingВҰ10106 himВҰ10106 a drink, she saidВҰ10107, вҖңI'llВҰ10110 also get waterВҰ10110 for yourВҰ10109 camelsВҰ10109 untilВҰ10111 theyВҰ10114 have finished drinkingВҰ10115.вҖқ
\v 20 ThenВҰ10117 she hurried and emptiedВҰ10118 herВҰ10119 jar into the troughВҰ10122 and ran back to the well to draw \add more\add* water, and she drew \add enough\add* water for all his camelsВҰ10132
\v 21 \add while Abraham's slave\add* watched her silentlyВҰ10137 to determine whetherВҰ10139 YahwehВҰ10140 had made his journey successfulВҰ10139 or not.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ10146 when the camelsВҰ10149 had finishedВҰ10148 drinkingВҰ10150, the slave took out an \add expensive\add* gold nose ring andВҰ10146 two \add solid\add* gold braceletsВҰ10158 for herВҰ10161 arms.
\v 23 вҖңTell me, whose daughterВҰ10167 are you?вҖқ he asked her. вҖңIs thereВҰ10174 roomВҰ10178 at your father'sВҰ10177 houseВҰ10175 for us to stay?вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңI'm Bethuel'sВҰ10186 daughterВҰ10184. He's the son of NahorВҰ10193 andВҰ10182 MilcahВҰ10190,вҖқ sheВҰ10192 answered.
\v 25 вҖңWe've got plenty of both strawВҰ10199 and fodderВҰ10202 \add for the camels\add*, and there's also a roomВҰ10207 where you could stay.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ10210 the \add slave\add* bowedВҰ10210 down andВҰ10212 worshippedВҰ10212 YahwehВҰ10213
\v 27 and said, вҖңPraised be Yahweh, my master Abraham'sВҰ10220 godВҰ10218, who hasn't relented from his kindnessВҰ10225 and faithfulnessВҰ10226 toward my master. As for me, Yahweh has led me onВҰ10230 the road to the home of my master's relativesВҰ10234.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ10237 the young woman ranВҰ10237 \add home\add* andВҰ10239 told herВҰ10241 mother'sВҰ10241 householdВҰ10240 what had happened.
\v 29 Now RebekahВҰ10245 had a brotherВҰ10246 named Lavan (LabanВҰ10248), andВҰ10247 he ranВҰ10249 out to the manВҰ10253 at the well.
\v 30 He had seen the nose ring and the braceletsВҰ10267 on his sister's arms, and when he'd heardВҰ10272 his sister Rebekah'sВҰ10276 wordsВҰ10275 saying, вҖңThis is what the man said to me,вҖқ thenВҰ10259 he went to the man, and indeed, he was \add there\add* standingВҰ10289 by the camelsВҰ10292 at the springВҰ10295
\v 31 and he \add invited him\add*, вҖңCome, you who are blessedВҰ10299 by YahwehВҰ10300. Why are you standingВҰ10302 out here? I've \add already\add* prepared the houseВҰ10306 and a placeВҰ10307 for the camelsВҰ10308.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 SoВҰ10310 \add Abraham's slave\add* wentВҰ10310 to the houseВҰ10312. ThenВҰ10310 he unloadedВҰ10313 the camels and gave them strawВҰ10316 and fodderВҰ10317, and waterВҰ10319 to wash his feet and the feet of the men who were with him.\f + \fr 24:32 \ft It's not certain from the pronouns in the text here, just who did what in this second sentenceвҖ”whether it was the slave (the guest) or Lavan (the host), so other translations might vary.\f*
\v 33 ThenВҰ10327 food was set out for \add them\add* to eat, butВҰ10327 \add Abraham's slave\add* said, вҖңI won'tВҰ10332 eat untilВҰ10334 I have \add said what I have to say\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңSpeak thenВҰ10327,вҖқ Lavan respondedВҰ10331.
\p
\v 34 вҖңI'mВҰ10345 one of Abraham'sВҰ10344 slavesВҰ10343,вҖқ he saidВҰ10342,
\v 35 and Yahweh has blessedВҰ10348 my masterВҰ10351 a lot, so that he has becomeВҰ10353 wealthyВҰ10353. \add Yahweh\add* has givenВҰ10354 him cattle, sheepВҰ10357 and goats, silverВҰ10359 and goldВҰ10360, male and femaleВҰ10362 slaves, and camelsВҰ10363 and donkeysВҰ10364.
\v 36 AndВҰ10378 my master's wife SarahВҰ10367 gaveВҰ10374 birthВҰ10366 to a son for my master \add despite\add* herВҰ10373 old age, andВҰ10366 \add my master\add* has givenВҰ10374 him everything that he owns.
\v 37 My masterВҰ10387 made promises, saying, вҖҳYou mustn't get a wifeВҰ10392 for my son from CanaaniteВҰ10395 women whose land I am livingВҰ10398 inВҰ10399,
\v 38 butВҰ10410 rather youВҰ10409 must goВҰ10409 to my father'sВҰ10408 houseВҰ10406 and to my clan, and find a wifeВҰ10414 for my son \add there\add*.вҖҷ
\v 39 ThenВҰ10417 I \add asked\add* my masterВҰ10420, вҖҳSuppose the womanВҰ10425 \add refuses\add* to come with me?вҖҷ
\v 40 And he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖҳ\add The God\add* YahwehВҰ10430 that I obey, he'll sendВҰ10435 his messengerВҰ10436 with you and make yourВҰ10439 journeyВҰ10439 succeedВҰ10438, so that you'll find a wifeВҰ10441 for my son from my clan, and from my father'sВҰ10445 houseВҰ10444.
\v 41 Then you'll be free of your promise: When you goВҰ10451 to my clan, and if they won'tВҰ10457 allow herВҰ10458 to \add return with\add* you, then you'll be clear from \add this promise\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 42 вҖңThenВҰ10464 today I cameВҰ10464 to the well, andВҰ10469 I saidВҰ10469, вҖҳYahwehВҰ10470, GodВҰ10471 of my masterВҰ10472 AbrahamВҰ10473, if it's what youВҰ10476 want, make my journeyВҰ10480 succeedВҰ10479 thatВҰ10481 I have come on.
\v 43 Listen, I'm standingВҰ10488 by this well, so let it be that the youngВҰ10494 womanВҰ10494 who comesВҰ10495 out to fetch water and I say to her, вҖңPlease give me a littleВҰ10502 water to drinkВҰ10499 from your jar,вҖқ
\v 44 and sheВҰ10516 replies to me, вҖңSure, drinkВҰ10512, and I will also get waterВҰ10515 for yourВҰ10514 camelsВҰ10514,вҖқ let her be the wife that YahwehВҰ10521 has chosen for the my master'sВҰ10524 son.вҖҷ
\v 45 Before I'd finishedВҰ10528 speakingВҰ10529 in my heartВҰ10532, then wow, RebekahВҰ10534 was comingВҰ10535 out with her jar on her shoulderВҰ10539. And she wentВҰ10540 down to the well and drew waterВҰ10542, and I asked her, вҖҳCan I have a drinkВҰ10545.вҖҷ
\v 46 So she hurried and loweredВҰ10549 her jar from her \add shoulder\add* and said, вҖҳDrink, and I'll also water your camels.вҖҷ So I drankВҰ10558 and she also watered the camels.
\v 47 Then I askedВҰ10563 her, вҖҳWhose daughter are you?вҖҷ And she said, вҖҳThe daughter of BethuelВҰ10573, a son of NahorВҰ10576 and his wife MilcahВҰ10581.вҖҷ Then I put the ring on her nose and the braceletsВҰ10587 on her arms.
\v 48 ThenВҰ10592 IВҰ10594 bowedВҰ10592 down and worshippedВҰ10593 and praised my master Abraham'sВҰ10601 godВҰ10599 YahwehВҰ10598, who led me onВҰ10604 the right way to \add find\add* the daughterВҰ10609 of my master's brotherВҰ10611 for his son.
\v 49 And now if youВҰ10618 all want to show kindness andВҰ10627 faithfulness to my masterВҰ10624, tell me. ButВҰ10615 if not, tell me, so that I \add can decide what to do next\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 ThenВҰ10641 LavanВҰ10642 andВҰ10644 BethuelВҰ10643 answeredВҰ10641, вҖңThis matterВҰ10647 has comeВҰ10646 from Yahweh, \add so\add* we're not able to tell youВҰ10651 bad or goodВҰ10655.
\v 51 \add ButВҰ10662\add* listen, Rebekah'sВҰ10659 \add right here\add*. Take her and goВҰ10662, and let her become the wifeВҰ10664 of your master'sВҰ10667 son, as YahwehВҰ10670 has \add indicated\add*.вҖқ
\v 52 \add Now\add* when Abraham'sВҰ10676 slaveВҰ10675 heardВҰ10674 theirВҰ10679 \add reply\add*, he bowedВҰ10680 down to the ground before YahwehВҰ10682.
\v 53 ThenВҰ10684 \add he\add* broughtВҰ10684 out silverВҰ10688 and goldВҰ10690 jewellery, and clothing, and gave them to RebekahВҰ10693. And he gave valuable things to her brotherВҰ10696 and her motherВҰ10697.
\p
\v 54 Then \add Abraham's slave\add* and the menВҰ10702 withВҰ10708 him ateВҰ10699 and drankВҰ10700 and stayed \add there overnight\add*. Then inВҰ10708 the morningВҰ10708 they got up, and he saidВҰ10709, вҖң\add Let\add* me \add leave now and return back\add* to my masterВҰ10711.вҖқ
\p
\v 55 ButВҰ10713 \add Rebekah's\add* brotherВҰ10714 andВҰ10715 herВҰ10714 motherВҰ10715 saidВҰ10713, вҖңLet the girlВҰ10717 stay with us a few daysВҰ10719, at least tenВҰ10721. After \add that\add* sheВҰ10723 can goВҰ10723.вҖқ
\p
\v 56 вҖңDon't detain me,вҖқ heВҰ10732 told them, вҖңsince YahwehВҰ10736 has made my journeyВҰ10733 successfulВҰ10732. Send me off so that I \add can return\add* to my masterВҰ10736.вҖқ
\p
\v 57 вҖңLet'sВҰ10742 call for the young woman andВҰ10741 \add find out what she wants to do\add*.вҖқ theyВҰ10738 respondedВҰ10738.
\v 58 SoВҰ10746 they calledВҰ10746 for RebekahВҰ10747 andВҰ10746 asked her, вҖңAre you \add prepared to leave now\add* with this manВҰ10753?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* I'll go.вҖқ she answered.
\p
\v 59 \add SoВҰ10758\add* they \add got ready to\add* send off theirВҰ10762 sisterВҰ10762 RebekahВҰ10761 with Abraham'sВҰ10769 slaveВҰ10768 andВҰ10758 his menВҰ10772, along with herВҰ10765 \add childhood\add* nurseВҰ10765.
\v 60 They \add prayed\add* a blessedВҰ10774 for RebekahВҰ10777, saying
\q1 вҖңOur sisterВҰ10780, may youВҰ10781 becomeВҰ10782 the mother of thousandsВҰ10784,
\q1 andВҰ10774 may yourВҰ10786 descendants defeat all of theirВҰ10789 enemiesВҰ10789.вҖқ
\m
\v 61 ThenВҰ10791 Rebekah got up with herВҰ10793 maidsВҰ10793, and they mountedВҰ10794 the camelsВҰ10797 and wentВҰ10798 with the manВҰ10800. SoВҰ10791 the slaveВҰ10802 tookВҰ10801 Rebekah and left.
\p
\v 62 Meanwhile Yitshak was livingВҰ10815 in the NegevВҰ10817 regionВҰ10816, andВҰ10808 \add had just returned from visiting\add* Be'er-LahaiВҰ10812-Roi.
\v 63 LateВҰ10820 on afternoon, he wentВҰ10819 out to the countrysideВҰ10822 to meditateВҰ10821, andВҰ10819 when he looked up, he sawВҰ10827 some camelsВҰ10829 approaching.
\v 64 RebekahВҰ10833 \add also\add* looked up and sawВҰ10837 YitshakВҰ10840, and dismounted from herВҰ10836 camelВҰ10843,
\v 65 asking the slave, вҖңWho's that manВҰ10851 out in the countrysideВҰ10854 who's coming to meet us?вҖқ
\p вҖңHe's my masterВҰ10859,вҖқ the slave replied, so she tookВҰ10860 the veil andВҰ10845 coveredВҰ10862 herself.
\p
\v 66 ThenВҰ10864 the slaveВҰ10865 reported everything thatВҰ10871 he'd done to YitshakВҰ10866.
\v 67 ThenВҰ10874 Yitshak broughtВҰ10874 her into the tent of SarahВҰ10877 his mother, and he took RebekahВҰ10882 as his wife. And Yitshak lovedВҰ10887 her and he was comfortedВҰ10888 afterВҰ10890 his mother\add 's death\add*.
\c 25
\s1 Abraham's other descendants
\rem /s1 Other Descendants of Abraham; Abraham Marries Keturah; The Death of Abraham
\r (1 Chr. 1:32-33)
\p
\v 1 Then AbrahamВҰ10895 married anotherВҰ10894 woman named KeturahВҰ10899,
\v 2 and she gaveВҰ10901 birthВҰ10901 to ZimranВҰ10905, YokshanВҰ10908, MedanВҰ10911, MidianВҰ10914, YishbakВҰ10917, and ShuahВҰ10920.
\v 3 Yokshan fatheredВҰ10923 ShebaВҰ10926 and Dedan, and the descendants of Dedan were the AsshurimВҰ10933, the LetushimВҰ10934, and the LeummimВҰ10935.
\v 4 Midian'sВҰ10938 sons were EfahВҰ10939, EferВҰ10940, HanochВҰ10941, AbidaВҰ10942, andВҰ10937 EldaahВҰ10943. All of those were Keturah'sВҰ10948 descendants.
\s1 Abraham's death and burial
\p
\v 5-7 AbrahamВҰ10951 \add went on to\add* live to be 175 years old. He gaveВҰ10950 \add valuable\add* gifts to \add all\add* the sons of his slave-wives, thenВҰ10950 he forced them to move to the east to ensure that they would be removed from his son Yitshak. ThenВҰ10950 he left everything \add else\add* he owned to Yitshak.
\rem /s1 The Death and Burial of Abraham; The Death of Abraham
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ10996 AbrahamВҰ10998 \add breathedВҰ10996 his last\add* and diedВҰ10997 atВҰ10999 a goodВҰ11000 old age, elderly and \add satisfied\add*, and he joined his \add ancestors inВҰ10999 death\add*.
\v 9 His sonsВҰ11012 Yitshak andВҰ11011 Yishma'elВҰ11011 buriedВҰ11008 him in Makpelah'sВҰ11016 cave (in the fieldВҰ11019 of EfronВҰ11020, ZoharВҰ11023 the Hittite'sВҰ11024 son, whichВҰ11025 faced MamreВҰ11029)вҖ”
\v 10 the fieldВҰ11031 that Abraham had bought from Het'sВҰ11039 sonsВҰ11037. So Abraham\add 's body was laid thereВҰ11040 alongside that of\add* his wife SarahВҰ11043.\x + \xo 25:10: \xt Gen 23:3-16.\x*
\v 11 After his deathВҰ11048, GodВҰ11051 blessedВҰ11050 his son Yitshak who lived near Be'er-LahaiВҰ11061-Roi.
\s1 Yishma'el's Descendants
\rem /s1 Ishmael's Sons; Ishmael's Descendants; The Descendants of Ishmael
\r (1 Chr. 1:28-31)
\p
\v 12 Now theseВҰ11065 are the generations of Yishma'elВҰ11067 the son of Abraham, whom HagarВҰ11073 the Egyptian, Sarah'sВҰ11076 female slaveВҰ11075, had given birth to for Abraham.
\v 13 These are the names of Yishma'el's sons, by their names according to their birthsВҰ11084: Yishma'el's firstbornВҰ11085 was NevayotВҰ11087, thenВҰ11079 KedarВҰ11088, AdbeelВҰ11089, MibsamВҰ11090,
\v 14 MishmaВҰ11092, DumahВҰ11093, MassaВҰ11094,
\v 15 HadadВҰ11096, TemaВҰ11097, YeturВҰ11098, NafishВҰ11099, and KedermahВҰ11100.
\v 16 Those were Yishma'el'sВҰ11105 sonsВҰ11104, and those are their namesВҰ11107 by their settlements and by their campsвҖ”twelve rulers accordingВҰ11114 to their tribesВҰ11114.
\v 17 Yishma'elВҰ11119 went on to live to be 137 yearsВҰ11125 old, before breathingВҰ11126 his last and dying and joining those who'd gone before.
\v 18 \add His descendants\add* settledВҰ11133 from HavilahВҰ11134 to ShurВҰ11137 (whichВҰ11138 is near EgyptВҰ11142 as you go towardВҰ11144 AsshurВҰ11144). He fell in the face of all his brothers.\f + \fr 25:18 \ft We've left this unusual sentence in here, because we don't really know now what this ancient idiom meant. Possibilities include being hostile to the brothers, living opposite them, or even dying in their presence.\f*
\s1 The birth of Esaw and Yacob
\rem /s1 The Birth and Youth of Esau and Jacob; The Births of Jacob and Esau; Jacob and Esau; The Birth of Esau and Jacob
\p
\v 19 These are the generations of Abraham'sВҰ11159 son Yitshak: Abraham fatheredВҰ11161 Yitshak
\v 20 andВҰ11166 Yitshak was fortyВҰ11170 years old when he married RebekahВҰ11175. (She was the daughterВҰ11176 of BethuelВҰ11178 the Aramean from PaddanВҰ11180-Aram, the sisterВҰ11182 of LavanВҰ11183 the Aramean.)
\v 21 \add In due course,\add* Yitshak prayed to Yahweh on his wife's behalfВҰ11191 because sheВҰ11195 was barrenВҰ11194. Yahweh \add вүҲanswered his prayerВҰ11196\add* andВҰ11199 his wife RebekahВҰ11200 got pregnantВҰ11199,
\v 22 \add butВҰ11203 the twins kept jostling\add* each other within herВҰ11205 \add womb\add*, so she asked, вҖңWhy's this happening to me?вҖқ She \add also\add* asked YahwehВҰ11217 about it
\v 23 and he respondedВҰ11219,\x + \xo 25:23: \xt Rom 9:12.\x*
\q1 вҖңThere's two nationsВҰ11223 inside yourВҰ11228 wombвҖ”
\q2 two \add different\add* peoplesВҰ11227 will come from withinВҰ11228 you.
\q1 One group will become strongerВҰ11232 than the other,
\q2 and the olderВҰ11233 will serveВҰ11234 the youngerВҰ11235.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 WhenВҰ11237 the time came to give birth, she gave birth to twin \add boys\add*.
\v 25 The firstbornВҰ11245 came out quite red andВҰ11250 covered with hair like a fur coat, so they named him вҖҳEsawВҰ11252вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳhairyвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 26 ThenВҰ11254 his brother was born andВҰ11263 his handВҰ11259 grabbed Esaw's heel, so heВҰ11257 was named вҖҳYacobВҰ11265вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳheel-grabberвҖҷ)\add*. Yitshak was sixtyВҰ11269 years old when they were born.
\s1 Esaw sells his future inheritance
\rem /s1 Esau Sells His Rights as the First-Born Son; Esau Sells His Birthright
\p
\v 27 As the boysВҰ11275 grew up, EsawВҰ11277 \add got good\add* at huntingВҰ11280, a man of the \add outdoors\add*, \add butВҰ11274\add* YacobВҰ11283 was a quietВҰ11285 man who stayed around the tentsВҰ11287.
\v 28 YitshakВҰ11290 liked the tasteВҰ11297 of game meat so he loved EsawВҰ11293, butВҰ11289 RebekahВҰ11298 loved YacobВҰ11302.
\rem /s1 Esau Sells His Birthright
\p
\v 29 \add One day,\add* YacobВҰ11305 was cookingВҰ11304 some stew when EsawВҰ11308 arrived home from being out, andВҰ11304 he was very hungry
\v 30 andВҰ11315 asked YacobВҰ11319, вҖңI'm \add вүҲstarving\add*вҖ”can I have some of that \add вүҲyummy-looking\add* red \add >stuff\add*.вҖқ (After that, Esaw's nickname became вҖҳEdomВҰ11336вҖҷ, \add meaning вҖҳredвҖҷ\add*.)
\p
\v 31 вҖң\add WellВҰ11342,\add* now,вҖқ YacobВҰ11339 answered, вҖңsell me yourВҰ11344 future inheritance.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 вҖңListen, I'm dying \add of starvation\add*,вҖқ saidВҰ11347 EsawВҰ11348, вҖңso what use would a future inheritance be to me?вҖқ
\p
\v 33 вҖң\add Well\add* thenВҰ11359, make a vow to me,вҖқ insisted YacobВҰ11360.\x + \xo 25:33: \xt Heb 12:16.\x*
\p SoВҰ11359 Esaw promised him, \add effectively\add* selling his future inheritance to Yacob,
\v 34 and YacobВҰ11384 gaveВҰ11373 him some of the lentilВҰ11377 stew and \add some\add* breadВҰ11375. \add SoВҰ11372\add* EsawВҰ11374 ateВҰ11378 and drankВҰ11379 and left again, thus despisingВҰ11382 his own inheritance \add as firstborn son\add*.
\c 26
\s1 Yitshak moves to Gerar
\rem /s1 Isaac and Abimelech; Isaac Lives at Gerar; Isaac at Gerar and Be'er-Sheva; Isaac Deceives Abimelech
\p
\v 1 Then there was a famine in the region (a different one from the earlier famine thatВҰ11395 was in the daysВҰ11397 of AbrahamВҰ11398) so Yitshak \add moved\add* to GerarВҰ11408, \add the region of\add* AbimelechВҰ11403, the PhilistinesВҰ11407 kingВҰ11405.
\v 2 ThenВҰ11410 YahwehВҰ11412 appearedВҰ11410 to \add Yitshak\add* andВҰ11413 told him, вҖңDon't goВҰ11416 down to EgyptВҰ11417вҖ”stay in the area thatВҰ11420 I'll tell youВҰ11422.
\v 3 Stay as a guest in this region, and I'll be with you and blessВҰ11429 you, because I'll giveВҰ11434 all this land to you and to your descendantsВҰ11433, and I'll confirm the oath thatВҰ11445 I made to your father AbrahamВҰ11447.\x + \xo 26:3-4: \xt Gen 22:16-18.\x*
\v 4 I'll multiply your descendants \add to be as numerousВҰ11450\add* as the starsВҰ11454 inВҰ11464 the sky, andВҰ11450 I'll giveВҰ11456 all this region to them. And all the nationsВҰ11466 onВҰ11464 the earthВҰ11467 will be blessedВҰ11463 through your descendants,
\v 5 because AbrahamВҰ11473 obeyed me by keeping my requirements, my commandsВҰ11477, my decrees, and my laws.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ11481 YitshakВҰ11482 settled \add there\add* inВҰ11483 GerarВҰ11483.
\v 7 ThenВҰ11485 the men of the place askedВҰ11485 aboutВҰ11488 his wife, andВҰ11485 he said, вҖңShe's my sisterВҰ11490,вҖқ because he was afraidВҰ11493 to say, вҖңShe's my wife.вҖқ He was thinking, вҖңWhat if the men in this place kill me because RebekahВҰ11503 is so beautiful to look at.вҖқ\x + \xo 26:7: \xt Gen 12:13; 20:2.\x*
\v 8 ThenВҰ11510 when he'd been in that area for quite a while, the PhilistineВҰ11520 KingВҰ11519 AbimelechВҰ11518 lookedВҰ11517 down from a windowВҰ11522 andВҰ11510 sawВҰ11523 that \add to his surprise\add*, YitshakВҰ11525 was laughing \add together\add* with his wife RebekahВҰ11528.
\v 9 So AbimelechВҰ11532 calledВҰ11531 for Yitshak andВҰ11531 said, вҖңHey, she's really your wifeВҰ11537! So how could you say, вҖҳShe's my sisterВҰ11541вҖҷ?вҖқ
\p вҖңBecause I said \add to myself\add*, вҖҳI might dieВҰ11550 because of herВҰ11551.вҖҷ,вҖқ Yitshak replied.
\p
\v 10 вҖңWhat's this that you've done to us?вҖқ continuedВҰ11553 AbimelechВҰ11554. вҖңOne of \add my\add* peopleВҰ11563 mightВҰ11560 easily have slept with your wife andВҰ11567 you would have broughtВҰ11567 condemnation onto us!вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ11571 \add King\add* AbimelechВҰ11572 orderedВҰ11571 all the peopleВҰ11577, вҖңWhoever touchesВҰ11579 this manВҰ11580 or his wifeВҰ11582 will certainly be killed.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Conflict over Water Rights
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ11586 YitshakВҰ11587 \add planted a crop\add* inВҰ11591 that land and YahwehВҰ11596 blessedВҰ11595 him and gave him one hundredВҰ11593 times as much as he'd planted.
\v 13 HenceВҰ11604 he becameВҰ11606 \add wealthier\add* andВҰ11598 that repeated untilВҰ11603 \add eventually\add* he was \add very powerful\add*.
\v 14 He \add also\add* owned sheep and goats, and cattle, and many slavesВҰ11617. \add Because\add* the PhilistinesВҰ11621 \add now\add* enviedВҰ11619 him,
\v 15 they blocked up all the wellsВҰ11625 thatВҰ11626 his father's slavesВҰ11628 had dug when his father AbrahamВҰ11634 had been alive, andВҰ11623 they filled them withВҰ11630 dirt.
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ11638 \add King\add* AbimelechВҰ11639 told Yitshak, вҖңYou all \add need to\add* leave this area because you've becomeВҰ11647 more powerfulВҰ11647 than us.вҖқ
\v 17 SoВҰ11652 Yitshak left that place and set up camp inВҰ11656 the GerarВҰ11658 Valley and settled there.
\v 18 ThenВҰ11662 he returned and dug out the waterВҰ11669 wellsВҰ11668 that they had dug inВҰ11672 the daysВҰ11672 of Abraham his father and that the PhilistinesВҰ11676 had blocked up afterВҰ11677 Abraham'sВҰ11673 deathВҰ11678, and he called them similar namesВҰ11682 to the ones that his father had called them.
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ11690 Yitshak'sВҰ11693 slavesВҰ11691 dug inВҰ11694 the valleyВҰ11694 andВҰ11695 foundВҰ11695 an \add underground\add* spring withВҰ11694 flowing waterВҰ11699 thereВҰ11697.
\v 20 ButВҰ11702 the herdsmen from GerarВҰ11704 quarrelledВҰ11718 with Yitshak's herdsmen, saying, вҖңThe waterВҰ11711 belongs to us.вҖқ SoВҰ11702 he named the well вҖҳEsekвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳdisputeвҖҷ)\add*, because they disputed with him.
\p
\v 21 \add Yitshak's men\add* dug anotherВҰ11723 well, butВҰ11721 they quarrelledВҰ11724 over it too, so he named it вҖҳSitnahВҰ11730вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳoppositionвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 22 ThenВҰ11732 he movedВҰ11732 from thereВҰ11733 and dug anotherВҰ11736 well, and they didn'tВҰ11737 quarrel over it, so he named it вҖҳRehobothВҰ11742вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳspaceвҖҷ)\add*, and he saidВҰ11743, вҖңBecause now YahwehВҰ11748 has made space for us and we'll be productive in this area.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ11753 from thereВҰ11754 Yitshak moved \add down\add* to BeerВҰ11755-ShebaВҰ11756,
\v 24 and YahwehВҰ11760 appearedВҰ11758 to him during that nightВҰ11761 and saidВҰ11763, вҖңI am the godВҰ11765 of your father Abraham. Don't be afraidВҰ11770, because I'm withВҰ11761 you and I will blessВҰ11775 you and multiplyВҰ11776 your descendants for the sake of my slaveВҰ11782 Abraham.вҖқ
\v 25 SoВҰ11784 Yitshak builtВҰ11784 an altarВҰ11786 there and he prayed to YahwehВҰ11789. He set up his tents there and his slavesВҰ11797 dug a well there.
\s1 Abimilik wants a commitment from Yitshak
\rem /s1 The Agreement between Isaac and Abimelech; A Treaty with Abimelech
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ11802 \add King\add* AbimelechВҰ11802 cameВҰ11803 to \add Yitshak\add* from GerarВҰ11805 along with his friend AhuzzathВҰ11806 andВҰ11802 FicolВҰ11808 the commanderВҰ11809 of his army\x + \xo 26:26: \xt Gen 21:22.\x*
\v 27 and Yitshak \add asked\add* them, вҖңWhy have you comeВҰ11817 \add here\add* since you hateВҰ11820 me and you \add forced\add* me away from you?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖңWe have clearlyВҰ11826 seen that YahwehВҰ11831 has been with you,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңso we said, вҖҳThere shouldВҰ11835 be an agreement between usвҖҷвҖ”between us andВҰ11825 you. SoВҰ11825 let us make an agreement with you,
\v 29 thatВҰ11854 you won'tВҰ11852 do \add anything\add* evil against us, just as we did not touchВҰ11853 you, and just as we did only did goodВҰ11859 to you and sentВҰ11860 you away inВҰ11861 peaceВҰ11861. Now you are blessedВҰ11864 by YahwehВҰ11865.вҖқ
\v 30 ThenВҰ11867 \add Yitshak prepared\add* a feastВҰ11869 for them, and they \add all\add* ateВҰ11870 and drankВҰ11871 \add together\add*.
\v 31 \add The visitors\add* got up earlyВҰ11873 the \add next\add* morningВҰ11874 and make promises to each otherВҰ11877. ThenВҰ11873 Yitshak sentВҰ11878 them onВҰ11874 their wayВҰ11878, and they left from \add there\add* inВҰ11874 peaceВҰ11882.
\p
\v 32 That \add very\add* dayВҰ11886, Yitshak's slavesВҰ11889 cameВҰ11888 and \add updated\add* him about the well thatВҰ11897 they had \add just been\add* digging and told him, вҖңWe've foundВҰ11901 waterВҰ11902.вҖқ
\v 33 SoВҰ11904 \add Yitshak\add* named \add the well\add* вҖҳShibahВҰ11906вҖҷ \add (which sounds like the Hebrew word meaning вҖҳpromiseвҖҷ)\add*, so that's why that cityВҰ11912 is named вҖҳBeerВҰ11913-ShevaвҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳwell of the promiseвҖҷ)\add* to this dayВҰ11916.
\s1 Esaw marries outsiders
\rem /s1 Esau's Foreign Wives; Esau's Hittite Wives
\p
\v 34 When EsawВҰ11921 was fortyВҰ11924 years old, he married \add two\add* HittiteВҰ11934 women: Be'eri's daughter YuditВҰ11930 and Elon'sВҰ11940 daughter BasematВҰ11937,
\v 35 \add butВҰ11943\add* this brought grief to his parents YitshakВҰ11946 andВҰ11947 RebekahВҰ11947.
\c 27
\s1 Yitshak's tricked into blessing Yacob
\rem /s1 Jacob Gets Isaac's Blessing; Jacob Steals Esau's Blessing; Jacob and Esau; Isaac Blesses Jacob
\p
\v 1 When Yitshak grew old and could no longer see, he calledВҰ11958 his older son Esaw and said to him, вҖңMy son.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add I'm here\add*,вҖқ Esaw replied.
\p
\v 2 вҖңPlease listen,вҖқ Yitshak \add continuedВҰ11972\add*, вҖңI'm old andВҰ11972 don'tВҰ11977 knowВҰ11978 how long I've got before I die.
\v 3 SoВҰ11982 pleaseВҰ11985 takeВҰ11983 your weaponsВҰ11986вҖ”your quiverВҰ11987, and your bowвҖ”and goВҰ11989 out into the countrysideВҰ11990 and hunt game for me
\v 4 and cook me a tasty meal inВҰ12008 the way that I loveВҰ12001 it, and bringВҰ12002 it to me so I can eatВҰ12004 it, so that \add I\add* can blessВҰ12006 youВҰ12006 beforeВҰ12008 I dieВҰ12009.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add Now\add* RebekahВҰ12011 had been listeningВҰ12012 while Yitshak spokeВҰ12013 to Esaw. ThenВҰ12011 Esaw wentВҰ12019 \add out\add* to the countrysideВҰ12021 to hunt game andВҰ12019 bringВҰ12024 it back.
\v 6 \add Meanwhile\add* RebekahВҰ12026 saidВҰ12027 to herВҰ12031 son YacobВҰ12030, вҖңListen, I heardВҰ12034 your father speakingВҰ12038 to your brotherВҰ12042 EsawВҰ12041, saying,
\v 7 вҖҳGet \add some\add* game \add meat\add* for me and prepareВҰ12048 me a tasty meal so that I can eatВҰ12052 it, and \add then\add* I can blessВҰ12053 youВҰ12053 in Yahweh'sВҰ12055 presence before I dieВҰ12057.вҖҷ
\v 8 SoВҰ12059 now \add Yacob\add*, listenВҰ12061 to what I tell youВҰ12066:
\v 9 Go \add out\add* to the flockВҰ12073 and get me twoВҰ12078 of the \add best\add* young goatsВҰ12080 so that I can prepareВҰ12082 a tasty meal from them that yourВҰ12085 fatherВҰ12085 lovesВҰ12087.
\v 10 ThenВҰ12089 you \add can\add* takeВҰ12089 it \add inВҰ12092\add* to yourВҰ12090 fatherВҰ12090, andВҰ12091 \add after\add* he's eaten it, he'll blessВҰ12094 you before he diesВҰ12096.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңLook,вҖқ YacobВҰ12099 saidВҰ12098 to his motherВҰ12103, вҖңMy brotherВҰ12106 EsawВҰ12105 is \add very\add* hairyВҰ12108, whereas \add my skin\add* is smoothВҰ12111.
\v 12 What if my fatherВҰ12115 touches me? Then he'll think of me as a deceiverВҰ12118 and \add he'll\add* curseВҰ12121 me rather than blessВҰ12123 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖңLet yourВҰ12129 curseВҰ12129 be onВҰ12133 me, my son,вҖқ his motherВҰ12127 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңJust \add do\add* what I saidВҰ12125 andВҰ12134 goВҰ12134 get \add the young goats\add* for me.вҖқ
\v 14 \add SoВҰ12139\add* he went and \add slaughtered them\add* and broughtВҰ12141 \add them\add* to his mother. ThenВҰ12139 \add she\add* preparedВҰ12143 tasty food the way his fatherВҰ12148 lovedВҰ12147 \add it\add*.
\v 15 \add She thenВҰ12150\add* got Esaw's best clothesВҰ12154 thatВҰ12159 were inВҰ12161 the houseВҰ12161 andВҰ12162 \add got\add* herВҰ12156 youngerВҰ12167 son YacobВҰ12165 to put \add them\add* onВҰ12161,
\v 16 and thenВҰ12169 sheВҰ12173 \add tied\add* the skinsВҰ12170 of the young goatsВҰ12172 \add over\add* his handsВҰ12176 andВҰ12177 \add around\add* the smoothВҰ12178 part of his neck.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ12181 sheВҰ12189 \add handed\add* the tastyВҰ12184 food andВҰ12181 the breadВҰ12187 to YacobВҰ12191,
\v 18 and he went \add in\add* to his \add elderly\add* father and said, вҖңMy father.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm here,вҖқ \add he\add* said, вҖңWhich son are you?вҖқ
\v 19 вҖңI'm your oldest son EsawВҰ12212,вҖқ YacobВҰ12207 \add вүҲreplied\add* to his fatherВҰ12210. вҖңI've done what you told me. Please get up, \add and come and\add* sitВҰ12221 up and eatВҰ12222 some of my game, so that you'll blessВҰ12225 me.вҖқ
\v 20 вҖңHow did you find it so quickly, my son?вҖқ Yitshak \add asked\add*.
\p вҖңBecause your godВҰ12243 YahwehВҰ12242 \add helped me when I went out hunting\add*,вҖқ Yacob \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ12246 Yitshak saidВҰ12246 to YacobВҰ12250, вҖңPlease comeВҰ12251 close so that I can touch you, my son, andВҰ12246 \add to be sure\add* whetherВҰ12256 you're really my son EsawВҰ12259 or not.вҖқ
\v 22 SoВҰ12264 Yacob went close to his fatherВҰ12269 and \add Yitshak\add* felt \add his skin\add* and said \add to himself\add*, вҖңIt's Yacob'sВҰ12265 voice, butВҰ12264 \add these\add* are \add definitely\add* Esaw's hands.вҖқ
\v 23 SoВҰ12279 he didn'tВҰ12279 recogniseВҰ12280 \add that it was Yacob\add*, because his hands were hairyВҰ12288 like Esaw's hands, so he was about to blessВҰ12289 him
\v 24 \add butВҰ12291 asked once more,\add* вҖңAre youВҰ12292 really my son EsawВҰ12295?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* I am,вҖқ Yacob answered.
\p
\v 25 \add So Yitshak told him\add*, вҖңBring the food \add here\add* and I'll eat some of myВҰ12307 son'sВҰ12304 game, so that \add I can then\add* blessВҰ12306 you.вҖқ \add So Yacob\add* took it to him and he ate, and then he brought wine to him and he drankВҰ12315.
\v 26 ThenВҰ12317 Yitshak asked \add Yacob\add*, вҖңMy son, pleaseВҰ12323 comeВҰ12321 close andВҰ12324 kissВҰ12324 me.вҖқ
\v 27 SoВҰ12329 he wentВҰ12329 close andВҰ12329 kissedВҰ12330 him. \add His dad noticed\add* the smell of his clothes, so he blessed him saying,\x + \xo 27:27-29: \xt Heb 11:20.\x*
\q1 вҖң\add Ah yes,\add* the smell of my son
\q2 is like the \add pleasant\add* fragrance of \add the\add* countrysideВҰ12344
\q2 thatВҰ12345 YahwehВҰ12347 has blessed.
\q1
\v 28 May GodВҰ12352 giveВҰ12349 you dew from the sky
\q2 and riches from the land,
\q1 \add to produce\add* plenty of grainВҰ12358 and wine.
\q1
\v 29 May peoples serve you,
\q2 and may nations bow down to you.
\q1 Be masterВҰ12369 over your brothersВҰ12370,
\q2 and may your mother'sВҰ12375 sonsВҰ12374 bow down to you.
\q1 \add May\add* those \add who\add* curse you be cursed,\x + \xo 27:29: \xt Gen 12:3.\x*
\q2 and \add may\add* those \add who\add* bless you be blessed.вҖқ
\s1 Esaw begs for a secondary blessing
\rem /s1 Esau's Lost Blessing; Esau Begs for Isaac's Blessing
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ12381 just as Yitshak had finishedВҰ12383 blessingВҰ12385 Yacob, andВҰ12381 as Yacob had only just gone out from his father'sВҰ12397 presence, his brother EsawВҰ12398 his brother \add returned\add* from his huntingВҰ12401.
\v 31 ThenВҰ12403 he too prepared \add some\add* tasty food and broughtВҰ12408 it \add in\add* to his father and said, вҖңLet my father get up and eat from the game that his son \add hunted\add* so that you can blessВҰ12418 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 ButВҰ12421 Yitshak asked him, вҖңWhich son \add are\add* youВҰ12427?вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm your oldest son EsawВҰ12432.вҖқ he \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 33 Then Yitshak \add started to\add* trembledВҰ12434 \add badly\add* and he saidВҰ12441, вҖңThen who was it that hunted game and broughtВҰ12449 it to me? I ateВҰ12451 it all just beforeВҰ12453 you cameВҰ12454 \add inВҰ12453\add*, and I blessed \add that man\add* and indeed, he'll be blessed.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 When EsawВҰ12462 heardВҰ12461 \add that\add*, then he let out a very loud and exceedingly bitterВҰ12470 wail, and \add then begged\add* his father, вҖңBless me too, my father.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 ButВҰ12482 Yitshak replied, вҖңYour brotherВҰ12484 cameВҰ12483 \add inВҰ12485 and deceivedВҰ12485 me\add* and he's taken yourВҰ12487 blessingВҰ12487!вҖқ
\p
\v 36 вҖң\add Yes,\add* his nameВҰ12492 YacobВҰ12493 \add (meaning вҖҳdeceiverВҰ12494вҖҷ) suits him exactly!\add*вҖқ\x + \xo 27:36: \xt Gen 25:29-34.\x* said Esaw. вҖң\add First\add* he took my inheritance andВҰ12489 man, now he's also takenВҰ12503 my blessing!вҖқ ThenВҰ12489 he \add asked\add*, вҖңHaven't you \add at least\add* saved a blessing for me?вҖқ
\p
\v 37 ButВҰ12512 Yitshak replied, вҖңListen, I've made him masterВҰ12517 over you, and I've givenВҰ12525 all his brothers to him as slavesВҰ12527. And I've sustainedВҰ12530 him with grainВҰ12528 and wine. SoВҰ12512 thenВҰ12512, what \add else\add* can I do for you, my son?вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖңMy father, Did you \add only\add* have \em one\em* blessingВҰ12542 that you \add could give\add*?вҖқ Esaw \add asked\add*. вҖңBless me too, my father!вҖқ ThenВҰ12537 Esaw sobbed loudly.\x + \xo 27:38: \xt Heb 12:17.\x*
\p
\v 39 ThenВҰ12558 his fatherВҰ12560 Yitshak respondedВҰ12561 and saidВҰ12561 to him,\x + \xo 27:39-40: \xt Heb 11:20.\x*
\q1 вҖңListen, you \add and yourВҰ12567 descendants\add* will live
\q2 away from the \add most fertile land\add* on the earth\f + \fr 27:39 \ft The Hebrew text is ambiguous here. It could mean: (1) вҖңaway from the fatness of the earth and away from the dew of the heavens from above.вҖқ or вҖңin a place/region where the earth/land/ground is not rich/fertile and where there is very little dew/rain.вҖқ or вҖңin a place/region where the land/soil is not good for farming and where there is not much rain.вҖқ or (2) вҖңof the fatness of the earth and of the dew of the heavens from above.вҖқ or вҖңin a place where the land is good/fertile for farming and where there is plenty of dew/rain.вҖқ\f*
\q1 in a place that doesn't get dew from the sky.
\q1
\v 40 YouВҰ12576 \add and your descendants\add* will liveВҰ12575 by your swordВҰ12574,\x + \xo 27:40: \xt Gen 36:8; 2Ki 8:20.\x*
\q2 and you'll serveВҰ12579 your brotherВҰ12578.
\q1 ButВҰ12572 when you become restlessВҰ12582
\q2 you'll \add all\add* breakВҰ12583 away from serving them.
\rem /s1 Jacob Flees to Paddan-Aram; Jacob Flees to Laban; Jacob Escapes Esau's Fury
\p
\v 41 \add From that time onwards,\add* Esaw hated Yacob because of the blessing that \add their\add* father had blessed him withВҰ12601, andВҰ12588 Esaw said \add to himself\add*, вҖңMy father's \add funeral\add* can't be that far awayвҖ”\add after that\add* I'll kill my brotherВҰ12610 Yacob.вҖқ
\p
\v 42 ButВҰ12612 RebekahВҰ12613 got to hear about Esaw's \add plans\add*, so she sentВҰ12620 for herВҰ12618 youngerВҰ12624 son YacobВҰ12622 andВҰ12612 told him, вҖңListen, your brotherВҰ12629 Esaw is \add coping with what happened by\add* planning to killВҰ12632 youВҰ12632.
\v 43 SoВҰ12634 my son, listenВҰ12636 to what I'm saying: for your own sake, \add pack\add* up andВҰ12638 flee to my brotherВҰ12645 Lavan's place inВҰ12637 HaranВҰ12646
\v 44 andВҰ12648 stayВҰ12648 with him for a \add while\add* untilВҰ12652 your brotherВҰ12657 \add cools down\add*.
\v 45 When \add he's\add* no longer angry with you and forgetsВҰ12666 what you did to him, then I'll sendВҰ12672 for you from thereВҰ12674 \add so you can return here\add*. I \add don't want to\add* lose both of you on the \add same\add* dayВҰ12680.вҖқ
\s1 Yitshak sends Yacob off to Lavan's
\rem /s1 Isaac Sends Jacob to Laban
\p
\v 46 ThenВҰ12683 RebekahВҰ12684 told her husband Yitshak, вҖңI'm \add quite\add* disgusted withВҰ12689 \add those\add* daughters of Het. If YacobВҰ12696 chooses a wife like Het'sВҰ12692 daughters from \add this culture around us here\add*, \add I wouldn't be able to bear it\add*.вҖқ
\c 28
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ12708 Yitshak calledВҰ12708 for YacobВҰ12712 and blessedВҰ12713 him, and instructedВҰ12715 him, вҖңDon't takeВҰ12720 a wifeВҰ12721 from the Caananite girls.
\v 2 \add Pack\add* up and goВҰ12726 to PaddanВҰ12727-AramВҰ12728вҖ”to the home of your mother's fatherВҰ12731 BethuelВҰ12730 and get yourselfВҰ12735 a wifeВҰ12737 from thereВҰ12736вҖ”from the daughtersВҰ12738 of your mother's brotherВҰ12740 LavanВҰ12739.
\v 3 AndВҰ12746 may the powerful GodВҰ12743 blessВҰ12745 you and make you fruitfulВҰ12747 and multiplyВҰ12748 you so that you becomeВҰ12749 a community of peoplesВҰ12751.
\v 4 May he giveВҰ12753 the \add same\add* blessingВҰ12758 of Abraham to youвҖ”to you and to yourВҰ12763 offspring with youвҖ”so thatВҰ12768 you will ownВҰ12763 the land where you've been staying and whichВҰ12768 GodВҰ12771 gaveВҰ12770 to Abraham.вҖқ\x + \xo 28:4: \xt Gen 17:4-8.\x*
\v 5 ThenВҰ12774 Yitshak sentВҰ12774 Yacob \add away\add*, and he wentВҰ12779 to PaddanВҰ12780-AramВҰ12781вҖ”to LavanВҰ12784, the son of BethuelВҰ12787 the ArameanВҰ12788 and the brotherВҰ12789 of Yacob and Esaw's motherВҰ12791 RebekahВҰ12790.
\s1 Esaw adds a non-Canaanite wife
\rem /s1 Esau Marries Ishmael's Daughter; Esau Takes Another Wife
\p
\v 6 Now EsawВҰ12796 noticed that Yitshak had blessed YacobВҰ12803 andВҰ12795 sent him to PaddanВҰ12806-AramВҰ12807 to take a wife for himself from thereВҰ12811. \add He'd also noticed\add* that when \add Yitshak\add* had blessed him, he'd instructedВҰ12815 him not to take a wife from the Canaanite girls,
\v 7 and that YacobВҰ12826 had listenedВҰ12825 to his parents and travelled to PaddanВҰ12834-AramВҰ12835.
\v 8 \add As a result,\add* EsawВҰ12838 \add realisedВҰ12837\add* that his fatherВҰ12845 wasn't happy about the Canaanite girls
\v 9 so \add he\add* wentВҰ12847 to Yishma'el and he tookВҰ12852 MahalathВҰ12855 as an additional wife. She was the daughterВҰ12857 of Abraham'sВҰ12862 son Yishma'elВҰ12851, and was the sisterВҰ12863 of NevayotВҰ12864.
\s1 Yacob's vision at Beyt-El
\rem /s1 Jacob's Dream at Bethel
\p
\v 10 \add Meanwhile,\add* YacobВҰ12873 had left Be'er-Sheva and was enroute to HaranВҰ12877.
\v 11 \add OneВҰ12883 nightВҰ12881\add* after he'd stopped when the sun had gone down, he laid down inВҰ12880 that place andВҰ12879 used one of the stonesВҰ12888 thereВҰ12882 to put underВҰ12891 his head \add for a pillow\add*.
\v 12 \add While he was sleeping,\add* he had a dreamВҰ12896, and wow, a stairwayВҰ12898 was set up on the earth and its top reachedВҰ12902 to the heavensВҰ12903, and look, God's messengersВҰ12905 were ascending and descendingВҰ12908 on it.\x + \xo 28:12: \xt Yhn 1:51.\x*
\v 13 And look, Yahweh was standingВҰ12913 above it and he saidВҰ12915, вҖңI am Yahweh, the god of AbrahamВҰ12919 your grandfather and the god of Yitshak. I will giveВҰ12929 the land thatВҰ12924 you are lyingВҰ12926 on to you and to your descendantsВҰ12930\x + \xo 28:13: \xt Gen 13:14-15.\x*
\v 14 and \add they\add* will be \add as numerous as\add* dust \add particles\add*, and you'll \add all\add* spreadВҰ12936 out to the west and to the east and to the northВҰ12939 and to the southВҰ12940. And all the families of the earthВҰ12935 will be blessedВҰ12941 \add through\add* you and yourВҰ12947 offspringВҰ12947.\x + \xo 28:14: \xt Gen 12:3; 22:18.\x*
\v 15 \add SoВҰ12949\add* listen, I'm withВҰ12953 you andВҰ12949 I'll watch over you everywhere you goВҰ12956. I'll bringВҰ12957 you back to this land because I won'tВҰ12963 leaveВҰ12964 you untilВҰ12965 I've done what I told you.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ12976 YacobВҰ12977 woke up andВҰ12976 saidВҰ12979 \add to himself\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ12982 is certainly \add here\add* inВҰ12983 this placeВҰ12983, butВҰ12976 I didn'tВҰ12986 realiseВҰ12987 it.вҖқ
\v 17 SoВҰ12989 he was afraidВҰ12989 and saidВҰ12990 \add to himself\add*, вҖңThis placeВҰ12994 is spine-chillingвҖ”it's nothing other than God's houseВҰ13001, and it's heaven'sВҰ13005 gateway.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ13007 inВҰ13009 the morningВҰ13009 YacobВҰ13008 got up earlyВҰ13007, and he tookВҰ13010 the stoneВҰ13013 thatВҰ13014 he'd put underВҰ13017 his head and stood it up \add longways\add* as a pillarВҰ13020, and he pouredВҰ13021 oilВҰ13022 over the top of it.
\v 19 He named that placeВҰ13032 вҖҳBeyt-ElвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳGod's houseВҰ13034вҖҷ)\add*, even though that townВҰ13041 had been named LuzВҰ13038 before thenВҰ13027.
\v 20 ThenВҰ13044 YacobВҰ13045 made a promise \add to God\add*, saying, вҖңIf God will be withВҰ13054 me and watch over me on this road thatВҰ13056 I'm walking on, and give me bread to eatВҰ13063 and clothesВҰ13064 to wear,
\v 21 andВҰ13073 if I'm \add able to\add* returnВҰ13067 \add safely\add* to my father'sВҰ13072 home, thenВҰ13067 I'll make YahwehВҰ13074 my godВҰ13076,
\v 22 and this stoneВҰ13078 that I've stood up as a pillarВҰ13083 will be God's houseВҰ13085, and I'll give you a tenth of everything that you give to me.вҖқ
\c 29
\s1 Yacob's arrival at Lavan's
\rem /s1 Jacob Arrives in Paddan Aram; Jacob Arrives at Laban's Home; Jacob Meets Rachel; Jacob Arrives at Paddan-Aram
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ13096 YacobВҰ13097 \add got on the road again\add* andВҰ13096 wentВҰ13099 to the land of the easternВҰ13103 peoplesВҰ13101.
\v 2 \add CloseВҰ13118 to his destination,\add* he looked \add ahead\add*, and wow, there was a well in the countrysideВҰ13108, and what's more, threeВҰ13112 flocks of sheepВҰ13115 and goats were lyingВҰ13116 there near it, because the flocks were wateredВҰ13123 from that well \add butВҰ13105\add* the stoneВҰ13125 over the mouthВҰ13129 of the well was largeВҰ13126 \add and heavy\add*.
\v 3 \add Once\add* all the flocksВҰ13137 were gatheredВҰ13132 thereВҰ13134, thenВҰ13132 they would roll the stone from over the mouth of the well andВҰ13132 waterВҰ13145 the \add animals\add*. ThenВҰ13132 they would return the stone to its placeВҰ13157 over the mouth of the well.
\p
\v 4 \add SoВҰ13159\add* YacobВҰ13161 \add asked the farmers\add*, вҖңMy brothersВҰ13162, whereВҰ13163 are youВҰ13164 from?вҖқ
\p вҖңWe're from HaranВҰ13166,вҖқ theyВҰ13165 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 5 вҖңDo you know Nahor'sВҰ13177 grandson Lavan?вҖқ Yacob asked.
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* we know him,вҖқ they \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 6 вҖңIs he doing well?вҖқ Yacob asked.
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* he's fine,вҖқ they said, вҖңandВҰ13181 here comes his daughterВҰ13189 Rahel with \add their\add* flock.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңLook, it's stillВҰ13197 \add broad daylight\add*,вҖқ Yacob told them. вҖңIt's not timeВҰ13202 for the livestockВҰ13204 to be brought it. Water the flock, andВҰ13207 goВҰ13207 pastureВҰ13208 them.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңWeВҰ13220 can'tВҰ13211,вҖқ they saidВҰ13210, вҖңuntilВҰ13213 \em all\em* the flocksВҰ13218 are gatheredВҰ13215 \add here\add* andВҰ13210 they roll the stoneВҰ13222 off the \add top\add* of the well. ThenВҰ13210 weВҰ13212 will waterВҰ13226 the sheepВҰ13227.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 He was still talkingВҰ13230 with them when Rahel cameВҰ13234 with herВҰ13239 father'sВҰ13239 flock, because she was \add the one who looked after\add* them.
\v 10 WhenВҰ13244 YacobВҰ13247 saw Rahel (the daughterВҰ13251 of his mother's brother, Lavan) with Lavan's flock, \add he\add* went over and rolledВҰ13264 the stoneВҰ13267 \add off the top\add* of the well and wateredВҰ13271 the sheep and goats.
\v 11 ThenВҰ13279 \add he gave\add* Rahel \add a kiss\add* andВҰ13279 \add happily\add* cried \add out loud\add*.
\v 12 Then \add he\add* told Rahel that he was a relativeВҰ13292 of her father and that he was a son of RebekahВҰ13298.
\p Then she ran and told her father,
\v 13 and when Lavan heardВҰ13305 the newsВҰ13309 about his sister'sВҰ13314 son Yacob, he ranВҰ13315 \add out\add* to meet him. Then he embracedВҰ13317 him and kissedВҰ13320 him and broughtВҰ13323 him to his houseВҰ13326. Then \add Yacob\add* told Lavan \add everything that had happened up until thenВҰ13304\add*,
\v 14 and Lavan told him, вҖңYou are indeed \add a close relative\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Yacob marries Le'ah then Rahel
\rem /s1 Jacob Marries Laban's Daughters; Jacob Serves Laban for Rachel and Leah; Jacob Marries Leah and Rachel
\p After Yacob had stayed with Lavan and \add worked for him\add* for a whole monthВҰ13344,
\v 15 Lavan saidВҰ13347 to \add him\add*, вҖңShould you work for me for nothingВҰ13355 just becauseВҰ13350 you're my relative? Tell me, what \add should I pay you\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 Now Lavan had twoВҰ13363 daughtersВҰ13364: the older one was named Le'ah, andВҰ13368 the youngerВҰ13369 one was named Rahel (RachelВҰ13370).
\v 17 Le'ah had \add pretty\add* eyesВҰ13372, butВҰ13372 Rahel was \add extremely beautiful in every way\add*.
\p
\v 18 \add Now\add* YacobВҰ13384 \add was inВҰ13392 love withВҰ13392\add* Rahel, so he \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңI'll \add work for\add* youВҰ13389 \add for\add* sevenВҰ13390 yearsВҰ13391 \add so I can marry\add* yourВҰ13393 youngerВҰ13394 daughterВҰ13393 Rahel.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖң\add Okay,\add* stay with me \add thenВҰ13396\add*,вҖқ said Lavan. вҖңIt's better for me to give her to you than to give her to some other manВҰ13405.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ13410 YacobВҰ13411 \add worked\add* sevenВҰ13413 yearsВҰ13414 for RahelВҰ13412, butВҰ13410 \add it only seemed\add* like a few daysВҰ13417 \add to himВҰ13416\add* because of hisВҰ13416 loveВҰ13419 for her,
\v 21 thenВҰ13422 \add he\add* saidВҰ13422 to Lanan, вҖңGive me my wifeВҰ13430 \add to marry now\add* because \add I've worked the agreed seven years\add*.вҖқ
\v 22 \add SoВҰ13437\add* LavanВҰ13438 invited all the local peopleВҰ13443 andВҰ13445 held a wedding reception,
\v 23 butВҰ13448 that eveningВҰ13449 Lavan \add broughtВҰ13455\add* his \add other\add* daughterВҰ13454 Le'ah to \add Yacob\add*, andВҰ13448 he \add slept withВҰ13449\add* herВҰ13459.
\v 24 (Lavan also gaveВҰ13461 his female slave ZilpahВҰ13466 to Le'ah to be \add her personal\add* slave.)
\v 25 \add ButВҰ13472\add* inВҰ13473 the morningВҰ13473, \add Yacob saw\add* that wow, it was LeahВҰ13477! вҖң\add Hey,\add* what's this \add that\add* you've done to me?вҖқ Yacob \add demanded of\add* Lavan. вҖңWasn't it Rahel that I \add worked for\add* you for? SoВҰ13472 why did you deceiveВҰ13492 me?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңIt's not ourВҰ13500 custom here,вҖқ Lavan answered, вҖңfor the youngerВҰ13502 \add daughter\add* to marry before the older one.
\v 27 StayВҰ13513 withВҰ13516 \add just\add* this one for the \add marriage\add* weekВҰ13507, andВҰ13509 \add then\add* we'll also giveВҰ13509 youВҰ13518 the \add younger\add* one \add inВҰ13516 return for\add* anotherВҰ13524 sevenВҰ13521 year's work.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \add SoВҰ13526\add* YacobВҰ13527 agreed andВҰ13526 \add spent the weekВҰ13530 with Le'ah\add*, thenВҰ13526 \add Lavan also\add* gaveВҰ13532 him his daughterВҰ13538 Rahel to be his wife.
\v 29 (Lavan also gaveВҰ13542 his female slave BilhahВҰ13548 to Rahel to be \add her personal\add* slave.)
\p
\v 30 \add SoВҰ13553 Yacob\add* also \add slept with\add* Rahel, \add butВҰ13553\add* he also lovedВҰ13558 \add her\add* more than Le'ah. ThenВҰ13553 he \add worked for Lavan\add* for anotherВҰ13571 sevenВҰ13568 yearsВҰ13570.
\s1 Yacob's children
\rem /s1 The Children Born to Jacob; Jacob's Many Children; Jacob's Children
\p
\v 31 \add Now\add* YahwehВҰ13574 sawВҰ13573 that Le'ah was spurned, so he \add allowed herВҰ13582 to conceive\add*, butВҰ13573 Rahel was \add unable to get pregnant\add*.
\v 32 \add SoВҰ13586\add* LeahВҰ13587 \add got pregnantВҰ13586\add* and gaveВҰ13588 birthВҰ13588 to a son, and she named him вҖҳReubenВҰ13592вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳLook, a sonвҖҷ)\add* because she saidВҰ13594, вҖңBecause YahwehВҰ13598 has lookedВҰ13597 onВҰ13599 my misery, surely my husbandВҰ13603 will loveВҰ13602 me now.вҖқ
\v 33 ThenВҰ13605 she \add got pregnantВҰ13605\add* againВҰ13606 and \add gave birthВҰ13607 to a second\add* son, and she said, вҖңBecause YahwehВҰ13613 heardВҰ13612 that I am hatedВҰ13616, thenВҰ13605 he also gave me this son.вҖқ SoВҰ13605 she calledВҰ13626 his nameВҰ13627 вҖҳSimeonВҰ13628вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳhe hearsвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 34 ThenВҰ13630 she \add got pregnantВҰ13630\add* againВҰ13631 and \add gaveВҰ13632 birthВҰ13632 to a third\add* son, and she saidВҰ13634, вҖңThis timeВҰ13636 now my husbandВҰ13638 will hold me close to him, because I've \add given\add* him threeВҰ13644 sonsВҰ13645.вҖқ That's why she named \add the baby\add* вҖҳLeviВҰ13652вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳhold closeвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 35 Then \add Le'ah got pregnant\add* againВҰ13655 and \add gaveВҰ13656 birthВҰ13656 to a fourth\add* son, and she said, вҖңThis timeВҰ13659 I will praise YahwehВҰ13663.вҖқ That's why she named him вҖҳYehudahВҰ13669вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳpraiseвҖҷ)\add*. Then she stopped \add getting pregnant\add*.
\c 30
\p
\v 1 Now Rahel \add realisedВҰ13673\add* that she wasn't \add producing any\add* children for Yacob, so she enviedВҰ13679 herВҰ13681 sisterВҰ13681 \add Le'ah\add*, and she \add demanded from\add* Yacob, вҖңGive me children, and if \add you don'tВҰ13676\add*, I'll die!вҖқ
\p
\v 2 \add ButВҰ13696\add* Yacob'sВҰ13699 angerВҰ13698 \add flared up\add* against Rahel andВҰ13696 he \add asked\add*, вҖңAm I inВҰ13700 the placeВҰ13702 of GodВҰ13703 who's kept you \add from getting pregnant\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add Rahel answered\add*, вҖңListen, \add here's\add* my slave BilhahВҰ13716. \add Sleep with\add* her so that she'll \add have childrenВҰ13723 on my behalf\add* andВҰ13713 I'll also \add be able to have a family throughВҰ13727\add* her.вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ13729 she gaveВҰ13729 BilhahВҰ13734 to him as a \add slave\add* wife andВҰ13737 YacobВҰ13739 \add slept with\add* herВҰ13735,
\v 5 \add so\add* thenВҰ13741 BilhahВҰ13742 \add got pregnantВҰ13741\add* andВҰ13743 \add produced\add* a son for YacobВҰ13744.
\v 6 Rahel saidВҰ13747, вҖңGodВҰ13750 has vindicatedВҰ13749 me, and indeed he's listenedВҰ13752 to my \add request\add* and givenВҰ13754 me a son!вҖқ That's why she named him вҖҳDanВҰ13763вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳhe judged (inВҰ13753 my favour)вҖҷ)\add*.
\v 7 \add Later on,\add* Rahel's slave BilhahВҰ13768 \add got pregnantВҰ13765\add* againВҰ13766 andВҰ13767 \add gaveВҰ13767 birthВҰ13767 to\add* a secondВҰ13772 son for YacobВҰ13773
\v 8 \add so\add* Rahel saidВҰ13775, вҖңI've \add had a difficult battle\add* with my sisterВҰ13783 butВҰ13775 I've \add succeeded\add* in the end!вҖқ \add SoВҰ13775\add* she named \add the baby\add* вҖҳNaftaliВҰ13789вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳmy struggleвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add Now when\add* Le'ah \add noticedВҰ13791\add* that she \add wasn't getting pregnant any more\add*, she gaveВҰ13801 herВҰ13800 female slave ZilpahВҰ13799 to YacobВҰ13803 as a \add slave\add* wife.
\v 10 ThenВҰ13806 \add eventually\add* Le'ah'sВҰ13809 slave ZilpahВҰ13807 \add produced\add* a son for YacobВҰ13810,
\v 11 andВҰ13817 Le'ah saidВҰ13813, вҖңWhat good fortune!вҖқ SoВҰ13813 she named him вҖҳGadВҰ13821вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳfortunateвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 12 ThenВҰ13823 Le'ah'sВҰ13826 slave ZilpahВҰ13824 \add produced\add* a secondВҰ13828 son for YacobВҰ13829,
\v 13 andВҰ13837 Le'ah saidВҰ13831, вҖңHow blessed I am because women will call me blessed.вҖқ SoВҰ13831 she named him вҖҳAsherВҰ13841вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳblessedвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add One day during\add* the wheatВҰ13848 harvestВҰ13846, ReubenВҰ13844 wentВҰ13843 out and foundВҰ13849 \add some\add* mandrake \add plants\add*\f + \fr 30:14 \ft The mandrake plants were believed to increase fertility, but it's not clear from the text which part of the plant was used or how they were applied.\f* inВҰ13845 the countrysideВҰ13851 and broughtВҰ13852 them \add home\add* to Le'ah his motherВҰ13857. ThenВҰ13843 Rahel \add asked\add* Le'ah, вҖңPlease giveВҰ13863 me some of yourВҰ13868 son'sВҰ13868 mandrakes.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңIs it a smallВҰ13872 matter you have takenВҰ13873 my husbandВҰ13876?вҖқ Le'ah \add snapped back\add*. вҖңAnd would you also takeВҰ13877 my son's mandrakes?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Well,\add* he can \add sleep\add* with you tonight \add in exchange\add* for your son's mandrakes.вҖқ Rahel \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\v 16 \add So that\add* eveningВҰ13898 \add when\add* YacobВҰ13894 cameВҰ13893 \add home\add* from the countrysideВҰ13897, LeahВҰ13900 wentВҰ13899 out to meet him andВҰ13893 told \add him\add*, вҖңYou must comeВҰ13904 to me \add tonight\add* because I've hiredВҰ13907 you with my son'sВҰ13909 mandrakesВҰ13908.вҖқ So he \add sleptВҰ13910\add* with her that nightВҰ13912.
\p
\v 17 GodВҰ13916 listenedВҰ13915 to Le'ahВҰ13919 and she \add got pregnantВҰ13920\add* and \add produced\add* a fifthВҰ13924 son for YacobВҰ13922,
\v 18 saying, вҖңGodВҰ13929 has givenВҰ13928 me my reward because I gaveВҰ13933 my slave to my husbandВҰ13935 \add to sleep with\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ13926 she named him вҖҳYissakarвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳrewardвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ13940 Le'ahВҰ13942 \add got pregnantВҰ13940\add* againВҰ13941 andВҰ13943 \add produced\add* a sixthВҰ13946 son for YacobВҰ13947,
\v 20 saying, вҖңGodВҰ13953 has \add given\add* me a nice present. This timeВҰ13958 my husbandВҰ13960 will honour me because I have \add produced\add* sixВҰ13965 sonsВҰ13966 for him.вҖқ So she calledВҰ13967 his nameВҰ13970 вҖҳZebulunВҰ13971вҖҷ \add (which might mean вҖҳhonourвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 21 Later on, Le'ah had a daughterВҰ13975 andВҰ13976 named her DinahВҰ13980.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ13982 GodВҰ13983 \add paid attention\add* to RahelВҰ13986 and listenedВҰ13987 to her and \add enabled her to conceive\add*,
\v 23 \add so\add* she \add got pregnantВҰ13995\add* and produced a son, and saidВҰ13998, вҖңGodВҰ14001 has taken away my disgraceВҰ14003.вҖқ
\v 24 She named him вҖҳYosefВҰ14009вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳmay heВҰ14011 give anotherвҖҷ)\add*, saying, вҖңMay YahwehВҰ14012 add another son to me.вҖқ
\s1 Yacob prospers at Lavan's expense
\rem /s1 Jacob's Bargain with Laban; Jacob's Wealth Increases; Jacob's Flocks Increase; Jacob Prospers at Laban's Expense
\p
\v 25 \add Sometime\add* after Rahel had given birth to YosefВҰ14023, YacobВҰ14025 saidВҰ14024 to Lavan, вҖңSend me off \add now\add*, so that I can \add return\add* to my place andВҰ14017 to my land.
\v 26 \add Let me take\add* my wivesВҰ14039 that I worked for you for, and take my childrenВҰ14042 so that I can leave, because you yourself knowВҰ14050 \add how long and hard I've worked for\add* you.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add ButВҰ14057\add* Lavan \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңPlease stay, if I've foundВҰ14063 favourВҰ14064 inВҰ14065 yourВҰ14069 eyesВҰ14065 \add because\add* I've learntВҰ14066 by divinationВҰ14066 that YahwehВҰ14068 has blessedВҰ14067 me because of you.вҖқ
\v 28 ThenВҰ14071 he \add added\add*, вҖңTell me how much you \add want\add* andВҰ14075 I'll pay you that.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖңYou yourself knowВҰ14080 how \add well\add* I've servedВҰ14083 you andВҰ14077 how your livestockВҰ14088 have \add prospered\add* with me.вҖқ Yacob \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 30 \add Before I came, you didn't have much, butВҰ14098 now you have plenty because\add* YahwehВҰ14101 has blessedВҰ14100 you \add wherever I was involved\add*. ButВҰ14098 now, when will I also do something for my \add own\add* householdВҰ14110?вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖңWhat should I give you?вҖқ Lavan \add asked\add*.
\p вҖңYou don'tВҰ14119 have to \em give\em* me anythingВҰ14124,вҖқ YacobВҰ14118 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңIf you'll do this \add one\add* thingВҰ14130 for me, I'll continue \add taking care of\add* your flocksВҰ14134:
\v 32 Let me look through all yourВҰ14140 flocksВҰ14140 today and separate out from them all the lambsВҰ14155 that are speckled, spotted, or dark-coloured, and all the young goatsВҰ14158 that are spotted or speckled. They will be my pay.
\v 33 \add SoВҰ14162\add* in the futureВҰ14167, you'll be able to see that I've been honestВҰ14165 because you'll be able to see it for yourself: any goat that's not speckledВҰ14179 and spottedВҰ14180, and any sheep that's not dark-coloured, if it's in my flock thenВҰ14162 it must have been stolenВҰ14184.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖңOkay thenВҰ14188, let's \add do it yourВҰ14193 way\add*.вҖқ Lavan \add agreed\add*.
\v 35 \add ButВҰ14195\add* that \add very\add* dayВҰ14196, he removedВҰ14195 the male goats that were streakedВҰ14201 and spotted, and all the femaleВҰ14206 goats that were speckledВҰ14207 and spotted, any that had whiteВҰ14212 onВҰ14217 it, and all the dark-coloured ones among the lambsВҰ14217. ThenВҰ14195 he gave them to his sons \add to look after\add*,
\v 36 andВҰ14223 \add they took them\add* a three-dayВҰ14225 journeyВҰ14224 \add away from where\add* Yacob \add was\add*, \add so\add* Yacob was \add left just\add* tending \em the rest\em* of Lavan's flocksВҰ14234.
\p
\v 37 ThenВҰ14238 YacobВҰ14241 \add got some\add* freshlyВҰ14244 cut branches of poplarВҰ14243 and almondВҰ14245 and planeВҰ14246 treesВҰ14246, and peeledВҰ14248 white stripesВҰ14250 inВҰ14249 them \add by\add* exposing the white thatВҰ14254 was inside the branches.
\v 38 ThenВҰ14260 he put the branchesВҰ14262 thatВҰ14263 he had peeled inВҰ14265 the waterВҰ14267 troughsВҰ14265 where the flocks \add would see them when they\add* came to drink, andВҰ14259 they mated when they came to drink.
\v 39 \add Thus\add* the flocks would mate by the \add stripedВҰ14285\add* branchesВҰ14282, and \add they\add* would bear young who were streaked, speckledВҰ14286, and spottedВҰ14287.
\p
\v 40 ThenВҰ14289 YacobВҰ14291 \add separated out those young animals into a separate flock\add*, and he made the \add older\add* flocks look atВҰ14301 the streaked and all the dark-coloured animals inВҰ14301 Lavan's flocks. \add SoВҰ14289\add* he kept his own flocks by themselves and didn'tВҰ14308 \add mix\add* them withВҰ14301 Lavan's flocks.
\p
\v 41 SoВҰ14315 whenever the strongВҰ14320 animals were \add ready to mate\add*, thenВҰ14315 YacobВҰ14322 put the branches in the troughsВҰ14328 \add in front\add* of the flocks so that they would mate by the branches,
\v 42 \add butВҰ14332\add* when the animals were weak, he didn'tВҰ14334 put them inВҰ14332. SoВҰ14332 the weak animals went to LavanВҰ14338 andВҰ14332 the strongВҰ14339 ones to YacobВҰ14340
\v 43 so he \add becameВҰ14342 very wealthyВҰ14342\add*, and he owned large flocks \add as well as\add* male and femaleВҰ14351 slaves, and camelsВҰ14353 and donkeysВҰ14354.
\c 31
\s1 Yacob flees from Lavan
\rem /s1 Jacob Flees from Laban; Jacob Flees with Family and Flocks
\p
\v 1 \add One day, Yacob\add* overheard the wordsВҰ14359 of Lavan's sons who were saying, вҖңYacob has takenВҰ14364 everything that belonged to our father, andВҰ14356 from what \add originally\add* belonged to our father he has gained all this wealthВҰ14377.вҖқ
\v 2 ThenВҰ14380 YacobВҰ14381 \add also noticedВҰ14380\add* that Lavan'sВҰ14385 \add attitude towards him had changed\add*, andВҰ14386 he wasn't \add in favour of him like he'd been in the past\add*.
\v 3 ThenВҰ14392 YahwehВҰ14393 \add вүҲtold\add* YacobВҰ14396, вҖңGo back to the land of your ancestorsВҰ14401 and to your relatives, and I'll be with youВҰ14404.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add SoВҰ14406\add* YacobВҰ14407 sentВҰ14406 for Rahel andВҰ14406 Le'ah to \add come to him out in\add* the countrysideВҰ14411 \add where he was with\add* his flocksВҰ14414
\v 5 and he told them, вҖңI'veВҰ14419 \add noticed\add* your father's \add attitude\add* and that he's not \add positive\add* toward me \add like he was a few daysВҰ14429\add* ago, butВҰ14416 my father's godВҰ14430 has been with me.
\v 6 You \add both\add* knowВҰ14436 that I've servedВҰ14441 yourВҰ14444 fatherВҰ14444 with all my strengthВҰ14440,
\v 7 \add butВҰ14446\add* yourВҰ14446 fatherВҰ14446 has deceivedВҰ14447 me andВҰ14446 changedВҰ14449 my wagesВҰ14452 tenВҰ14453 timesВҰ14454. HoweverВҰ14450, GodВҰ14458 hasn't allowedВҰ14457 himВҰ14457 to harm me.
\v 8 \add When he told me\add*: вҖҳThe speckled animals will be your wages,вҖҷ then all the flocks bore speckled young. ButВҰ14469 when he \add вүҲtold me\add*: вҖҳThe streaked ones will be your wages,вҖҷ then all the flocks bore streaked young.
\v 9 \add InВҰ14489 that way,\add* GodВҰ14488 took yourВҰ14492 father'sВҰ14492 animals away from him andВҰ14493 gaveВҰ14493 them to me.
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add One day during\add* the season when the flocks were \add matingВҰ14507\add*, I \add looked up\add* and sawВҰ14503 inВҰ14498 a dreamВҰ14504 that, wow, the maleВҰ14506 goatsВҰ14506 that were mounting the flocks were streaked, speckledВҰ14512, and spotted.
\v 11 ThenВҰ14515 God's messengerВҰ14517 said to me inВҰ14519 the dreamВҰ14519, вҖҳYacobВҰ14520!вҖҷ andВҰ14515 I said, вҖҳ\add I'm listening\add*.вҖҷ
\v 12 ThenВҰ14524 he \add вүҲtold me\add*, вҖҳPlease \add look up\add* and \add observe that\add* all the maleВҰ14532 goatsВҰ14532 that are mounting the flocksВҰ14536 are streaked, speckledВҰ14538, and spotted, because I have seenВҰ14541 everything that Lavan is doingВҰ14547 to you.
\v 13 I'm the godВҰ14551 of Beyt-El, where you anointedВҰ14556 a pillarВҰ14558вҖ”where you vowedВҰ14560 a vow to me. Now \add pack\add* up and depart from this land, and returnВҰ14571 to the land where you were born.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 31:13: \xt Gen 28:18-22.\x*
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ14577 Rahel andВҰ14577 Le'ah replied, вҖң\add Yes,\add* we're not expecting any portion or inheritanceВҰ14585 from ourВҰ14587 father'sВҰ14587 \add property\add*.
\v 15 Doesn't he just \add treat\add* us like foreignersВҰ14590 \add now\add*? \add Yes,\add* he sold us andВҰ14595 then he \add frittered away all the moneyВҰ14601 that should have been\add* ours,
\v 16 so all the wealthВҰ14606 that God took from our fatherВҰ14610 \add belonged\add* to us and to our childrenВҰ14613 \add anyway\add*. So \add yes\add*, \add go ahead and\add* do everything that God's told youВҰ14619 \add to do\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ14622 YacobВҰ14623 \add packed\add* up and put his wivesВҰ14630 and childrenВҰ14627 on the camelsВҰ14633.
\v 18 ThenВҰ14635 he droveВҰ14635 all his livestock andВҰ14635 all his propertyВҰ14645 that he had acquiredвҖ”the livestock in his possessionВҰ14649 that he had acquired in PaddanВҰ14652-AramвҖ”to goВҰ14654 \add back\add* to IsaacВҰ14657 his fatherВҰ14658 in the CanaanВҰ14660 regionВҰ14659.
\v 19 \add Now\add* Lavan had gone \add off for several days\add* to shearВҰ14664 his sheepВҰ14667, so Rahel stoleВҰ14668 the idols thatВҰ14673 belongedВҰ14674 to herВҰ14674 fatherВҰ14674,
\v 20 andВҰ14676 YacobВҰ14677 \add deceived\add* LavanВҰ14681 (the SyrianВҰ14682) by not telling him that \add they all\add* were leaving.
\v 21 \add SoВҰ14692\add* Yacob \add took his household\add* and everything that belonged to \add them\add* and crossed the \add Euphrates\add* River and \add headed upward\add* toward the hill-country of GileadВҰ14709.
\s1 Lavan catches up to Yacob
\rem /s1 Laban Overtakes Jacob; Laban Pursues Jacob
\p
\v 22 Three days later, Lavan was \add informed\add* that YacobВҰ14717 had fled \add with his family\add*,
\v 23 \add so\add* he tookВҰ14719 \add some of\add* his relatives withВҰ14731 himВҰ14725 and chased afterВҰ14725 Yacob \add and his family\add* for sevenВҰ14727 daysВҰ14728 until they overtook \add them\add* inВҰ14731 the hill-country of GileadВҰ14732.
\v 24 \add ButВҰ14734\add* that nightВҰ14741 GodВҰ14735 \add appeared\add* to Lavan the SyrianВҰ14739 inВҰ14740 a dreamВҰ14740 andВҰ14742 told him, вҖңWatch yourselfВҰ14745 that youВҰ14748 don't \add say anything to\add* YacobВҰ14751, either goodВҰ14752 or badВҰ14755.вҖқ
\v 25 \add WhenВҰ14757\add* Lavan had caught up to Yacob, Yacob had pitched \add their\add* tents inВҰ14767 the hills, so Lavan withВҰ14767 his relatives \add also\add* pitched theirs onВҰ14767 the GileadВҰ14774 hills.
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ14776 Lavan saidВҰ14776 to YacobВҰ14778, вҖңWhat have youВҰ14780 done? \add You've deceivedВҰ14781 me\add* andВҰ14776 carriedВҰ14785 away myВҰ14784 daughtersВҰ14788 like \add prisoners of war\add*.
\v 27 Why did you flee secretly and deceiveВҰ14795 me and not tell me? I would have sentВҰ14801 you \add all off\add* withВҰ14802 \add music and singing and a cheery party\add*.
\v 28 You didn'tВҰ14807 let me kissВҰ14809 my grandchildren \add goodbye\add* andВҰ14811 my daughtersВҰ14811, \add instead youВҰ14813 made a foolishВҰ14813 decision\add*.
\v 29 \add I have the right andВҰ14823 the ability to punish\add* youВҰ14821, butВҰ14823 last nightВҰ14825 yourВҰ14824 father'sВҰ14824 godВҰ14823 told me, вҖҳ\add Be careful not to\add* speak either goodВҰ14836 or badВҰ14839 to YacobВҰ14835.вҖҷ
\v 30 \add SoВҰ14841\add* now, you probably left because you miss your father's place badly, \add butВҰ14841\add* why did you stealВҰ14851 my godsВҰ14854?вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖң\add We left like that,\add*вҖқ YacobВҰ14857 answeredВҰ14856 Lavan, вҖңbecause I was afraidВҰ14861, because I said that perhaps you would \add use force to take\add* your \add married\add* daughtersВҰ14869 from me.
\v 32 \add As for your idols,\add* whoever you find your godsВҰ14877 with will \add be put to death\add*. Look through everything we have and takeВҰ14887 \add back anything that\add* belongs to you, with our relatives \add as witnesses\add*.вҖқ (Now YacobВҰ14893 didn'tВҰ14878 know that Rahel had stolenВҰ14896 them.)
\p
\v 33 \add SoВҰ14898\add* Lavan \add inspected\add* Yacob'sВҰ14901 and Le'ah's tents, and the tent of the two slave women, butВҰ14898 he didn'tВҰ14908 find anything. ThenВҰ14898 he came out of Le'ah's tent and went into Rahel's tent.
\v 34 Now Rahel had takenВҰ14918 the idols andВҰ14917 put them inВҰ14923 the camel'sВҰ14924 saddleВҰ14923 \add which she was now\add* sitting onВҰ14923, \add so although\add* Lavan searchedВҰ14927 throughout \add her\add* entireВҰ14931 tent, he didn'tВҰ14934 find them,
\v 35 andВҰ14937 she saidВҰ14937 to herВҰ14940 fatherВҰ14940, вҖңDon't let my masterВҰ14945 \add be upset\add* that I'm not able to stand up in yourВҰ14950 presenceВҰ14950, because \add I have the regular female concern at the moment\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ14937 he searchedВҰ14956, butВҰ14937 he didn'tВҰ14941 find the idols.
\p
\v 36 \add SoВҰ14963\add* YacobВҰ14964 \add got very angry\add* andВҰ14963 he argued withВҰ14966 Lavan, demanding from \add him\add*, вҖңWhat's my crime? What's my sinВҰ14975, that you've hotlyВҰ14977 chased afterВҰ14978 me?
\v 37 Since you've searchedВҰ14982 through all \add ourВҰ15002\add* things, what things from \em your\em* houseВҰ14994 have you found? Put it here in front of my relatives and your relatives, and let them judge betweenВҰ15001 the two of us!
\p
\v 38 вҖңI've \add worked\add* for youВҰ15008 for twentyВҰ15005 years. Your ewes and your femaleВҰ15010 goatsВҰ15010 didn'tВҰ15011 miscarryВҰ15012, and I haven't eatenВҰ15016 rams from your flocksВҰ15014.
\v 39 I didn'tВҰ15019 bring \add dead sheep or goats\add* to youВҰ15022 \add that had been attacked by wild animalsВҰ15018\add*вҖ”I bore the loss of \add those\add* myself. You requiredВҰ15026 \add that I cover anything\add* stolen during the dayВҰ15028 or during the nightВҰ15030.
\v 40 I was \add always out there\add*вҖ”during the dayВҰ15033 the heat \add tormented\add* me, and atВҰ15033 nightВҰ15037 the frost \add so bad that I couldn't sleepВҰ15039\add*.
\v 41 That's how it was for me for twentyВҰ15045 years inВҰ15047 your houseВҰ15047. I \add worked for you for\add* fourteen years for your two daughtersВҰ15054, then six \add more\add* years for your flocksВҰ15057, and you changedВҰ15058 my wagesВҰ15061 ten timesВҰ15063 \add to your advantage\add*.
\v 42 If my father'sВҰ15067 godвҖ”the god of AbrahamВҰ15069 and the one Yitshak respectedвҖ”had not been with me, surely you would have sentВҰ15077 me away empty-handedВҰ15076 now. GodВҰ15066 has seenВҰ15086 my suffering and \add my hard work\add*, and last nightВҰ15089, he rebukedВҰ15088 you.вҖқ
\s1 Yacob and Lavan make a treaty
\rem /s1 Jacob's Treaty with Laban; Laban and Jacob Make a Covenant; The Agreement between Jacob and Laban
\p
\v 43 ThenВҰ15091 Lavan respondedВҰ15093 and told YacobВҰ15096, вҖң\add These women\add* are my daughters, and the children are my grandchildren, and the flocks are my flocks. Everything that you see \add here\add* belongs to me. ButВҰ15091 what can I do today about theseВҰ15115 daughters of mine or about theirВҰ15118 children that they gave birth to?
\v 44 \add SoВҰ15122\add* comeВҰ15123 now, let's make an agreement, IВҰ15126 and you, and let itВҰ15128 be a witnessВҰ15129 between me and you.вҖқ
\p
\v 45 SoВҰ15133 YacobВҰ15134 tookВҰ15133 a stoneВҰ15135 andВҰ15133 \add stood it up longways\add* as a pillarВҰ15137,
\v 46 then \add he instructed\add* his relatives, вҖңGatherВҰ15140 stones.вҖқ SoВҰ15139 they \add fetched\add* stones andВҰ15139 made a pile, then they ate thereВҰ15150 by the pile.
\v 47 Lavan gave the pile \add the Aramaic name\add* вҖҳYegarВҰ15159 SahaduthaВҰ15160вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳpile that remindsвҖҷ)\add* while YacobВҰ15161 gave it \add the Hebrew name\add* вҖҳGale'edвҖҷ \add (which has the same meaning)\add*.
\p
\v 48 ThenВҰ15166 Lavan saidВҰ15166, вҖңThis pile is a witnessВҰ15170 \add of the agreement\add* between me andВҰ15166 you today.вҖқ (That's why he'd named it GaleedВҰ15181.)
\v 49 It's also \add named\add* вҖҳMitspahВҰ15183вҖҷ \add (whichВҰ15184 means вҖҳwatchtowerвҖҷ)\add*, because he saidВҰ15185, вҖңMay YahwehВҰ15187 watchВҰ15186 between me andВҰ15189 you when we are hiddenВҰ15191 one from the otherВҰ15193.
\v 50 IfВҰ15198 you \add mistreatВҰ15197\add* my daughters, or if you take \add other\add* wivesВҰ15204 besides my daughters, even though there's not someone \add there to see it\add*, listen, GodВҰ15212 \add will be\add* a witnessВҰ15213 between me and you.вҖқ
\v 51 ThenВҰ15217 Lavan saidВҰ15217 to YacobВҰ15219, вҖңLook at this pile \add of stones\add*, and look at the pillarВҰ15225 whichВҰ15227 I set up between me and youВҰ15230.
\v 52 This pile is a witness and the pillar is a witness that I won't go past these to you, and that you won't go past these to me to do harm.
\v 53 May Abraham'sВҰ15266 godВҰ15265 and the gods of theirВҰ15272 ancestor NahorВҰ15268 judgeВҰ15269 betweenВҰ15270 us.вҖқ Then YacobВҰ15274 sworeВҰ15273 by the one respected by his father Yitshak,
\v 54 and YacobВҰ15280 offered a sacrificeВҰ15279 on the hill. ThenВҰ15279 he calledВҰ15283 his relatives to eatВҰ15285 bread and they ateВҰ15288 bread and spentВҰ15290 the nightВҰ15290 on the hill.
\v 55 In the morning, Lavan got up early and \add gave\add* his grandchildren and his daughters \add a kiss\add*, and he blessed them. Then \add he\add* left and returned to his place.
\c 32
\s1 Yacob encounters God's messengers
\rem /s1 Jacob Prepares to Meet Esau; Jacob Sends Gifts to Esau
\p
\v 1 Then Yacob \add continued onВҰ15296\add* his way \add withВҰ15296 his family and flocks\add*, and \add some\add* of God's messengers met him
\v 2 and when he saw them, YacobВҰ15308 said, вҖңThis \add must be\add* God's army camp.вҖқ So he named that place вҖҳMahanaimвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳtwo campsвҖҷ)\add*.
\s1 Yacob sends gifts ahead for Esaw
\rem /s1 Jacob Sends Presents to Appease Esau
\p
\v 3 Then YacobВҰ15319 sent messengers ahead of him to his brother Esaw in the Se'ir region in the country of Edom,
\v 4 instructing them, вҖңThis is what you'll say to my master, to EsawВҰ15340: вҖҳThis is what your servant YacobВҰ15335 says, вҖңI have been staying with \add Uncle\add* Lavan and have remained there until now.
\v 5 \add Now\add* I have cattle and donkeys, flocks, and male and female slaves. And I've sent \add these messengers\add* to speak with my masterВҰ15353, so that I'll find favour in yourВҰ15357 eyes.вҖқ вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add In due course\add* the messengers returned to Yacob, saying, вҖңWe went to yourВҰ15383 brother Esaw and \add now\add* he's coming to meet you along withВҰ15383 his four hundred men!вҖқ
\v 7 \add ThisВҰ15398 made\add* YacobВҰ15390 very scared and distressed, so he divided the people who were with him and the flocks and the herds and the camels into two groups,
\v 8 \add reasoning\add*, вҖңIf Esaw comes and attacks one camp, then the camp that's left can escape.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Then \add he prayed\add*, вҖңYahweh, God of my grandfather Abraham, and God of my father Yitshak, who saidВҰ15432 to me, вҖҳReturn to your land and to your relatives, and I will cause things to prosper with you,вҖҷ
\v 10 I'm unworthy of all the kindnesses and of all the faithfulness that youВҰ15463 have shown \add me\add* your slave, because I crossed this Yordan \add River\add* with \add only\add* my staff, butВҰ15448 now I've become two camps.
\v 11 Please save me from my brother Esaw, because I'm afraid thatВҰ15472 he'll come and attack me and the mothers withВҰ15478 the children.
\v 12 ButВҰ15504 you said,\x + \xo 32:12: \xt Gen 22:17.\x* вҖҳI will surely cause things to prosper with you, and I'll make your descendants as \add numerous as\add* the sand \add grains on the beach\add* which are too many to be counted.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 13 Then he stayed there for thatВҰ15522 night and he \add selected\add* gifts for his brother Esaw from what he had with him:
\v 14 two hundred female and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,
\v 15 thirty milk camels with their young, forty cows and ten bulls, and twenty femaleВҰ15543 and ten male donkeys.
\v 16 Then he \add handed them over\add* to his slaves, each herd by itself, and he \add вүҲtold them\add*, вҖңGo ahead of me \add one by one\add*, and \add keep a\add* space between each herd.вҖқ
\v 17 And he instructed the first one, saying, вҖңWhen Esaw my brother meets you and asks you, saying, вҖҳWho do you belong to, and where are you going? And who do those animals belong to?вҖҷ
\v 18 then you \add should answer\add*, вҖҳThey belong to yourВҰ15609 servant Yacob. They are a gift sent to my master EsawВҰ15597. \add In fact, he's coming along\add* behind us.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 19 Then \add YacobВҰ15614\add* also instructed the second and third slaves, as well as everyone who followed behindВҰ15624 the herds, \add telling them\add*, вҖңSay the same thing to EsawВҰ15619 when you find him,
\v 20 and also say, вҖҳLook, your servant Yacob is behindВҰ15642 us.вҖҷ вҖқ \add Yacob was thinking\add*, вҖңI'll \add cheer him up\add* withВҰ15651 the gifts that are going ahead of me, and after that, when I see \add him inВҰ15651 person\add*, perhaps he'll \add accept me\add*.вҖқ
\v 21 \add So\add* the gifts went aheadВҰ15668 of him, and he himself stayed inВҰ15666 the camp for that night.
\s1 Yacob gets renamed after fighting at Penu'el
\rem /s1 Jacob Wrestles With God; Jacob Wrestles with God; Jacob Wrestles at Peniel
\p
\v 22 Then during that night, \add Yacob\add* got up and took his two wives and \add their\add* two female slaves and his eleven sons and crossed over the ford of the Yabbok \add Stream\add*.
\v 23 \add AfterВҰ15713\add* crossingВҰ15710 the stream, he \add also\add* sent across \add everything else that\add* belonged to him.
\v 24 Then Yacob was left alone, and a man wrestled with him until dawn.\x + \xo 32:24-26: \xt Hos 12:3-4.\x*
\v 25 \add When the manВҰ15734 realised\add* he wasn't gaining on him, he touched \add YacobВҰ15731\add* on the socket of his hip so that it became dislocated as \add they\add* wrestledВҰ15733 with \add each other\add*.
\v 26 Then \add the man\add* said, вҖңRelease me \add now\add*, because it's \add already\add* dawning.вҖқ
\p вҖңI won'tВҰ15743 release you until you bless me,вҖқ YacobВҰ15754 \add вүҲresponded\add*.
\p
\v 27 вҖңWhat's your name?вҖқ the man \add asked\add*.
\p вҖңYacob,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 28 вҖңYou won't be called YacobВҰ15779 anymore,вҖқ the man said, вҖңbutВҰ15773 \add you'll be\add* вҖҳYisra'elвҖҷ \add (or вҖҳIsraelвҖҷ, which means вҖҳhe struggled with GodвҖҷ)\add*, because you have struggled with God and with men, and you won.вҖқ\x + \xo 32:28: \xt Gen 35:10.\x*
\p
\v 29 вҖңPlease tell \add me\add* \em your\em* name,вҖқ YacobВҰ15784 \add requested\add*.\x + \xo 32:29: \xt Jdg 13:17-18.\x*
\p вҖңWhy \add would you want to know\add* my name?вҖқ \add the man replied\add*, then he blessed Yacob there.
\p
\v 30 \add So\add* YacobВҰ15805 named the place вҖҳPenu'elвҖҷ \add (also spelt вҖҳPeni'elвҖҷ, which means вҖҳGod's faceвҖҷ)\add*, because he said, вҖңI saw God face to face, yet my life was preserved.вҖқ
\v 31 And the sun rose above him as he passed through Penu'el, and he was limping because of his hip.
\v 32 That's why Israelis don't eat the muscle of the tendon that is on the hip socket to this day, because \add the man\add* touched the socket of Yacob's hip on the muscle of the tendon.
\c 33
\s1 Esaw and Yacob meet peacefully
\rem /s1 Jacob and Esau Meet; Jacob Meets Esau; Jacob and Esau Make Peace
\p
\v 1 Then Yacob \add raised his head\add* and looked \add ahead\add*, and wow, EsawВҰ15889 was comingВҰ15890 \add towards himВҰ15891\add* along with \add his\add* fourВҰ15892 hundredВҰ15893 men. Then \add Yacob quickly\add* dividedВҰ15895 the children among Le'ah and Rahel and \add their\add* twoВҰ15906 female slaves,
\v 2 and he put the slave women and theirВҰ15915 children firstВҰ15916, and thenВҰ15909 Le'ah and herВҰ15920 children after them, and \add finally\add* Rahel and YosefВҰ15927 after them.
\v 3 ThenВҰ15930 he himself wentВҰ15939 aheadВҰ15932 of them, andВҰ15930 he bowedВҰ15933 to the ground sevenВҰ15935 timesВҰ15936 as he approached his brother.
\v 4 \add ButВҰ15944\add* EsawВҰ15945 ranВҰ15944 \add forward\add* to meet him and embracedВҰ15947 him and \add threw his arms around\add* his neck and kissedВҰ15953 him, and they \add both\add* cried \add together\add*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ15957 \add Esaw looked up\add* and sawВҰ15961 the womenВҰ15964 and the children, and \add asked\add*, вҖңWho are theseВҰ15971 \add others\add* with youВҰ15972?вҖқ
\p вҖңThe children that GodВҰ15978 has graciously given to yourВҰ15981 servantВҰ15981,вҖқ Yacob replied.
\v 6 ThenВҰ15983 the \add two\add* female slaves approached with theirВҰ15986 childrenВҰ15986, andВҰ15983 theyВҰ15985 bowedВҰ15987 down.
\v 7 \add Next\add* Le'ah also approached with herВҰ15993 childrenВҰ15993, and they bowed down. ThenВҰ15989 afterВҰ15995 that, YosefВҰ15997 and Rahel approached, and they bowed down.
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ16001 \add Esaw asked\add*, вҖңWhat were all these groups thatВҰ16008 I met?вҖқ
\p вҖңTo \add win\add* my master'sВҰ16015 favourВҰ16013,вҖқ Yacob \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 9 вҖңI've got plenty, my brotherВҰ16023,вҖқ saidВҰ16017 EsawВҰ16018. вҖң\add Keep\add* what belongsВҰ16024 to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңNo, please,вҖқ YacobВҰ16031 \add insisted\add*. вҖңIf I've \add won\add* your favour, thenВҰ16030 take my gifts. Because indeed, I've seen you face-to-face, which is like seeingВҰ16050 God's face, andВҰ16030 you've receivedВҰ16053 me \add favourably\add*.
\v 11 Please take my \add gifts\add* thatВҰ16061 were broughtВҰ16062 to you, becauseВҰ16068 GodВҰ16067 has been graciousВҰ16066 to me and I have \add way more than I need\add*.вҖқ
\p And he urgedВҰ16074 him, so \add Esaw\add* tookВҰ16077 it
\v 12 and said, вҖң\add Okay,\add* let's get moving and go, and I'll go ahead of you.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ButВҰ16085 \add Yacob replied\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ16087 knows that the children are tender plus I have flocks andВҰ16085 herdsВҰ16094 \add with young animals\add*. If theyВҰ16097 driveВҰ16097 them \add harder today\add*, thenВҰ16085 all the flocks will dieВҰ16100.
\v 14 Please let my master go on before his servantВҰ16110, and I'll lead them on at my gentle paceвҖ”at the pace of the livestockВҰ16116 thatВҰ16117 are ahead of me and at the pace of the childrenвҖ”untilВҰ16122 I come to my master's \add place\add* in Se'ir.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖң\add At least\add* let me leave some of my men with you \add all\add*,вҖқ said EsawВҰ16132.
\p вҖңWhy do thatВҰ16140?вҖқ \add contradicted Yacob\add*. вҖңMay my masterВҰ16149 \add allow me to decide\add*.вҖқ
\v 16 \add SoВҰ16151\add* EsawВҰ16154 \add andВҰ16151 his men\add* started heading \add home\add* to Se'irВҰ16156,
\v 17 \add butВҰ16158\add* Yacob travelled to Succot \add where he\add* builtВҰ16161 a houseВҰ16163 for himself andВҰ16158 made shelters for his livestockВҰ16164. That's why he named the placeВҰ16173 вҖҳSuccotвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳsheltersвҖҷ)\add*.
\s1 Yacob begins to settle at Shekem
\rem /s1 Jacob Reaches Shechem
\p
\v 18 Then YacobВҰ16178, having come from PaddanВҰ16186-Aram, arrived peacefully atВҰ16185 the city of ShekemВҰ16181 inВҰ16185 the CanaanВҰ16184 regionВҰ16183, and he campedВҰ16188 \add outside\add* the city.
\v 19 \add InВҰ16195 due course,\add* he boughtВҰ16194 the portionВҰ16197 of the fieldВҰ16198 whereВҰ16199 he'd pitchedВҰ16200 his tents from the sonsВҰ16205 of HamorВҰ16207, the fatherВҰ16208 of ShekemВҰ16209, for a hundredВҰ16210 \add piecesВҰ16211 of silver\add*.\x + \xo 33:19: \xt Josh 24:32; Yhn 4:5.\x*
\v 20 He set up an altarВҰ16216 thereВҰ16215 andВҰ16213 he named it вҖҳElВҰ16220 EloheВҰ16221 Yisra'elвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳGod, the god of Yisra'elвҖҷ)\add*.
\c 34
\s1 Dinah's rape leads to a plan
\rem /s1 The Rape of Dinah; Dinah and the Shechemites; Revenge against Shechem
\p
\v 1 \add One day,\add* YacobВҰ16232 and Le'ah's daughterВҰ16227 DinahВҰ16226, wentВҰ16225 out to \add visit some of\add* the \add local womenВҰ16234\add*,
\v 2 \add butВҰ16237\add* ShekemВҰ16239, the son of HamorВҰ16242 the HiviteВҰ16243, the ruler of the land, sawВҰ16237 her and he \add grabbed\add* her and \add rapedВҰ16250\add* her.
\v 3 \add ShekemВҰ16257 admired DinahВҰ16254 so much that he fell inВҰ16254 love withВҰ16254 her\add* andВҰ16252 spokeВҰ16262 \add sweetly to her to try to cultivate a relationship\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ16268 \add he asked\add* HamorВҰ16272 his fatherВҰ16273, вҖңGetВҰ16269 this girlВҰ16280 for me as a wife.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add WhenВҰ16284\add* Yacob heardВҰ16285 that \add Shekem\add* had dishonoured his daughterВҰ16291 DinahВҰ16290, his sonsВҰ16292 were \add out\add* in the countrysideВҰ16297 with his livestockВҰ16296, so Yacob \add waited quietly\add* untilВҰ16300 they \add got home\add*.
\v 6 \add Meanwhile\add* Shekem's fatherВҰ16306 HamorВҰ16305 \add took Shekem\add* to \add negotiate\add* with YacobВҰ16311.
\v 7 \add In due course\add* Yacob's sonsВҰ16315 cameВҰ16317 \add home\add* from the countrysideВҰ16320. WhenВҰ16315 they heardВҰ16321 \add what had happened\add*, thenВҰ16315 theyВҰ16323 were \add very angry andВҰ16315 upset\add*, because \add Shekem\add* had done something disgracefulВҰ16329 to Yisra'el by \add taking advantage of\add* Yacob's daughterВҰ16335. \add Something like that should never have happened\add*.
\v 8 \add ButВҰ16342\add* HamorВҰ16343 spokeВҰ16342 with them, saying, вҖңMy son ShekemВҰ16346 my son \add is madly inВҰ16350 love with\add* yourВҰ16350 daughterВҰ16350. Please giveВҰ16351 her to him as a wife.
\v 9 \add In fact, why don't you allow us to marry\add* your daughters, andВҰ16357 you \add people could have\add* our daughters \add to marry\add*,
\v 10 thenВҰ16369 you could settle \add here permanently\add* with us. \add This region would open up to you all so\add* settle inВҰ16377 it and tradeВҰ16375 \add with us\add* and \add you could\add* buy \add more land around here\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ16379 ShekemВҰ16380 spoke to \add Dinah's\add* fatherВҰ16383 and brothersВҰ16387, вҖң\add Look kindly onВҰ16391 my request\add* and I'll giveВҰ16395 \add whatever youВҰ16393 ask for\add*.
\v 12 \add Set any very high amount for\add* the bride-priceВҰ16400 and gifts \add from\add* me, and I'll give \add whatever you ask\add*вҖ”\add just\add* give the young womanВҰ16412 to me as a wife.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add ButВҰ16414 because\add* Shekem had \add abused\add* theirВҰ16431 sisterВҰ16431 DinahВҰ16430, Yacob'sВҰ16417 sonsВҰ16415 \add gave a false answerВҰ16414\add* to Shekem andВҰ16414 his fatherВҰ16424,
\v 14 \add stating\add*, вҖң\add SorryВҰ16441,\add* we can'tВҰ16435 do that because it would be a disgrace \add in our culture\add* to allow a manВҰ16444 with a foreskinВҰ16448 \add to marry her\add*.
\v 15 We'd only consent \add to your proposal\add* if you'd become like us by circumcisingВҰ16463 everyВҰ16465 maleВҰ16467 among you,
\v 16 ThenВҰ16469 we'd give our daughters to you \add to marry\add*, and we'd take your daughters for us \add to marry\add*. And we'd settle among you, and we \add all\add* would becomeВҰ16482 one \add united\add* peopleВҰ16483.
\v 17 \add ButВҰ16486\add* if youВҰ16489 all won'tВҰ16488 \add agree\add* to get circumcisedВҰ16491, thenВҰ16486 we'll \add just\add* takeВҰ16492 \add DinahВҰ16493\add* andВҰ16486 goВҰ16496.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add This idea\add* pleasedВҰ16498 HamorВҰ16501 andВҰ16502 his son,
\v 19 \add so Shekem\add* didn'tВҰ16508 delayВҰ16510 \add implementing the plan\add* because he was the most honouredВҰ16520 son inВҰ16516 his father'sВҰ16523 householdВҰ16522, andВҰ16508 he was so delightedВҰ16515 withВҰ16516 Yacob'sВҰ16518 daughterВҰ16516.
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ16525 HamorВҰ16526 and ShekemВҰ16527 wentВҰ16525 to \add the city elders at\add* the gate of their city, and they spokeВҰ16533 to them, saying,
\v 21 вҖңThese men are peacefulВҰ16542 towards us, so let them settle in the land, and let them tradeВҰ16547 in it. And look, the land \add is plenty wide enough for them as well\add*. We can take theirВҰ16557 daughters for ourselves as wivesВҰ16561, and we can give our daughters to them \add to marry\add*.
\v 22 \add But\add* they'll only consent to settle among us and unite withВҰ16570 us onВҰ16570 this \add condition\add*: we would need to circumcise all of the males amongst us, just like they're circumcised.
\v 23 Won't all of their livestock and their propertyВҰ16589 and all their animalsВҰ16592 then belong to us? \add So\add* let's agreeВҰ16597 with \add their condition\add* and then they'll settle amongВҰ16600 us.вҖқ
\v 24 All \add the elders\add* at the city gate \add agreed with\add* HamorВҰ16605 and his son ShekemВҰ16608, and \add so\add* everyВҰ16616 male who \add passed through\add* the city gate was circumcisedВҰ16615.
\rem /s1 Dinah's Brothers Avenge Their Sister
\p
\v 25 Three days later when \add all those men\add* were inВҰ16626 pain \add from the cutting\add*, twoВҰ16631 of Yacob'sВҰ16635 sonsВҰ16633, SimeonВҰ16636 and LeviВҰ16637 who were Dinah'sВҰ16639 brothersВҰ16638, tookВҰ16630 theirВҰ16628 swordsВҰ16641 and boldly attacked the cityВҰ16645 and slaughtered everyВҰ16648 maleВҰ16650,
\v 26 including HamorВҰ16654 and his son Shekem. ThenВҰ16652 they retrieved DinahВҰ16666 from Shekem's houseВҰ16667 and left \add the city\add*.
\v 27 Then when Yacob'sВҰ16672 \add other sonsВҰ16671\add* discovered that a slaughter \add had taken place\add*, theyВҰ16673 looted the cityВҰ16678 because theirВҰ16681 sisterВҰ16681 had been violatedвҖ”
\v 28 taking flocksВҰ16685 and herdsВҰ16688 and donkeysВҰ16691вҖ”anything the was in the cityВҰ16696 or \add out\add* in the countrysideВҰ16700.
\v 29 They captured their women and children and tookВҰ16716 all their wealthВҰ16707 and everything that was inВҰ16722 their housesВҰ16722.
\p
\v 30 \add Afterwards,\add* YacobВҰ16725 scolded SimeonВҰ16728 and LeviВҰ16731, saying, вҖңYou \add two\add* have \add made\add* troubleВҰ16732 for me by \add destroying my reputation withВҰ16735\add* those who live inВҰ16735 the landвҖ”the CanaanitesВҰ16737 and the PerizzitesВҰ16738. \add There's only a few of us\add*, and if they gatherВҰ16742 together to attackВҰ16744 me \add and my household\add*, thenВҰ16724 \add we'll\add* be destroyedвҖ”me and \add all\add* my household.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 \add ButВҰ16749\add* they \add вүҲrespondedВҰ16749\add*, вҖңShould he \add have gotten away with\add* treating our sisterВҰ16754 like a prostituteВҰ16750?вҖқ
\c 35
\s1 God blesses Yacob at Beyt-El
\rem /s1 Jacob Returns to Bethel; Jacob's Return to Bethel; God Blesses Jacob at Bethel
\p
\v 1 Then GodВҰ16758 told YacobВҰ16761, вҖң\add Pack\add* up and \add move\add* to Beyt-El and settleВҰ16767 there, and make an altarВҰ16773 there to the god who appearedВҰ16775 to you when you were fleeing from your brotherВҰ16781 EsawВҰ16780.вҖқ\x + \xo 35:1: \xt Gen 28:11-17.\x*
\p
\v 2 \add SoВҰ16783\add* YacobВҰ16784 instructed his householdВҰ16787 and \add everyone\add* withВҰ16799 him, вҖңRemoveВҰ16794 \add any\add* foreignВҰ16797 \add idols\add* thatВҰ16798 are among youВҰ16799, and purifyВҰ16800 yourselves and changeВҰ16801 yourВҰ16802 clothesВҰ16802.
\v 3 ThenВҰ16804 \add we'll leave here\add* and \add make the uphill trip\add* to Beyt-El, and I'll make an altarВҰ16812 thereВҰ16811 to GodВҰ16813, who answeredВҰ16814 me \add when I was\add* distressedВҰ16817. He's been withВҰ16820 me \add wherever\add* I've gone.вҖқ
\v 4 SoВҰ16824 they gaveВҰ16824 YacobВҰ16827 all \add their idols and their earrings\add*, and \add he buried\add* them underВҰ16843 the terebinth tree thatВҰ16833 was near ShekemВҰ16848.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ16850 they \add started theirВҰ16859 journey butВҰ16850\add* andВҰ16850 the \add peopleВҰ16861 of\add* the citiesВҰ16857 aroundВҰ16859 them \add were afraid of Yacob'sВҰ16864 godВҰ16854\add* so they didn'tВҰ16860 \add attack them\add*.
\v 6 \add SoВҰ16866\add* YacobВҰ16867 andВҰ16866 everyoneВҰ16879 with him \add eventually arrived\add* at LuzВҰ16868 in the CanaanВҰ16871 regionВҰ16870 (which is \add now named\add* Beyt-El).
\v 7 He builtВҰ16884 an altarВҰ16886 there andВҰ16884 named the placeВҰ16888 вҖҳEl Beyt-ElвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳthe god of Beyt-ElвҖҷ)\add*, because God had revealedВҰ16895 himself to him there when he was fleeing from his brother \add Esaw\add*.
\v 8 ThenВҰ16902 Rebekah'sВҰ16905 nurseВҰ16904 DeborahВҰ16903 diedВҰ16902 andВҰ16902 was buriedВҰ16906 under the oak tree below Beyt-El \add so\add* he named \add the place\add* вҖҳAllon BakutвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳoak of weepingвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add Now that YacobВҰ16923 had left\add* PaddanВҰ16926-Aram and \add come back to Beyt-El\add*, GodВҰ16920 appearedВҰ16919 to him \add there\add* againВҰ16924 and blessedВҰ16928 him
\v 10 andВҰ16931 told him, вҖңYourВҰ16940 name is Yacob \add butВҰ16931\add* you won'tВҰ16937 be called Yacob anymore. \add From now on,\add* you'll be called Yisra'el (вҖҳIsraelВҰ16947вҖҷ).вҖқ SoВҰ16931 \add againВҰ16942\add*\x + \xo 35:10: \xt Gen 32:28.\x* \add GodВҰ16934\add* called \add him\add* Yisra'el.
\v 11 ThenВҰ16956 God \add also told\add* him, вҖңI'm God the provider. Be fruitfulВҰ16962 and multiplyВҰ16963. Out of you will come a nationВҰ16964 and a community of nationsВҰ16966, and kingsВҰ16969 will come from yourВҰ16970 \add descendants\add*,\x + \xo 35:11-12: \xt Gen 17:4-8.\x*
\v 12 and I'll give you the land thatВҰ16976 I gaveВҰ16977 to AbrahamВҰ16978 and to IsaacВҰ16979, and \add in the future,\add* I'll give the land to your descendantsВҰ16982 afterВҰ16983 you.вҖқ
\v 13 After GodВҰ16991 finished talking to Yacob, heВҰ16995 left himВҰ16990 andВҰ16989 went \add back\add* up.
\v 14 ThenВҰ16998 YacobВҰ16999 set up a stoneВҰ17007 pillar atВҰ17001 the placeВҰ17001 whereВҰ17002 \add God\add* had spokenВҰ17004 withВҰ17001 him, andВҰ16998 heВҰ17004 poured a drinkВҰ17010 offeringВҰ17010 over it, followed by oilВҰ17013,\x + \xo 35:14-15: \xt Gen 28:18-19.\x*
\v 15 andВҰ17015 he named that placeВҰ17020 вҖҳBeyt-ElвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳGod's houseВҰ17026вҖҷ) because\add* God had spokenВҰ17022 to him thereВҰ17024.
\s1 Rahel dies giving birth to Benyamin
\rem /s1 The Birth of Benjamin and the Death of Rachel; The Death of Rachel; The Deaths of Rachel and Isaac
\p
\v 16 Then they moved onВҰ17044 from Beyt-El, andВҰ17030 there was still quite a distanceВҰ17036 to goВҰ17039 to reach to \add the town of\add* EfrathВҰ17040. Then Rahel \add went into labourВҰ17044\add*, butВҰ17030 was having great difficultyВҰ17043 inВҰ17044 \add delivering the baby\add*.
\v 17 \add At one point\add* when sheВҰ17047 was inВҰ17047 hard labourВҰ17048, the midwifeВҰ17051 saidВҰ17049 to herВҰ17048, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ17054. You've got another son.вҖқ
\v 18 \add ButВҰ17063 Rahel\add* was dying, andВҰ17063 as her \add spirit\add* was leaving her, sheВҰ17067 named \add the baby\add* вҖҳBen'oniвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳson of my sorrowвҖҷ)\add*, butВҰ17063 \add afterwards Yacob\add* renamed him вҖҳBenyaminВҰ17077вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳson of my right handвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 19 \add Thus\add* Rahel diedВҰ17079 andВҰ17081 was buriedВҰ17081 onВҰ17082 the pathВҰ17082 to EfrathВҰ17083 (which is \add now called\add* Bethlehem).
\v 20 YacobВҰ17089 set up a \add stone\add* pillar over herВҰ17093 graveвҖ”that's the pillar of Rahel'sВҰ17098 grave to this dayВҰ17101.
\v 21 ThenВҰ17103 Yisra'el \add and his household moved on\add* and pitchedВҰ17105 \add their\add* tents beyondВҰ17108 Migdal Eder.
\s1 Yisra'el's sons
\rem /s1 The Sons of Jacob
\r (1 Chr. 2:1-2)
\p
\v 22 While they were livingВҰ17114 inВҰ17114 that area, \add Yisra'el's son\add* ReubenВҰ17119 slept withВҰ17114 his father'sВҰ17127 slave-wife BilhahВҰ17124, andВҰ17113 Yisra'el found out \add about it\add*.\x + \xo 35:22: \xt Gen 49:4.\x*
\p \add Yisra'el\add* now had twelve sonsВҰ17134.
\v 23 Le'ah's sonsВҰ17140 were his eldest son Reuven, and then to SimeonВҰ17145, LeviВҰ17146, YihudahВҰ17147, Yissakar, and ZebulunВҰ17149.
\v 24 Rahel'sВҰ17152 sonsВҰ17151 were YosefВҰ17153 andВҰ17154 BenyaminВҰ17154.
\v 25 The sonsВҰ17156 of Rahel's slave woman BilhahВҰ17157 were DanВҰ17160 andВҰ17161 NaftaliВҰ17161.
\v 26 The sons of Leah'sВҰ17166 slave women ZilpahВҰ17164 were GadВҰ17167 andВҰ17163 AsherВҰ17168. Those were \add Yisra'el's\add* sons who were \add nearly all\add* born inВҰ17176 PaddanВҰ17176-Aram.
\s1 Yitshak's death
\rem /s1 The Death of Isaac
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ17179 \add Yisra'el\add* wentВҰ17179 VISIT OR LIVE? to his fatherВҰ17184 Yitshak in MamreВҰ17185 (\add also named\add* KiriatВҰ17186-Arba or HebronВҰ17189), whereВҰ17190 AbrahamВҰ17195 andВҰ17196 Yitshak had \add lived for a time\add*.\x + \xo 35:27: \xt Gen 13:18.\x*
\v 28 YitshakВҰ17200 lived to be 180 years old.
\v 29 ThenВҰ17206 Yitshak, having lived a long and full life, \add breathedВҰ17206 his last\add* and diedВҰ17208 and \add joined his ancestors\add*, and his sonsВҰ17220 EsawВҰ17218 and \add Yisra'el\add* buriedВҰ17216 him.
\c 36
\s1 Esaw's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Esau; Descendants of Esau; Esau's Descendants
\r (1 Chr. 1:34-37)
\p
\v 1 These are the descendants of EsawВҰ17225 (who's also known as EdomВҰ17227):
\v 2 EsawВҰ17229 had \add married two local womenВҰ17234 from the CanaanВҰ17235 region\add*: AdahВҰ17238 (the HittiteВҰ17242 Elon'sВҰ17241 daughter) and OholibamahВҰ17245 (Anah'sВҰ17248 daughter and granddaughter of the HiviteВҰ17252 ZibeonВҰ17251)\x + \xo 36:2: \xt Gen 26:34.\x*
\v 3 and BasematВҰ17256 (Yishma'el'sВҰ17259 daughterВҰ17257 and the sisterВҰ17260 of NevayotВҰ17261).\x + \xo 36:3: \xt Gen 28:9.\x*
\p
\v 4 Esaw'sВҰ17265 \add wife\add* AdahВҰ17264 gave birth to ElifazВҰ17268, andВҰ17263 BasematВҰ17269 gave birth to ReuelВҰ17273.
\v 5 Oholibamah gave birth to YeushВҰ17279 and YalamВҰ17283 and KorahВҰ17286. Those were Esaw's sonsВҰ17288 who were born in the CanaanВҰ17295 regionВҰ17294.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ17297 EsawВҰ17298 tookВҰ17297 his wivesВҰ17301 and his sonsВҰ17304 and daughtersВҰ17307 and all his householdВҰ17313, and his livestock and all his animals and all his possessions thatВҰ17326 he had acquired in the CanaanВҰ17329 regionВҰ17328, and he wentВҰ17330 to a place \add far away\add* from his brother Yisra'elВҰ17335,
\v 7 because they had too many possessions for them to remain togetherВҰ17344, and the land they were staying in wasn't able to supportВҰ17349 \add both of\add* them because of \add all\add* their livestockВҰ17352.
\v 8 \add SoВҰ17354\add* EsawВҰ17355 (\add also known\add* as EdomВҰ17360) settled \add his household\add* inВҰ17356 the Se'ir hills.
\p
\v 9 Now theseВҰ17362 are the \add following\add* generations of EsawВҰ17364, the father of the Edomites inВҰ17367 the Se'ir hills:
\v 10 \add Two of\add* Esaw's sonsВҰ17372 were ElifazВҰ17375, who he had with his wife AdahВҰ17378, and ReuelВҰ17381, who he had with his wife BasematВҰ17384.
\p
\v 11 Elifaz'sВҰ17390 sonsВҰ17389 were TemanВҰ17391, OmarВҰ17392, ZefoВҰ17393 and GatamВҰ17394 and KenazВҰ17395.
\v 12 Elifaz and his slave-wife Timna had \add a son they named\add* AmalekВҰ17409. (Elifaz'sВҰ17401 sonsВҰ17411 \add were all\add* grandsons of EsawВҰ17404 and his wife AdahВҰ17412.)
\v 13 Reuel'sВҰ17418 sons were NahatВҰ17419, ZerahВҰ17420, ShammahВҰ17421, and MizzahВҰ17422. (They were the grandsons of EsawВҰ17429 and his wife BasematВҰ17427.)
\v 14 EsawВҰ17442 and his wife Oholibamah had YeushВҰ17447, YalamВҰ17451, and KorahВҰ17454. (\add Oholibamah was\add* the daughter of AnahВҰ17437 and the granddaughter of ZibeonВҰ17440.)
\rem /s1 Clans and Kings of Edom
\p
\v 15 TheseВҰ17456 were Esaw's sons \add who became\add* leaders: the sons of ElifazВҰ17462 (Esaw's eldest son) \add which were\add* Chief TemanВҰ17466, Chief OmarВҰ17468, Chief ZefoВҰ17470, Chief KenazВҰ17472,
\v 16 Chief KorahВҰ17476, Chief GatamВҰ17478, Chief AmalekВҰ17480. Those were the chiefsВҰ17482 of ElifazВҰ17483 in the EdomВҰ17485 regionВҰ17484. (They were the grandsons of \add Esaw and his wife\add* AdahВҰ17488.)
\p
\v 17 These were the sons of Esaw's son Reuel: Chief NahathВҰ17497, Chief ZerahВҰ17499, Chief ShammahВҰ17501, Chief MizzahВҰ17503. Those were the chiefsВҰ17505 of Reuel in the EdomВҰ17508 regionВҰ17507. (They were the grandsons of Esaw andВҰ17490 his wife BasemathВҰ17511.)
\p
\v 18 These were the sonsВҰ17516 of Esaw's wife Oholibamah: Chief YeushВҰ17521, Chief YalamВҰ17523, Chief KorahВҰ17525. (They were the chiefsВҰ17527 from Esaw's wife OholibamahвҖ”Anah'sВҰ17531 daughterВҰ17529.)
\v 19 Those were the sonsВҰ17536 of EsawВҰ17538 (\add also known\add* as EdomВҰ17542), andВҰ17539 those were theirВҰ17540 chiefsВҰ17540.
\s1 Se'ir's descendants
\rem /s1 The Descendants of Seir; Original Peoples of Edom
\r (1 Chr. 1:38-42)
\p
\v 20 These were the sonsВҰ17546 of Se'ir the HoriteВҰ17549 who were inhabitingВҰ17550 \add that area\add*: LotanВҰ17552, ShobalВҰ17553, ZibeonВҰ17554, AnahВҰ17555,
\v 21 DishonВҰ17557, EzerВҰ17558, andВҰ17557 DishanВҰ17559. Those were the chiefsВҰ17561 of the HoritesВҰ17562, Se'ir's sonsВҰ17563, in the EdomВҰ17566 regionВҰ17565.
\v 22 Lotan'sВҰ17571 sonsВҰ17569 were HoriВҰ17572 and HemamВҰ17573, and his sisterВҰ17574 was TimnaВҰ17576.
\v 23 Shobal'sВҰ17580 sonsВҰ17579 were AlvanВҰ17581, ManahathВҰ17582, EbalВҰ17583, ShefoВҰ17584, andВҰ17578 OnamВҰ17585.
\v 24 Zibeon'sВҰ17590 sonsВҰ17588 were AiahВҰ17591 andВҰ17587 Anah. This is the same Anah who discovered some hot springsВҰ17599 while he was out inВҰ17600 the desert grazing his father'sВҰ17606 donkeysВҰ17604.
\v 25 Anah'sВҰ17611 childrenВҰ17609 were \add his son\add* DishonВҰ17612 andВҰ17613 his daughterВҰ17614 OholibamahВҰ17613.
\v 26 Dishon'sВҰ17620 sonsВҰ17619 were HemdanВҰ17621, EshbanВҰ17622, IthranВҰ17623, andВҰ17618 KeranВҰ17624.
\v 27 Ezer'sВҰ17629 sonsВҰ17627 were BilhanВҰ17630, ZaavanВҰ17631, and AkanВҰ17632.
\v 28 Dishan'sВҰ17637 sonsВҰ17635 were UzВҰ17638 andВҰ17639 AranВҰ17639.
\v 29 TheseВҰ17641 were the chiefsВҰ17642 of the HoritesВҰ17643: Chief LotanВҰ17645, Chief ShobalВҰ17647, Chief ZibeonВҰ17649, Chief AnahВҰ17651,
\rem /s1 The Kings of Edom
\rem /r (1 Chronicles 1.43-54)
\v 30 Chief DishonВҰ17654, Chief EzerВҰ17656, Chief DishanВҰ17658. Those were the chiefs of the HoritesВҰ17661, accordingВҰ17662 to theirВҰ17662 clans in the Se'ir regionВҰ17663.
\s1 The kings around Edom
\rem /s1 The Rulers of Edom; Rulers of Edom
\r (1 Chr. 1:43-54)
\p
\v 31 And theseВҰ17667 were the kingsВҰ17668 who reigned in EdomВҰ17672 regionВҰ17671 before the tribes of Yisra'el had a kingВҰ17676:
\v 32 Beor'sВҰ17685 son BelaВҰ17682 reignedВҰ17680 inВҰ17681 EdomВҰ17681, andВҰ17686 the nameВҰ17686 of his cityВҰ17687 was DinhabahВҰ17688.
\v 33 ThenВҰ17690 BelaВҰ17691 diedВҰ17690, andВҰ17692 Zerah'sВҰ17697 son YobabВҰ17694 from BozrahВҰ17698 reignedВҰ17692 in his placeВҰ17693.
\v 34 ThenВҰ17700 YobabВҰ17701 diedВҰ17700, andВҰ17700 HushamВҰ17704 from the land of the TemanitesВҰ17706 reignedВҰ17702 in his placeВҰ17703.
\v 35 ThenВҰ17708 HushamВҰ17709 diedВҰ17708, and Bedad'sВҰ17715 son HadadВҰ17712 reignedВҰ17710 in his placeВҰ17711, and the nameВҰ17722 of his cityВҰ17723 was AvithВҰ17724. \add He was the one\add* who attacked the Midianites in the countrysideВҰ17720 in MoabВҰ17721.
\v 36 ThenВҰ17726 HadadВҰ17727 diedВҰ17726, andВҰ17728 SamlahВҰ17730 from MasrekahВҰ17731 reignedВҰ17728 in his placeВҰ17729.
\v 37 ThenВҰ17733 SamlahВҰ17734 diedВҰ17733, andВҰ17735 Sha'ulВҰ17737 from RehobothВҰ17738 \add by\add* the riverВҰ17739 reignedВҰ17735 in his placeВҰ17736.
\v 38 ThenВҰ17741 Sha'ul diedВҰ17741, andВҰ17743 Acbor's son Baal-HananВҰ17746 reignedВҰ17743 in his placeВҰ17744.
\v 39 ThenВҰ17751 (Acbor's son) Baal-HananВҰ17753 died, and HadarВҰ17759 reignedВҰ17757 in his placeВҰ17758, and the name of his cityВҰ17761 was PauВҰ17762. His wife's name was MehetabelВҰ17765 (\add and she was\add* the daughter of Matred'sВҰ17768 daughter and the granddaughter of Me-ZahabВҰ17771).
\p
\v 40 And theseВҰ17773 are the names of the chiefsВҰ17775 of EsawВҰ17776, according to their clansВҰ17777, according to their places, by their names: Chief TimnaВҰ17781, Chief Alvan, Chief YetetВҰ17785,
\v 41 Chief OholibamahВҰ17788, Chief ElahВҰ17790, Chief PinonВҰ17792,
\v 42 Chief KenazВҰ17795, Chief TemanВҰ17797, Chief MibzarВҰ17799,
\v 43 Chief MagdielВҰ17802, and Chief IramВҰ17804. They were the chiefsВҰ17803 of EdomВҰ17808, accordingВҰ17809 to their dwellings in the land of their possessionВҰ17811. That was \add the record about\add* EsawВҰ17813, the ancestorВҰ17814 of the Edomites.
\c 37
\s1 Yosef's dreams cause conflict
\rem /s1 Joseph; Joseph Dreams of Greatness; Joseph's Dreams; Joseph and His Brothers
\p
\v 1 Yisra'el \add (Israel/YacobВҰ17819/Jacob)\add* lived in the area where his fatherВҰ17822 \add Yitshak\add* had stayed, in the CanaanВҰ17824 regionВҰ17820.
\v 2 This is \add the record of his\add* descendants:
\p When Yosef \add (Joseph)\add* was seventeenВҰ17833, he was shepherdingВҰ17838 the flocksВҰ17842 withВҰ17842 his brothers. He was \add younger than his brothers\add* who were the sons of his father's \add slave\add* wivesВҰ17853 BilhahВҰ17848 and ZilpahВҰ17852. \add One day\add* Yosef gave a \add tell-tale\add* bad reportВҰ17859 about them to theirВҰ17863 father.
\p
\v 3 \add Now\add* Yisra'el lovedВҰ17866 YosefВҰ17869 more than all of his \add other\add* sonsВҰ17872 because he was \add born to him when he was already old\add*, so he made a multicoloured robe for him.
\v 4 \add WhenВҰ17885\add* his brothers saw that theirВҰ17891 fatherВҰ17891 lovedВҰ17890 \add Yosef\add* more than all of his brothers, they hatedВҰ17895 him andВҰ17885 couldn't \add make themselves say anything nice\add* to him.
\p
\v 5 \add OneВҰ17910 night\add* YosefВҰ17903 had a dreamВҰ17904, andВҰ17902 he told his brothersВҰ17906 about it, \add butВҰ17902\add* that made them hateВҰ17909 him even more.
\v 6 He \add вүҲtold\add* them, вҖңPlease \add listenВҰ17914 about\add* this dreamВҰ17917 thatВҰ17919 I \add had\add*:
\v 7 See, we were \add tying up bundles of grain stalks\add* in the middleВҰ17926 of a fieldВҰ17927, and wow, my bundle got up and stoodВҰ17933 uprightВҰ17933. ThenВҰ17922 \add would you believe it\add*, your bundles gatheredВҰ17935 around and bowedВҰ17937 down to my \add one\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңWill you really reign over us?вҖқ his brothersВҰ17942 \add retorted\add*. вҖң\add Do you think\add* you'll really rule over us?вҖқ \add SoВҰ17940\add* they continuedВҰ17940 to hateВҰ17953 him even more because of his dreamsВҰ17957 andВҰ17940 because of \add what he saidВҰ17940\add*.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ17962 \add Yosef had\add* another dream, and \add againВҰ17963\add* he told his brothersВҰ17968, вҖңListen, I \add had\add* another dream, and wow, the sun and the moon and eleven starsВҰ17979 were bowingВҰ17980 down to me.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add WhenВҰ17983\add* he told his father and his brothers, his father scolded him, вҖңWhat's this dreamВҰ17997 thatВҰ17999 you \add had\add*? Will your motherВҰ18004 and I and your brothers \add actually\add* come to bow down to the groundВҰ18008 to you?вҖқ
\v 11 \add ConsequentlyВҰ18016\add* his brothersВҰ18013 envied him, butВҰ18010 his fatherВҰ18014 \add keptВҰ18015 pondering it\add*.\x + \xo 37:11: \xt Acts 7:9.\x*
\s1 Yosef is sold by his brothers
\rem /s1 Joseph Is Sold and Taken to Egypt; Joseph Is Sold by His Brothers; Joseph Sold by His Brothers
\p
\v 12 \add Sometime after that, Yosef's\add* brothersВҰ18021 wentВҰ18020 to shepherd theirВҰ18027 father'sВҰ18027 flocksВҰ18025 near ShekemВҰ18028.
\v 13 \add One day,\add* Yisra'el said to YosefВҰ18034, вҖңAren't your brothersВҰ18036 \add away\add* shepherding near ShekemВҰ18038? Come \add we'll get some supplies\add* andВҰ18030 I'll send you to them.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Sure\add*,вҖқ Yosef \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ18046 he \add вүҲtold\add* him, вҖңPlease goВҰ18048 and seeВҰ18051 \add how\add* your brothersВҰ18055 \add are doing\add* and the flocksВҰ18059 \add as well\add*, thenВҰ18046 \add come and let me know\add*.вҖқ
\p SoВҰ18046 he sentВҰ18062 \add Yosef off\add* from the HebronВҰ18064 valleyВҰ18063, and he wentВҰ18065 to ShekemВҰ18066.
\v 15 \add WhenВҰ18068 he got there,\add* a man \add noticed\add* him wanderingВҰ18071 around the countrysideВҰ18072 andВҰ18068 askedВҰ18073 him, вҖңWhat are you lookingВҰ18078 forВҰ18078?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңI'm looking forВҰ18085 my brothersВҰ18083,вҖқ he answered. вҖңPlease tell me whereВҰ18090 they're \add looking after our flocks\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңThey've leftВҰ18096 here,вҖқ the manВҰ18095 respondedВҰ18094. вҖңI heardВҰ18099 them say, вҖҳLet's goВҰ18101 to DothanВҰ18102.вҖҷ вҖқ
\rem /s1 Joseph Sold into Slavery
\p SoВҰ18094 YosefВҰ18104 continuedВҰ18094 onВҰ18108 afterВҰ18105 his brothersВҰ18106 andВҰ18094 foundВҰ18107 them atВҰ18108 DotanВҰ18102,
\v 18 \add butВҰ18110\add* they sawВҰ18110 him from a distanceВҰ18112 andВҰ18110 beforeВҰ18113 heВҰ18114 \add got close\add* to them, they \add made plans among themselves\add* to killВҰ18118 him.
\v 19 вҖңLook, that masterВҰ18126 \add dreamerВҰ18127\add* is comingВҰ18129,вҖқ theyВҰ18120 saidВҰ18120 to each other.
\v 20 вҖң\add Here's our chance to\add* killВҰ18134 him andВҰ18131 throwВҰ18135 \add his body\add* into one of the pits \add around here\add*. We'll sayВҰ18138 that a \add wild\add* animalВҰ18139 \add attacked\add* him. \em ThenВҰ18131\em* we'll seeВҰ18142 what his dreamsВҰ18146 \add turn into\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 ButВҰ18148 ReubenВҰ18149 heard \add what they were saying\add*, andВҰ18148 he \add tried to\add* rescue \add Yosef by insisting\add*, вҖңLet's not \add takeВҰ18154\add* his lifeВҰ18155.вҖқ
\v 22 вҖңDon't shed bloodВҰ18165,вҖқ he continuedВҰ18157. вҖңThrow him into \add thatВҰ18172\add* pit inВҰ18173 the wildernessВҰ18173, butВҰ18157 don'tВҰ18161 \add wound\add* him.вҖқ \add He saidВҰ18157 this\add* because he was planning to rescueВҰ18181 Yosef \add later\add* andВҰ18157 return him \add home\add* to \add theirВҰ18183\add* fatherВҰ18187.
\v 23 \add SoВҰ18189\add* when YosefВҰ18193 \add reached\add* his brothersВҰ18196, they \add grabbed him andВҰ18189 ripped\add* off the colouredВҰ18207 robeВҰ18203 thatВҰ18208 \add he was wearing\add*.
\v 24 ThenВҰ18211 they tookВҰ18211 him andВҰ18211 \add dropped\add* him into the pit. (TheВҰ18213 pit was emptyВҰ18216 with no waterВҰ18219 in \add the bottom\add*).
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ18221 they sat down to eatВҰ18222, and \add a bit later when they looked up\add*, look, \add there was\add* a caravanВҰ18229 of Yishma'elitesВҰ18230 comingВҰ18231 \add towardsВҰ18240 them\add*. \add They had left\add* GileadВҰ18232 carryingВҰ18239 spicesВҰ18235 and balm and myrrhВҰ18237 on their camelsВҰ18233 that they were going to take down to EgyptВҰ18240.
\v 26 ThenВҰ18242 YehudahВҰ18243 \add (Judah)\add* saidВҰ18242 to his brothersВҰ18246, вҖңWhat will we gain if we killВҰ18251 our brotherВҰ18254 andВҰ18242 coverВҰ18255 up his bloodВҰ18258?
\v 27 Let's sell him to \add these\add* IshmaelitesВҰ18262 \add so we won'tВҰ18264 be guilty of killing\add* him. \add After all,\add* he's our brotherВҰ18271вҖ”our \add own\add* fleshВҰ18272 \add and blood\add*.вҖқ And his brothersВҰ18275 \add agreed\add*.
\v 28 \add SoВҰ18277 when\add* the Midianite traders came past, \add the brothers\add* pulled Yosef up and liftedВҰ18282 him out of the pit and sold \add him\add* to the IshmaelitesВҰ18293 for twentyВҰ18294 \add pieces\add* of silverВҰ18295. ThenВҰ18277 \add the traders tookВҰ18296\add* Yosef \add onwards withВҰ18294 them\add* to Mitsrayim.\x + \xo 37:28: \xt Acts 7:9.\x*
\p
\v 29 \add LaterВҰ18313 onВҰ18311,\add* ReubenВҰ18303 returnedВҰ18302 to the pit, butВҰ18302 wow, YosefВҰ18310 wasn't \add down there\add*, so he tore his clothesВҰ18315 \add inВҰ18311 despair\add*
\v 30 and returnedВҰ18317 to his brothersВҰ18320 and saidВҰ18321, вҖңThe boyВҰ18322 isn't there. \add What am I goingВҰ18328 to do\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ18330 theyВҰ18330 slaughteredВҰ18335 a young goatВҰ18336 and tookВҰ18330 Yosef'sВҰ18334 robeВҰ18341 and dippedВҰ18338 \add it\add* inВҰ18342 the bloodВҰ18342.
\v 32 ThenВҰ18344 they sent the colouredВҰ18348 robe \add back\add* to theirВҰ18352 fatherВҰ18352 with this message: вҖңWe foundВҰ18355 this. Please examine whether or not it's your son'sВҰ18360 robe.вҖқ
\p
\v 33 \add Yisra'el\add* recognisedВҰ18366 it andВҰ18366 saidВҰ18367, вҖңIt \em is\em* my son'sВҰ18369 robe. A \add wild\add* animalВҰ18370 \add must have eaten\add* him. YosefВҰ18375 was \add almost\add* certainly torn to piecesВҰ18374.вҖқ
\v 34 ThenВҰ18377 YacobВҰ18378 ripped his clothesВҰ18379 and put sackclothВҰ18381 \add around\add* his \add waist\add*, and he mournedВҰ18383 for his son many daysВҰ18387.
\v 35 All his \add other\add* sonsВҰ18393 and all his daughtersВҰ18396 \add came\add* to comfort him, butВҰ18390 he refusedВҰ18398 to be comforted and saidВҰ18400, вҖңI will goВҰ18403 down to my son in \add the grave\add* mourningВҰ18407.вҖқ SoВҰ18390 his fatherВҰ18411 wept for him.
\p
\v 36 Meanwhile, the Midianites \add arrived\add* in EgyptВҰ18418 andВҰ18413 sold him to PotifarВҰ18419вҖ”Far'oh's captain of the guardsВҰ18423.
\c 38
\s1 Yehudah mistreats Tamar
\rem /s1 Judah and Tamar
\p
\v 1 \add Around that timeВҰ18427\add*, YehudahВҰ18430 \add (Judah)\add* went down \add the hills\add* from \add where\add* his brothersВҰ18432 \add were\add* and settledВҰ18433 near an AdullamiteВҰ18437 manВҰ18436 named HirahВҰ18439.
\v 2 There YehudahВҰ18444 sawВҰ18441 the daughterВҰ18445 of a CanaaniteВҰ18448 manВҰ18447 named ShuaВҰ18450, andВҰ18441 he tookВҰ18451 her \add as a wife\add*. He \add slept with\add* her
\v 3 and she got pregnantВҰ18455 and \add in due course\add*, gaveВҰ18456 birthВҰ18456 to a son who Yehudah named ErВҰ18462.
\v 4 ThenВҰ18464 she got pregnantВҰ18464 againВҰ18465 and gaveВҰ18466 birthВҰ18466 a \add another\add* son, and she named him OnanВҰ18469.
\v 5 ThenВҰ18474 she \add got pregnant yet againВҰ18475\add* and gaveВҰ18476 birthВҰ18476 to a \add third\add* son, and she named him ShelahВҰ18482. (\add Yehudah\add* was inВҰ18484 Kezib when she \add Onan was born\add*.)
\p
\v 6 \add In due course,\add* YehudahВҰ18489 tookВҰ18488 a wifeВҰ18490 for ErВҰ18491 his firstbornВҰ18492, andВҰ18493 herВҰ18493 nameВҰ18493 was TamarВҰ18494.
\v 7 ButВҰ18496 ErВҰ18497 was evilВҰ18500 in Yahweh's eyesВҰ18501, so Yahweh killed himВҰ18503.
\v 8 ThenВҰ18506 YehudahВҰ18507 saidВҰ18506 to OnanВҰ18508, вҖңGo to your brother's wifeВҰ18512 andВҰ18506 performВҰ18514 your \add brotherly\add* duty to her \add to\add* produce \add children\add* for your brother.вҖқ
\v 9 However, OnanВҰ18521 knewВҰ18520 that \add any children\add* wouldn't be his, so \add whenever\add* he \add slept with\add* his brother's wifeВҰ18534, he spilledВҰ18536 \add his semenВҰ18536\add* on the ground so that he wouldn't giveВҰ18539 \add children\add* to his \add late\add* brother.
\v 10 \add ButВҰ18552\add* YahwehВҰ18546 \add considered\add* what he did to be evil, so he killed him also.
\v 11 ThenВҰ18554 YehudahВҰ18555 \add вүҲtold\add* his daughter-in-lawВҰ18557 Tamar, вҖңRemain a widowВҰ18559 in your father's house untilВҰ18563 my son ShelahВҰ18566 grows up.вҖқ \add This was\add* because he'd said, вҖңSo that he doesn't also die like his brothersВҰ18576!вҖқ So Tamar went andВҰ18554 lived in the house of herВҰ18581 father.
\p
\v 12 \add A long time afterwards\add*, Yehudah'sВҰ18591 wifeВҰ18589 (Shua'sВҰ18588 daughterВҰ18586) diedВҰ18585. \add After\add* Yehudah \add had finished mourning\add*, he andВҰ18583 his friend HirahВҰ18600 (the AdullamiteВҰ18602) went to TimnahВҰ18603 to \add where\add* the men were shearingВҰ18597 his sheepВҰ18598.
\v 13 ThenВҰ18605 TamarВҰ18606 was told, вҖңLook, yourВҰ18609 father-in-lawВҰ18609 is goingВҰ18610 to TimnahВҰ18611 to shearВҰ18612 his sheepВҰ18613.вҖқ
\v 14 \add SoВҰ18615\add* she \add changed out of\add* herВҰ18617 widow'sВҰ18617 clothesВҰ18616 and coveredВҰ18619 herself withВҰ18620 a veil and wrappedВҰ18621 herself \add up\add*. ThenВҰ18615 she satВҰ18622 atВҰ18620 the entranceВҰ18623 of EnaimВҰ18624 whichВҰ18625 is onВҰ18620 the roadВҰ18628 to TimnahВҰ18629. \add She was doing this\add* because she had seenВҰ18631 thatВҰ18625 ShelahВҰ18635 had grownВҰ18634 up, butВҰ18615 she hadn't been givenВҰ18639 to him as a wife.
\p
\v 15 \add In due course,\add* YehudahВҰ18644 sawВҰ18643 her andВҰ18643 because she had coveredВҰ18648 her faceВҰ18649, he thought she was a prostituteВҰ18646.
\v 16 \add SoВҰ18651\add* he turned to her beside the road andВҰ18651 asked, вҖңPlease let me \add lie with\add* you,вҖқ because he didn'tВҰ18663 know that she was his daughter-in-lawВҰ18666.
\p вҖңWhat will you giveВҰ18671 me \add in exchange\add*?вҖқ she \add asked\add*.
\p
\v 17 вҖңI'll send \add you\add* a young goat from my flockВҰ18687,вҖқ he replied.
\p вҖңButВҰ18679 what about \add something to keep now as\add* a pledgeВҰ18692 untilВҰ18693 you send it,вҖқ she \add bartered\add*.
\p
\v 18 вҖңWhat pledgeВҰ18698 \add should\add* I giveВҰ18700 you?вҖқ he \add asked\add*.
\p вҖңYour signet \add ring\add* and \add its\add* cord, and your staffВҰ18706 thatВҰ18699 \add you're holding\add*.вҖқ \add SoВҰ18696\add* he \add handed\add* them to her and wentВҰ18712 and lay withВҰ18708 her, and she became pregnantВҰ18714 \add as a result\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ18717 \add Tamar\add* got up and left, and she took off her veil and put her widow'sВҰ18724 clothesВҰ18723 \add back\add* on.
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ18728 YehudahВҰ18727 sentВҰ18726 his friend the AdullamiteВҰ18734 to take the young goat andВҰ18726 get the pledgeВҰ18736 back from the womanВҰ18738, butВҰ18726 he couldn't find her,
\v 21 \add so\add* he askedВҰ18742 \add some of the local\add* menВҰ18745, вҖңWhere's the temple prostitute who was atВҰ18751 EnaimВҰ18751 beside the roadВҰ18754?вҖқ
\p \add ButВҰ18742\add* they answered, вҖңThere's \add never\add* been a temple prostitute \add around here\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \add SoВҰ18762 Hirah\add* returnedВҰ18762 to YehudahВҰ18765 andВҰ18762 \add вүҲtold him\add*, вҖңI couldn't find her. \add What's more\add*, the menВҰ18770 of the place said that there hasn't been a temple prostituteВҰ18777 atВҰ18776 that place.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 вҖң\add Oh well,\add*вҖқ saidВҰ18779 YehudahВҰ18780. вҖңLet her \add keep those\add* things for herself so that we don'tВҰ18792 becomeВҰ18785 a laughingstockВҰ18786. Anyway, I \add did my duty by sending the goatВҰ18789\add*, butВҰ18779 you couldn't find her.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 About three monthsВҰ18799 later, YehudahВҰ18801 was told, вҖңYour daughter-in-lawВҰ18805 TamarВҰ18804 has prostitutedВҰ18803 herself, and \add not only that\add*, she's pregnantВҰ18808 from doing it.вҖқ
\p вҖңBring her out and let her be burnt \add to death\add*.вҖқ Yehudah \add demanded\add*.
\p
\v 25 \add So they got her and\add* broughtВҰ18816 her out, \add butВҰ18817\add* she sentВҰ18818 a message to her father-in-lawВҰ18821, saying, вҖңIt was the manВҰ18823 who these things belong to that got me pregnantВҰ18829.вҖқ Then she \add added\add*, вҖңPlease identify whose signet ring and cords and staffВҰ18837 these are.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \add WhenВҰ18840\add* YehudahВҰ18841 recognisedВҰ18840 \add the items\add*, he admitted, вҖңShe's more \add in the rightВҰ18843\add* than I am,\x + \xo 38:26: \xt 37:11.\x* because I didn't giveВҰ18852 my son ShelahВҰ18853 to her.вҖқ \add ButВҰ18840\add* he didn't \add lie with her againВҰ18858\add*.
\p
\v 27 When the timeВҰ18863 came for \add Tamar\add* to giveВҰ18864 birthВҰ18864, wow, \add she was going to have twinsВҰ18866\add*.
\v 28 \add While\add* she was givingВҰ18870 birthВҰ18870, one \add of the babies poked\add* out a hand andВҰ18869 the midwifeВҰ18875 tied a scarletВҰ18880 threadВҰ18880 \add around its wrist\add*, saying, вҖңThis one came out firstВҰ18884.вҖқ
\v 29 \add However,\add* it pulled its handВҰ18889 back in, thenВҰ18886 wow, its brother \add was delivered first\add*. ThenВҰ18886 she\f + \fr 38:28 \ft It's not clear from the text who вҖҳsheвҖҷ wasвҖ”either the mother or the midwife. Similarly, the вҖҳheвҖҷ in the next sentence (and in the next verse) is presumably the father.\f* saidВҰ18893, вҖңHow \add did you manage to\add* break out first?вҖқ SoВҰ18886 he named him вҖҳPerezВҰ18901вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳbreak outвҖҷ)\add*.
\v 30 After that, his brother who had the scarletВҰ18910 threadВҰ18910 on his \add wrist\add* was delivered, andВҰ18903 he named him ZerahВҰ18913.
\c 39
\s1 Yosef and Potifar's wife
\rem /s1 Joseph and Potiphar's Wife; Joseph in Potiphar's House
\p
\v 1 \add Meanwhile,\add* YosefВҰ18916 had been taken down to EgyptВҰ18918, and an Egyptian manВҰ18925 named Potifar had boughtВҰ18919 him from the IshmaelitesВҰ18928 who had taken him down thereВҰ18931. \add Potifar was\add* the chief of the guardsВҰ18924 for Far'ohВҰ18922 \add (PharaohВҰ18922)\add*.
\v 2 YosefВҰ18937 \add lived\add* in the houseВҰ18942 of his EgyptianВҰ18944 masterВҰ18943, and YahwehВҰ18934 was with him and he was successfulВҰ18940 \add at his work\add*.\x + \xo 39:2: \xt Acts 7:9.\x*
\v 3 His masterВҰ18947 \add noticedВҰ18946\add* that Yahweh was with him andВҰ18946 that Yahweh made everything that heВҰ18954 did succeedВҰ18957,
\v 4 \add so\add* YosefВҰ18961 earned his favourВҰ18962 as he served him. ThenВҰ18960 \add PotifarВҰ18965\add* put him inВҰ18963 charge of his \add entireВҰ18970\add* householdВҰ18969 andВҰ18960 \add everything that he owned\add*.
\v 5 \add From that timeВҰ18979 onwards,\add* Yahweh blessed that Egyptian householdВҰ18994 becauseВҰ18996 of YosefВҰ18997, andВҰ18978 Yahweh's blessing \add even extended\add* from everything inВҰ18982 the home \add all the way out\add* to \add the\add* countrysideВҰ19008.
\v 6 \add Potifar\add* left all his belonging inВҰ19016 Yosef'sВҰ19018 chargeВҰ19016, \add so much so thatВҰ19028\add* he didn'tВҰ19019 have to think about anythingВҰ19023 else beyond \add what he wanted to eat\add*.
\p \add Now\add* Yosef \add had developed\add* into a well-built andВҰ19010 handsomeВҰ19034 \add young man\add*,
\v 7 and afterВҰ19041 a while, his master'sВҰ19047 wifeВҰ19045 \add started to develop a crush on\add* him and told \add him\add*, вҖңComeВҰ19053 to bed with me.вҖқ
\v 8 \add ButВҰ19058\add* he refusedВҰ19058 and told \add her\add*, вҖңListen, withВҰ19073 me here, my masterВҰ19064 doesn't \add have to\add* think about what's in the houseВҰ19073 and \add he's put me in charge of everything\add*.
\v 9 In this houseВҰ19085, he doesn't \add even\add* have more authority than I do and he hasn't kept anythingВҰ19092 back from me, except for you, his wife. How could I do this very wickedВҰ19103 thing and sinВҰ19106 againstВҰ19107 GodВҰ19107.
\v 10 \add ButВҰ19109\add* she kept persisting with YosefВҰ19113 day \add after\add*, \add butВҰ19109\add* he wouldn't lie with her like she wanted.
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ19126 \add one\add* dayВҰ19127 when he went into the house to do his work andВҰ19126 thereВҰ19137 were no other men of the house \add around\add*,
\v 12 \add Potifar's wife\add* grabbed Yosef's cloak and demanded, вҖң\add Come to bed\add* withВҰ19141 me.вҖқ \add ButВҰ19140\add* he \add pulled away and \add* fled outsideВҰ19150 \add the house\add*, leaving herВҰ19147 \add there\add* holding his cloak.
\v 13 \add AsВҰ19154 soon as it registered\add* that he'd fled outsideВҰ19160 leaving his cloak \add behind\add*,
\v 14 she \add yelled\add* for the other male slaves andВҰ19162 told them, вҖңLook, he broughtВҰ19169 a HebrewВҰ19172 \add here\add* manВҰ19171 to \add mock\add* atВҰ19174 us. He \add tried to get me onto the bed\add*, butВҰ19162 I yelled out loudly.
\v 15 WhenВҰ19183 he \add grasped\add* that \add IВҰ19187 was screaming for help\add*, he left his cloak here andВҰ19183 \add just took off\add* outsideВҰ19195.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add Potifar's wife\add* kept the cloak besideВҰ19199 her untilВҰ19200 \add her husband\add*, Yosef's masterВҰ19203, got homeВҰ19206,
\v 17 thenВҰ19208 she told him \add the same storyВҰ19210\add*, вҖң\add That\add* HebrewВҰ19217 slaveВҰ19216 that youВҰ19220 broughtВҰ19220 \add into our home\add* cameВҰ19213 to me to \add mock\add* me,
\v 18 \add butВҰ19225\add* when IВҰ19226 yelledВҰ19228 out, he left his cloak here andВҰ19225 \add took off\add* outsideВҰ19233.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Joseph Put in Prison
\p
\v 19 WhenВҰ19235 Yosef's masterВҰ19237 heardВҰ19236 his wife tell what his slaveВҰ19251 \add had tried\add* to do to her, he \add became furious\add*.
\v 20 \add HeВҰ19257\add* took him andВҰ19255 threw him into the prison \add built\add* for the king's prisoners.
\v 21 \add ButВҰ19277\add* YahwehВҰ19278 was with YosefВҰ19281 and was kind to him and \add caused the prisonВҰ19291 warden to be pleased with him\add*,\x + \xo 39:21: \xt Acts 7:9.\x*
\v 22 \add so\add* the warden put him in charge of all the \add other\add* prisonersВҰ19304 andВҰ19308 \add YosefВҰ19300 ended up being in charge\add* of everything that happened inside.
\v 23 Then the warden didn't need to \add concern himself\add* with anythingВҰ19329 that was going onВҰ19331 because YahwehВҰ19332 was with \add Yosef\add* and helped him succeedВҰ19339 inВҰ19331 \add everything\add* he did.
\c 40
\s1 Yosef explains the dreams of two prisoners
\rem /s1 The Dreams of Two Prisoners; Joseph Interprets Two Dreams; The Cupbearer and the Baker; Joseph Interprets the Prisoners' Dreams
\p
\v 1 \add Sometime afterВҰ19343 that\add* the Egyptian king's cupbearer and bakerВҰ19351 sinnedВҰ19346 against theirВҰ19352 masterВҰ19352, \add also known as Far'oh\add*.
\v 2 Far'ohВҰ19357 was angryВҰ19356 at those twoВҰ19359 officialsВҰ19360
\v 3 andВҰ19368 he put them in the custodyВҰ19370 of the chief of the guardsВҰ19373вҖ”in the prisonВҰ19378 whereВҰ19380 YosefВҰ19381 was \add also being held\add*.
\v 4 \add There\add* the chief of the guardsВҰ19387 assignedВҰ19385 YosefВҰ19390 to serve them.
\p After they'd been inВҰ19396 custodyВҰ19396 for quite some time,
\v 5 the king's \add cupbearerВҰ19408 and bakerВҰ19409\add* inВҰ19403 prisonВҰ19416 each had \add separate\add* dreams onВҰ19403 the same nightВҰ19403, and each man's dream had its own interpretation.
\v 6 \add TheВҰ19423 next\add* morningВҰ19421, YosefВҰ19420 cameВҰ19418 to them, andВҰ19418 wowВҰ19424, theyВҰ19424 were worried,
\v 7 \add so\add* he askedВҰ19427 the \add two former\add* officialsВҰ19430 of Far'ohВҰ19431, вҖңWhyВҰ19428 are you looking so upset today?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңWe each had a dreamВҰ19445 last night,вҖқ theyВҰ19443 answered, вҖңbutВҰ19443 there'sВҰ19448 no one here who can tell us what our dreams mean.вҖқ
\p вҖңGodВҰ19454 is the only one who gives someone the ability to interpretВҰ19447 the meaning of dreams,вҖқ YosefВҰ19452 replied. вҖңPlease tell me what you dreamed.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ19461 the chiefВҰ19462 of the cupbearersВҰ19464 \add went first andВҰ19461\add* told his dream to YosefВҰ19468, вҖңListenВҰ19465, in myВҰ19475 dream there was a grapevineВҰ19474 in frontВҰ19475 of me
\v 10 withВҰ19477 threeВҰ19478 branches on it. ThenВҰ19477 as soon as the buds appeared \add on the branches\add*, its blossomsВҰ19483 came out \add straight away\add* andВҰ19477 its clustersВҰ19485 ripenedВҰ19484 into grapesВҰ19486.
\v 11 ThenВҰ19488 I was holding Far'oh's cup and I tookВҰ19491 the grapesВҰ19494 and squeezedВҰ19495 them into it and I gave the cup to Far'ohВҰ19489.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңThis is the interpretationВҰ19514,вҖқ YosefВҰ19512 respondedВҰ19510. вҖңThe three branchesВҰ19516 \add represent\add* three daysВҰ19518.
\v 13 Within threeВҰ19523 daysВҰ19524, Far'oh will \add display you publicly\add* and then restoreВҰ19530 you to your position. Then you'll place Far'oh's cup into his handВҰ19538, \add just like you used to before\add* when you were his cupbearerВҰ19543.
\v 14 ButВҰ19553 when itВҰ19551 \add all\add* goes well for you, if you rememberВҰ19548 me then pleaseВҰ19555 be kind and mentionВҰ19558 me to Far'ohВҰ19561 \add to\add* get me out of this \add prison\add*,
\v 15 because indeedВҰ19570 I was trafficked from the land of the HebrewsВҰ19573. And even here, I didn'tВҰ19577 do anythingВҰ19580 \add to deserve being held inВҰ19585 this\add* pit.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add Now when\add* the chiefВҰ19588 of the bakersВҰ19590 saw that \add this first dream was\add* interpretedВҰ19593 \add so\add* favourably, he told YosefВҰ19597, вҖңI also was inВҰ19601 my dream, andВҰ19587 listen, there were threeВҰ19603 basketsВҰ19604 of whiteВҰ19605 breadВҰ19605 onВҰ19601 my head.
\v 17 InВҰ19619 the top basket \add there\add* were \add various\add* kinds of food for Far'ohВҰ19614вҖ”baker'sВҰ19616 goodsвҖ”butВҰ19610 the birds were eatingВҰ19618 them out of the basket onВҰ19610 my head.вҖқ
\v 18 вҖңThis is the interpretationВҰ19630,вҖқ YosefВҰ19627 respondedВҰ19628. вҖңThe three basketsВҰ19632 are three daysВҰ19634.
\v 19 Within threeВҰ19639 daysВҰ19640, Far'ohВҰ19642 will \add display you publicly\add* and then impale you on a pole, and the birdsВҰ19653 will eatВҰ19652 your fleshВҰ19656 \add off your bones\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ19659 \add three days later\add*, \add it was Far'oh'sВҰ19668 birthday\add* and he held a feastВҰ19670 for all his officials and he got the chief of the cupbearersВҰ19680 and the chief of the bakersВҰ19685 \add brought in to stand publicly\add* in the middleВҰ19686 of \add everyone\add*.
\v 21 ThenВҰ19690 he restoredВҰ19689 the chiefВҰ19692 of the cupbearersВҰ19693 to his positionВҰ19696, andВҰ19689 \add the man carried\add* the cup \add across to\add* Far'ohВҰ19702,
\v 22 butВҰ19704 he had the chiefВҰ19705 of the bakersВҰ19706 executed, just like YosefВҰ19711 had \add described in the interpretationВҰ19709 of the dream\add*.
\v 23 \add HoweverВҰ19719,\add* the chiefВҰ19716 of the cupbearersВҰ19718 \add completely\add* forgotВҰ19722 about YosefВҰ19721.
\c 41
\s1 Yosef interprets the king's dreams
\rem /s1 Pharaoh's Dreams; Joseph Interprets Pharaoh's Dream; Joseph Interprets the King's Dreams
\p
\v 1 \add Some twoВҰ19727 yearsВҰ19727 later\add*, \add King\add* Far'ohВҰ19729 had a dreamВҰ19730 and \add in it\add*, he was standingВҰ19732 beside the Nile \add River\add*.
\v 2 ThenВҰ19740, wow, sevenВҰ19742 fine-looking and well-fed cows came up out of the river, and they grazedВҰ19748 among the reedsВҰ19749.
\v 3 \add ButВҰ19751\add* wow, sevenВҰ19752 ugly, skinny cows came up out of the river afterВҰ19756 them, andВҰ19751 they stoodВҰ19764 besideВҰ19765 the \add other\add* cows on the river bank.
\v 4 ThenВҰ19778 the ugly, skinny cows ateВҰ19772 the sevenВҰ19779 nice, fat cows, andВҰ19772 thenВҰ19772 Far'ohВҰ19785 woke up.
\v 5 ThenВҰ19787 he fell asleepВҰ19787 \add again\add* andВҰ19787 had a secondВҰ19789 dreamВҰ19788. And wow, sevenВҰ19792 goodВҰ19798, fat heads of grainВҰ19793 came up onВҰ19795 one stalkВҰ19795.
\v 6 \add ButВҰ19800\add* wow, sevenВҰ19801 thin heads of grain sprouted afterВҰ19807 themвҖ”these heads of grain had been scorchedВҰ19804 by the \add hot, desert\add* wind.
\v 7 ThenВҰ19809 the thin heads of grain swallowedВҰ19809 up the sevenВҰ19813 good, fat heads. \add AtВҰ19812 that point\add*, Far'ohВҰ19818 woke up, andВҰ19809 \add realised that\add* it had been a dreamВҰ19820.
\v 8 \add That\add* morningВҰ19823, Far'oh's spirit was troubled, so he sentВҰ19826 for all the sorcerers and wise men of EgyptВҰ19833 and \add he\add* told them his dreamsВҰ19844, butВҰ19822 no one could interpretВҰ19847 them for \add the king\add*.\x + \xo 41:8: \xt Dan 2:2.\x*
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ19851 the chiefВҰ19852 of the cupbearersВҰ19853 spokeВҰ19851 with Far'ohВҰ19856 saying, вҖңI'veВҰ19861 \add just\add* rememberedВҰ19862 my \add broken promise\add* today.
\v 10 \add The king\add* had been angryВҰ19866 withВҰ19872 his servantsВҰ19869, and he put me in the custodyВҰ19872 of the chief of the guardsВҰ19875 \add in his prison\add*вҖ”me and the chief of the bakersВҰ19879.
\v 11 \add TheВҰ19885 two of us each\add* had a dream \add one\add* nightВҰ19883, andВҰ19881 each of \add the dreams had different interpretations\add*.
\v 12 There was a youngВҰ19894 HebrewВҰ19895 man \add in thereВҰ19892\add* with usвҖ”a slaveВҰ19896 of the chief of the guardsВҰ19898. \add WhenВҰ19892\add* we told him our dreams, he interpreted our \add two different\add* dreams for us.
\v 13 And it \add all\add* happened just as he'd interpretedВҰ19915 \add them\add*вҖ”I was restoredВҰ19921 to my position andВҰ19913 \add the baker\add* was \add executed\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add SoВҰ19928\add* Far'ohВҰ19929 sent for YosefВҰ19933, and they quicklyВҰ19934 brought him \add in\add* from the pit. \add WhenВҰ19944\add* he'd shavedВҰ19938 and changedВҰ19939 his clothesВҰ19940, he \add was brought in\add* to \add the king\add*
\v 15 \add who told him\add*, вҖңI \add had\add* a dream butВҰ19946 no one could interpret it. \add However,\add* I heardВҰ19957 that you could listenВҰ19960 to a dream andВҰ19946 \add explain what it means\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add No, it's not my ability\add*,вҖқ YosefВҰ19966 responded, вҖң\add butВҰ19965\add* \em GodВҰ19972\em* will answerВҰ19973 \add the king to give him peace\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңIn my dreamВҰ19984,вҖқ Far'ohВҰ19980 told YosefВҰ19983, вҖңwowВҰ19985, I was standingВҰ19986 onВҰ19984 the river bank
\v 18 and thenВҰ19992 listen, up from the river came sevenВҰ19997 cows. \add TheyВҰ19995 were\add* well-fed and good-looking, and they grazedВҰ20003 among the reedsВҰ20004.
\v 19 ThenВҰ20006 listen, sevenВҰ20007 other cows came up afterВҰ20012 them. \add They were in\add* poor \add condition\add* and very ugly and skinnyвҖ”I haven't seenВҰ20021 cows that ugly \add anywhere in\add* EgyptВҰ20026.
\v 20 ThenВҰ20033 the skinny, ugly cows ateВҰ20029 the firstВҰ20036 sevenВҰ20034 fat cows,
\v 21 \add butВҰ20039\add* you wouldn't know itВҰ20044 because their bellies \add were just as skinny as before\add* andВҰ20039 they looked just as ugly as they had before. ThenВҰ20039 I woke up.
\p
\v 22 вҖңThenВҰ20057 I \add had another\add* dreamВҰ20058, and listen, sevenВҰ20061 heads of grainВҰ20062 came up onВҰ20058 one stalkВҰ20064. \add They were\add* full and goodВҰ20067.
\v 23 ThenВҰ20069 listen, sevenВҰ20070 \add more\add* heads of grainВҰ20071 sprouted afterВҰ20077 them, \add butВҰ20069 they were\add* witheredВҰ20072 and thin, and scorchedВҰ20074 by the east windВҰ20075.
\v 24 ThenВҰ20079 the thin heads of grain swallowedВҰ20079 up the sevenВҰ20084 goodВҰ20086 heads of grain. IВҰ20083 told \add these dreams\add* to the sorcerers, butВҰ20079 no one could explain \add them\add* to me.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ20095 YosefВҰ20096 saidВҰ20095 to Far'ohВҰ20099, вҖң\add The king's\add* dreamsВҰ20100 are one \add andВҰ20095 the same\add*. GodВҰ20106 has shown Far'oh what he's going to do.
\v 26 The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good heads of grain are seven yearsвҖ”\add both\add* dreamsВҰ20123 \add mean the same\add*.
\v 27 And the seven thin and ugly cows that came up afterВҰ20132 them are seven years, and so are the seven thin heads of grain scorchedВҰ20139 by the east windВҰ20140. There will be seven years of \add drought\add*.
\v 28 That's \add why\add* I told Far'ohВҰ20152 thatВҰ20148 GodВҰ20154 has shownВҰ20156 \add him\add* what he's going to do.
\v 29 Listen, there's sevenВҰ20162 yearsВҰ20163 coming of plentifulВҰ20165 \add harvests\add* throughout all of EgyptВҰ20170,
\v 30 \add butВҰ20172\add* sevenВҰ20173 years of \add drought\add* will \add follow\add* afterВҰ20177 them, \add such that the years of plenty will be quickly\add* forgottenВҰ20178 andВҰ20172 famine will \add devastate\add* the land.
\v 31 \add YesВҰ20201,\add* the \add time of plenty\add* won'tВҰ20190 be remembered because of the famineВҰ20196 \add that follows\add*вҖ”it'll be very \add severe\add*.
\v 32 And as for \add having twoВҰ20213 dreamsВҰ20209 with the same meaning\add*, it's because the matterВҰ20217 has been established by God, andВҰ20220 God will do it soon.
\p
\v 33 вҖңSoВҰ20224 now \add the king\add* shouldВҰ20225 find a manВҰ20227 who's discerningВҰ20228 and wise, and appoint him over \add all\add* EgyptВҰ20234.
\v 34 Then \add the king\add* should get himВҰ20236 to appointВҰ20238 supervisors \add all across the country\add* to collect twenty percent of the \add crops\add* during the sevenВҰ20248 yearsВҰ20249 of plenty.
\v 35 They should collect that \add surplus\add* food in the comingВҰ20260 goodВҰ20259 yearsВҰ20258, andВҰ20252 storeВҰ20262 it in the citiesВҰ20270 \add underВҰ20265 the king's authority\add*. It should be kept
\v 36 andВҰ20273 used as a reserveВҰ20275 for the sevenВҰ20277 yearsВҰ20278 of famine that will affect the country, so that the \add people\add* will survive.
\s1 Yosef becomes a ruler in Egypt
\rem /s1 Joseph's Rise to Power; Joseph Is Made Governor over Egypt; Joseph Made Ruler of Egypt
\p
\v 37 \add This idea sounded\add* goodВҰ20290 to Far'ohВҰ20293 andВҰ20294 to all his servantsВҰ20297,
\v 38 so he asked them, вҖң\add Do we have any other\add* manВҰ20306 like this who has God's spiritВҰ20308 in him?вҖқ
\v 39 ThenВҰ20312 he told YosefВҰ20316, вҖңSinceВҰ20313 GodВҰ20319 has shown you all this, there'sВҰ20326 no one as discerningВҰ20328 andВҰ20312 wise as you.
\v 40 You'll be over my householdВҰ20336, and all my peopleВҰ20343 will \add obey your every word\add*. Only I on the throne will be greaterВҰ20346 than you.вҖқ\x + \xo 41:40: \xt Acts 7:10.\x*
\rem /s1 Joseph in Charge of Egypt
\v 41 ThenВҰ20349 \add he added\add*, вҖңSee, I've put youВҰ20356 over all the \add entireВҰ20358 country\add*.вҖқ
\v 42 ThenВҰ20363 \add he\add* removedВҰ20363 his signetВҰ20367 ring from his hand and put it on Yosef's hand, and he had him dressed in fine linenВҰ20380 clothesВҰ20376, and put a goldВҰ20383 chainВҰ20382 around his neck.\x + \xo 41:42: \xt Dan 5:29.\x*
\v 43 He had \add Yosef\add* ride in hisВҰ20396 #2 chariotВҰ20390, andВҰ20388 they called out in frontВҰ20396 of him, вҖңBow down!вҖқ SoВҰ20388 \add the king\add* put him over the entireВҰ20401 \add country\add* of EgyptВҰ20404.
\v 44 Far'oh \add also\add* told \add him\add*, вҖңI'm Far'oh, andВҰ20406 no person in all EgyptВҰ20427 will lift their handВҰ20420 or footВҰ20423 withoutВҰ20413 \add yourВҰ20413 permission\add*.вҖқ
\v 45 ThenВҰ20429 Far'ohВҰ20430 gaveВҰ20436 him the Egyptian nameВҰ20431 вҖҳZafenathВҰ20434-PaneahВҰ20435вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳthe one who reveals secretsвҖҷ)\add*, andВҰ20429 he \add presented him with\add* AsenathВҰ20441, the daughterВҰ20442 of Potifera the priestВҰ20446 of On, as a wife. And YosefВҰ20433 \add travelled throughout\add* the land of EgyptВҰ20454.
\p
\v 46 YosefВҰ20456 was thirtyВҰ20459 years old when he'd \add been called to\add* stand before Far'oh kingВҰ20464 of Egypt. \add WhenВҰ20456 he left\add* Far'oh's presence, he travelledВҰ20471 throughout the land of Egypt
\v 47 andВҰ20478 the land producedВҰ20478 outstandingВҰ20483 harvestsВҰ20483 during the sevenВҰ20480 yearsВҰ20481 of plenty.
\v 48 For sevenВҰ20492 yearsВҰ20493, he gatheredВҰ20485 all the food throughout the land of EgyptВҰ20497 andВҰ20485 had it storedВҰ20498 inВҰ20501 the citiesВҰ20501. The food from the countrysideВҰ20503 that surrounded each city, he put inside \add that city\add*.
\v 49 \add SoВҰ20511\add* YosefВҰ20512 storedВҰ20511 up so much grainВҰ20513 \add that it was\add* like sand \add on the beaches\add*, untilВҰ20518 he \add eventually\add* stopped measuringВҰ20522 it because it \add too much to calculate\add*.
\p
\v 50 Before the years of the famineВҰ20535 cameВҰ20533, YosefВҰ20528 had twoВҰ20530 sonsВҰ20531 that AsenathВҰ20540 (the daughterВҰ20541 of Potifera, the priestВҰ20545 of On) gave birth to.
\v 51 YosefВҰ20549 named the oldest son вҖҳManassehВҰ20554вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳforgetвҖҷ)\add*, because he said, вҖңGodВҰ20558 has made me forget all my hardshipsВҰ20563 andВҰ20548 all of my family.вҖқ
\v 52 His secondВҰ20572 son he named вҖҳEfrayimВҰ20574вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳfruitfulвҖҷ)\add*, because he said, вҖңGodВҰ20578 has made me fruitful in the land of my difficulties.вҖқ
\p
\v 53 ThenВҰ20582 the sevenВҰ20583 yearsВҰ20584 of plenty in EgyptВҰ20589 cameВҰ20582 to an endВҰ20582
\v 54 andВҰ20591 the sevenВҰ20592 yearsВҰ20593 of famine started, just as YosefВҰ20598 had saidВҰ20597. The famine \add covered the entireВҰ20601 wider regionВҰ20606\add*, butВҰ20591 \add it was different in\add* EgyptВҰ20607.\x + \xo 41:54: \xt Acts 7:11.\x*
\v 55 All the land of EgyptВҰ20615 became famishedВҰ20611, and the peopleВҰ20617 criedВҰ20616 to \add the king\add* for food, so Far'ohВҰ20620 saidВҰ20622 to all the Egyptians, вҖңGo to YosefВҰ20630 \add and\add* do whatever he tells you.вҖқ\x + \xo 41:55: \xt Yhn 2:5.\x*
\v 56 The famine was \add right across the country\add*, so YosefВҰ20645 openedВҰ20644 all the grain stores andВҰ20637 sold grain to the Egyptians. \add ButВҰ20637\add* the famine in EgyptВҰ20657 was \add really\add* severeВҰ20654.
\v 57 ThenВҰ20659 \add people from much further away started\add* coming to EgyptВҰ20663 to buy grainВҰ20664 from YosefВҰ20667, because the famineВҰ20671 was severeВҰ20670 in the \add entireВҰ20659 wider region\add*.
\c 42
\s1 Yosef's brothers turn up in Egypt
\rem /s1 Joseph's Brothers Go to Egypt to Buy Grain; Joseph's Brothers Go to Egypt
\p
\v 1 \add Meanwhile (up in the Canaan region),\add* YacobВҰ20677 \add heard\add* that there was grainВҰ20681 \add available\add* in EgyptВҰ20682, so \add he\add* saidВҰ20683 to his sonsВҰ20685, вҖңWhy are youВҰ20687 \add just standing there\add* lookingВҰ20687 atВҰ20682 each other?
\v 2 Listen, I've heardВҰ20691 that \add they're selling\add* grainВҰ20695 inВҰ20696 EgyptВҰ20696. Go down there andВҰ20689 buy some for us so that weВҰ20706 \add won'tВҰ20705 just starve to death here\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 42:2: \xt Acts 7:12.\x*
\v 3 \add SoВҰ20708\add* tenВҰ20712 of Yosef'sВҰ20711 brothersВҰ20709 \add travelled\add* down to EgyptВҰ20715 to buy grainВҰ20714,
\v 4 \add butВҰ20717\add* YacobВҰ20725 wouldn't send BenyaminВҰ20719 (Yosef's \add youngest\add* brotherВҰ20720) with \add the others\add*, because he saidВҰ20730, вҖңI don'tВҰ20722 want any harm to comeВҰ20733 to him.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add SoВҰ20736\add* Yisra'el'sВҰ20738 sonsВҰ20737 \add found themselves\add* among \add many others\add* who \add wentВҰ20741\add* to buy grainВҰ20739, because the famineВҰ20745 was \add also throughout\add* the CanaanВҰ20747 \add regionВҰ20746\add*.
\v 6 \add Now\add* Yosef was the governorВҰ20751 over \add all of Egypt\add* and he \add was the one there\add* who was selling grain to all the peopleВҰ20759. SoВҰ20749 Yosef's brothersВҰ20762 \add approached\add* and bowedВҰ20764 down to him with their noses to the groundВҰ20768.
\v 7 \add WhenВҰ20770\add* YosefВҰ20771 sawВҰ20770 his brothersВҰ20774, he recognizedВҰ20775 them and acted like a strangerВҰ20776 to them, and he spokeВҰ20778 harshlyВҰ20780 with them \add (through an interpreter)\add*, вҖңWhere \add are youВҰ20784 lot from\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңFrom the land of CanaanВҰ20787 to buy food,вҖқ theyВҰ20785 \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 8 YosefВҰ20793 had recognised his brothersВҰ20796, butВҰ20792 theyВҰ20797 hadn't recognised himВҰ20799,
\v 9 andВҰ20801 \add just thenВҰ20801\add* he rememberedВҰ20801 the dreamsВҰ20804 thatВҰ20805 he had dreamed about them, \add so\add* he saidВҰ20808 to them, вҖңYou are spiesВҰ20810. You've \add all\add* comeВҰ20817 to \add discover any weak points in this country's defences\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 42:9: \xt Gen 37:5-10.\x*
\p
\v 10 вҖңNo, my masterВҰ20822,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңYour servantsВҰ20823 have \add only\add* comeВҰ20824 to buy food.
\v 11 We're \add all\add* sonsВҰ20830 of \add the same\add* manВҰ20831. We're \add being\add* honestВҰ20835. Your servantsВҰ20840 are not spiesВҰ20841.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңNo, you've definitely \add all\add* comeВҰ20850 \add here\add* to seeВҰ20851 \add where our land is vulnerable\add*,вҖқ \add Yosef insisted\add*.
\p
\v 13 вҖңYour servantsВҰ20856 are twelve brothersВҰ20857,вҖқ theyВҰ20853 protested. вҖңWe're \add all\add* sonsВҰ20860 of one manВҰ20861 in the CanaanВҰ20865 \add regionВҰ20864\add*. \add It's all true\add*вҖ”the youngest is \add home\add* with our fatherВҰ20870, andВҰ20853 one \add has passed away\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add Yes,\add* it's just as I said,вҖқ retorted YosefВҰ20877. вҖңYou're spiesВҰ20883!
\v 15 \add But\add* this is how we'll test you all: On Far'oh's lifeВҰ20888, you won't \add ever\add* leave this place unless your youngest brotherВҰ20898 comesВҰ20897 here.
\v 16 \add Select\add* one among you to go and get yourВҰ20903 brotherВҰ20908, and \add the rest of\add* you will be \add imprisonedВҰ20910\add*. Then \add we'll find out if you've all been telling the truthВҰ20913\add*. And if not, on Far'oh's lifeВҰ20918, you're certainly spiesВҰ20921.вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ20925 he had them \add locked up\add* togetherВҰ20924 for threeВҰ20929 daysВҰ20930.
\p
\v 18 On the thirdВҰ20936 dayВҰ20935, YosefВҰ20934 told them, вҖңI'm a man who reveres GodВҰ20942. SoВҰ20932 if you do \add exactly\add* what I say, I'll let you liveВҰ20939.
\v 19 If you are \add actually\add* honestВҰ20948, leave one of your brothersВҰ20950 \add in prisonВҰ20954 here\add*, and you \add others\add* goВҰ20956 and takeВҰ20957 grainВҰ20958 back \add to feed\add* your families.
\v 20 ThenВҰ20962 \add when\add* you will bringВҰ20966 me your youngest brotherВҰ20964 so that \add I can verifyВҰ20968 your statements\add*, thenВҰ20962 you won'tВҰ20970 dieВҰ20971.вҖқ SoВҰ20962 theyВҰ20972 \add agreed\add*,
\v 21 saying to each other \add (inВҰ20992 Hebrew)\add*, вҖңWe are truly guiltyВҰ20982 concerning our brotherВҰ20987 \add Yosef\add*, because we sawВҰ20989 the distress of his soulВҰ20991 when he pleadedВҰ20992 withВҰ20992 us, butВҰ20976 we didn'tВҰ20994 \add take any notice\add*. \add That's why\add* this \add predicament has happened to\add* us.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңDidn't I \add beg\add* you \add all\add* not to sinВҰ21015 against the lad?вҖқ ReubenВҰ21005 spoke up. вҖңButВҰ21004 you wouldn't listenВҰ21018, so now, see, \add now we're having to account for\add* his bloodВҰ21021.вҖқ\x + \xo 42:22: \xt Gen 37:21-22.\x*
\v 23 (\add ButВҰ21025\add* they didn'tВҰ21026 know that YosefВҰ21030 understood them, because \add he andВҰ21025 them had been speaking through an interpreterВҰ21032\add*.)
\v 24 \add Yosef\add* turned away from them \add briefly so they couldn't see his tears\add*, thenВҰ21035 he turned back toward them and spokeВҰ21040 to them. ThenВҰ21035 he had SimeonВҰ21046 \add separated\add* from \add the group\add* and tied up in front of them.
\v 25 ThenВҰ21051 YosefВҰ21052 ordered \add his servants\add* and they filled their bags with grainВҰ21057, and he \add quietly\add* ordered them to returnВҰ21058 each man's silver \add back\add* to his sack and to giveВҰ21064 them provisions to them for the road.
\s1 Yosef's brothers return home
\rem /s1 Joseph's Brothers Return to Canaan
\p \add After Yosef had provided for his brothers\add*,
\v 26 they loadedВҰ21072 their grainВҰ21075 onto their donkeysВҰ21078 andВҰ21072 departedВҰ21079.
\v 27 At a lodgingВҰ21090 placeВҰ21090 \add that night\add*, one \add of them\add* openedВҰ21082 his sack to feed his donkeyВҰ21089 andВҰ21082 \add to his horror\add*, he sawВҰ21091 his silver inside the top of the sack.
\v 28 вҖңMy silver's been returnedВҰ21105,вҖқ heВҰ21121 told his brothersВҰ21104, вҖңandВҰ21101 it's \add right here\add* inВҰ21109 my sack!вҖқ ThenВҰ21101 theirВҰ21111 \add вүҲstomachs tightened\add*, and tremblingВҰ21112, they \add вүҲasked\add* each other, вҖңWhat's this that God's doing to us?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \add WhenВҰ21125\add* they \add got home\add* to YacobВҰ21128 theirВҰ21129 fatherВҰ21129 in CanaanВҰ21131, they told him everything that had happenedВҰ21137 to them,
\v 30 вҖң\add This\add* manВҰ21142, the masterВҰ21143 of \add Egypt\add*, spokeВҰ21141 harshlyВҰ21146 to us and treated us as if we were spyingВҰ21149 out \add his country\add*,
\v 31 butВҰ21154 we told him, вҖҳWe're honestВҰ21156вҖ”we're not spiesВҰ21160.
\v 32 We're twelve brothersВҰ21166, the sons of our father. One is \add no longer\add* alive, and the youngestВҰ21171 is with our father today \add back\add* in CanaanВҰ21177.вҖҷ
\v 33 ThenВҰ21179 \add that\add* manВҰ21181 told us, вҖҳ\add I'll find out if you're honestВҰ21187\add*: Leave one of your brothersВҰ21189 withВҰ21184 me, and takeВҰ21197 grain for your families and goВҰ21198.
\v 34 Then bringВҰ21200 me your youngest brother so that I'll know you're not spiesВҰ21209вҖ”that you're \add telling the truth\add*. Then I'll \add release\add* your brother andВҰ21200 you can trade \add here freely\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ21224 \add when\add* they \add started\add* emptyingВҰ21226 their sacksВҰ21227, wow, each man's pouch of silver was inside his sack. \add WhenВҰ21236 the brothers\add* andВҰ21224 their fatherВҰ21241 sawВҰ21235 their pouches of silver, they were afraid.
\v 36 вҖңYou've \add deprived\add* me \add of another son\add*,вҖқ YacobВҰ21246 \add exclaimed\add*. YosefВҰ21250 is \add gone\add*! Simeon'sВҰ21252 \add gone\add*! And \add thenВҰ21244 you want to takeВҰ21257\add* BenyaminВҰ21256 \add as well\add*! \add Why's everything going so wrong for\add* me?вҖқ
\v 37 ThenВҰ21262 ReubenВҰ21263 \add offered\add* to his fatherВҰ21266, вҖңYou can killВҰ21272 my twoВҰ21270 sonsВҰ21271 if I don'tВҰ21275 bringВҰ21276 \add Benyamin back\add* to you. \add Let me take responsibility for him\add*, andВҰ21262 I'll \add make sure that he\add* returnsВҰ21284 to you.вҖқ
\v 38 вҖңMy son will \em not\em* go withВҰ21302 you,вҖқ Yacob countered, вҖңbecause his brother is dead, andВҰ21287 he aloneВҰ21298 is left. And if harm were to meet him on the road thatВҰ21303 you're going on, thenВҰ21287 you'd bringВҰ21307 my gray head down to the grave inВҰ21302 grief.вҖқ
\c 43
\s1 Yosef's brothers bring Benyamin to Egypt
\rem /s1 Joseph's Brothers Return to Egypt with Benjamin; The Brothers Come Again, Bringing Benjamin; The Brothers Return to Egypt; The Second Journey to Egypt
\p
\v 1 \add However,\add* the famineВҰ21314 in the region was \add still\add* very severe,
\v 2 \add so\add* when they'd \add used up all\add* the grainВҰ21324 thatВҰ21325 they'd broughtВҰ21326 from EgyptВҰ21327, theirВҰ21330 fatherВҰ21330 \add instructed\add* them, вҖңGoВҰ21322 back \add there andВҰ21328\add* buy \add some\add* food for us.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add ButВҰ21339\add* YehudahВҰ21341 \add challenged\add* him, вҖң\add That\add* manВҰ21346 \add вүҲtold us that he won'tВҰ21348 even seeВҰ21350 us\add* unless \add our\add* brotherВҰ21353 is withВҰ21345 \add us\add*.
\v 4 WeВҰ21360 can \add only\add* goВҰ21364 \add there\add* to buy food for you if you'll \add agree to\add* send ourВҰ21362 \add youngest\add* brotherВҰ21362 with us.
\v 5 IfВҰ21375 you don'tВҰ21371, \add it's not even worth going, because that\add* manВҰ21377 \add clearly told us that he won'tВҰ21371 even seeВҰ21382 us\add* unless \add our\add* brotherВҰ21385 is with \add us\add*.
\p
\v 6 вҖңWhy did you all treat me badly by telling the manВҰ21394 you have \add a younger\add* brotherВҰ21397?вҖқ \add their father\add* Yisra'el asked.
\p
\v 7 вҖңThe man \add kept asking\add* aboutВҰ21405 us andВҰ21399 our relatives,вҖқ they answered. вҖң\add He asked\add*, вҖҳIs your fatherВҰ21408 stillВҰ21407 alive? Do you have another brother?вҖҷ \add We just answered what he asked\add*. How could we possibly know that he would \add insist that we bringВҰ21426 our youngest brother thereВҰ21410\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ21431 YehudahВҰ21432 saidВҰ21431 to his fatherВҰ21436, вҖң\add EntrustВҰ21435\add* the young man to me, and we'll \add pack\add* up and goВҰ21441 so that both we and youВҰ21450 and our littleВҰ21453 ones will liveВҰ21442 and not dieВҰ21444.
\v 9 I myself will guarantee him. \add If anything happens to him, you can charge it to me\add*. If I don'tВҰ21461 \add get\add* him \add safely\add* back to you, then I'll \add personally\add* carry the blameВҰ21466 \add for the rest of myВҰ21457 life\add*.
\v 10 \add IfВҰ21475 we hadn't sat around here doing nothing for so long\add*, certainly by now we could have \add been there and back\add* twice!вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add Well, if that's our only choice\add*,вҖқ theirВҰ21485 fatherВҰ21485 \add acceded\add*, вҖңthenВҰ21482 do this: Take some of the best produceВҰ21494 \add from around here\add* inВҰ21496 your bags, and take it down to the manВҰ21498 as a giftВҰ21499: a little balm, a little honeyВҰ21503, spicesВҰ21504 and myrrhВҰ21505, \add and some\add* pistachioВҰ21506 nuts and almondsВҰ21507.
\v 12 And take doubleВҰ21510 the \add amount of\add* silver, because you must repay the silver that was returnedВҰ21516 inВҰ21512 the \add tops\add* of yourВҰ21512 sacksВҰ21518. Perhaps it was a mistakeВҰ21522.
\v 13 SoВҰ21525 takeВҰ21528 yourВҰ21527 brotherВҰ21527 and \add goВҰ21530 and\add* return to the manВҰ21533.
\v 14 May the provider GodВҰ21535 Almighty \add cause\add* the manВҰ21541 to treat you kindly, and may he send your otherВҰ21547 brotherВҰ21546 and BenyaminВҰ21550 \add back\add* with you. And \add as for me\add*, if I \add lose another son\add*, I'll \add just have to mourn him\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add SoВҰ21556\add* the \add brothers\add* took the gifts and doubleВҰ21562 the \add amount of\add* silver. ThenВҰ21556 \add taking\add* BenyaminВҰ21569, they \add travelled\add* down to EgyptВҰ21572 and \add presentedВҰ21560 themselves\add* to YosefВҰ21575.
\v 16 \add WhenВҰ21577\add* YosefВҰ21578 saw BenyaminВҰ21582 with them, he told \add his head house-servant\add*, вҖңTake \add these\add* men to the house, and slaughter an animal and prepareВҰ21595 a meal, because \add they'll\add* eat with me atВҰ21600 noon.вҖқ
\v 17 The man did what \add he'd\add* been instructed andВҰ21602 broughtВҰ21607 the men to Yosef's houseВҰ21612.
\p
\v 18 \add ButВҰ21615\add* the \add brothers\add* were afraidВҰ21615 when they \add found out that they'd been\add* brought to \add wait outside\add* Yosef's houseВҰ21619, and said \add to each other\add*, вҖңWe must have been brought \add here\add* because of the silver that was returnedВҰ21626 inВҰ21627 our sacksВҰ21627 the firstВҰ21628 timeВҰ21628. \add He wants to overpower us, thenВҰ21615 arrest\add* us and \add confiscate\add* our donkeysВҰ21640 and take us as slavesВҰ21637.вҖқ
\rem /s1 A Feast at Joseph's Palace
\v 19 \add SoВҰ21650\add* they approached the \add head servant\add* andВҰ21651 spokeВҰ21651 to him at the entranceВҰ21653 of the houseВҰ21654,
\v 20 \add explaining\add*, вҖңPlease, my masterВҰ21658, honestly, weВҰ21660 cameВҰ21660 down here the firstВҰ21661 timeВҰ21661 to buy food.
\v 21 \add ButВҰ21666\add* when we \add got\add* to \add our\add* lodgingВҰ21672 placeВҰ21672 \add that evening\add*, we openedВҰ21673 our sacksВҰ21676 andВҰ21666 \add got a shock because\add* each man's silver was inВҰ21681 the \add top\add* of his sackвҖ”the full amount of our silver was there. SoВҰ21666 we've broughtВҰ21685 it back \add here onВҰ21681 this trip\add*,
\v 22 plus we've broughtВҰ21691 more silver to buy food. We don'tВҰ21696 knowВҰ21697 who put \add that\add* silver inВҰ21692 ourВҰ21692 sacksВҰ21702.вҖқ
\v 23 \add ButВҰ21704\add* he saidВҰ21704, вҖңPeace to youвҖ”don'tВҰ21707 be afraid. Your god andВҰ21704 the god of your fatherВҰ21712 has given you hiddenВҰ21715 treasureВҰ21715 inВҰ21716 your sacksВҰ21716вҖ”\add I received your previous payment\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ21704 he broughtВҰ21720 SimeonВҰ21724 out to them.
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ21726 the \add servant\add* took the \add brothers\add* into Yosef'sВҰ21732 houseВҰ21731. He \add had\add* waterВҰ21735 \add given to them\add* and they washedВҰ21736 their feetВҰ21737, and he \add had\add* fodderВҰ21739 \add given\add* to their donkeysВҰ21740.
\v 25 ThenВҰ21743 they \add got theirs gifts ready\add* for when YosefВҰ21749 would arrive atВҰ21750 midday, because they'd heardВҰ21752 that they would \add be given lunch\add* thereВҰ21755.
\v 26 \add WhenВҰ21764\add* YosefВҰ21760 \add arrived there\add*, they broughtВҰ21762 \add their gifts\add* andВҰ21759 they bowedВҰ21771 to the groundВҰ21774 \add inВҰ21769 front of him\add*.
\v 27 ThenВҰ21776 he askedВҰ21776 them about their \add living situation at home\add* andВҰ21776 \add questioned\add*, вҖңIs everything ok for your elderly fatherВҰ21781 that you \add вүҲtold me\add* about? Is he stillВҰ21785 aliveВҰ21786?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖңThings are well for yourВҰ21790 servantВҰ21790 our fatherВҰ21791. \add And yes,\add* he's stillВҰ21792 aliveВҰ21793.вҖқ ThenВҰ21788 theyВҰ21788 bowed their headsВҰ21794 andВҰ21788 bowed \add to the ground again\add*.
\p
\v 29 Then \add Yosef looked around\add* and saw his full-brother BenyaminВҰ21805, and asked, вҖңIs this your youngest brother that you spokeВҰ21815 to me about?вҖқ Then he said, вҖңMay GodВҰ21818 be graciousВҰ21819 to you, my son.вҖқ
\v 30 \add AtВҰ21824 that point, YosefВҰ21823 had to\add* hurry out \add of the room\add*, because \add he was so overcome with emotionВҰ21827 for his younger\add* brother that he needed to cry, \add so\add* he wentВҰ21833 to \add his\add* inner room andВҰ21822 cried thereВҰ21836.
\v 31 ThenВҰ21838 he washedВҰ21838 his face and came out, controllingВҰ21841 himself and \add ordering\add*, вҖңServe the meal.вҖқ
\v 32 \add SoВҰ21846 the servants\add* served \add Yosef at his own table\add*, and served \add the brothers separately\add* and the Egyptians who were eatingВҰ21852 with him \add separately again\add* (because Egyptians won'tВҰ21856 eatВҰ21859 \add together\add* with HebrewsВҰ21862, because Egyptians \add would find that demeaning\add*).
\v 33 \add At their table, the brothers were astonished to discover\add* that theyВҰ21870 had been seated in order from the oldest to the youngestВҰ21874.
\v 34 ThenВҰ21883 they were servedВҰ21883 food \add Yosef's table\add*, butВҰ21883 Benyamin'sВҰ21890 serving was fiveВҰ21893 times larger than any of \add the others\add*, and they drankВҰ21895 and they and \add Yosef all\add* got a bit tiddly.
\c 44
\s1 Yosef frames Benyamin for theft
\rem /s1 The Missing Cup; Joseph's Silver Cup; Joseph Detains Benjamin; A Silver Cup in a Sack
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ21899 \add Yosef commandedВҰ21899 his head servant\add*, вҖңFill the men'sВҰ21911 sacksВҰ21910 withВҰ21920 grain, as much as they are able to carryВҰ21915, andВҰ21916 put each man's \add payment back into the top\add* of his sack.
\v 2 AndВҰ21937 put my \add own\add* silver cup inВҰ21929 the \add top\add* of the youngest one's sack \add along withВҰ21929 his payment\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ21923 he did \add what he was instructed\add*.
\v 3 The \add next\add* morningВҰ21941 at daylight, the \add brothers\add* and their donkeysВҰ21946 were sentВҰ21944 off \add to start their trip home\add*.
\v 4 They hadn't gone very far out of the cityВҰ21952 \add when\add* YosefВҰ21955 \add вүҲtold his head servant\add*, вҖңGet up and, follow afterВҰ21963 \add those\add* menВҰ21964. When you overtakeВҰ21965 them, \add ask\add* them, вҖҳWhy did you repay goodВҰ21972 with evilВҰ21970?
\v 5 Isn't this \add the cup that\add* my masterВҰ21978 drinksВҰ21977 from and indeedВҰ21981, what he divinesВҰ21981 with? You've done evilВҰ21984 \add taking that\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add SoВҰ21991 the servant\add* overtookВҰ21988 them andВҰ21989 \add did exactly what he'd been instructed to do\add*.
\v 7 ButВҰ21996 they \add asked\add* him, вҖңWhy does my masterВҰ22000 \add say that\add*? Far be it from your servantsВҰ22004 to do something like that.
\v 8 \add Listen\add*, we broughtВҰ22015 the silver thatВҰ22011 we foundВҰ22012 inВҰ22013 the \add top\add* of our sacksВҰ22014 back to you from the land of CanaanВҰ22018. So \add why\add* would we \add then\add* stealВҰ22020 silver or goldВҰ22025 from the houseВҰ22021 of your masterВҰ22022?
\v 9 If you find \add anything stolen with any of us\add*, \add that person can be executed\add*, and \add the rest of us can also be taken as\add* slavesВҰ22037 for my masterВҰ22036.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңIndeed,вҖқ the \add servant replied\add*, вҖңaccording to your wordsВҰ22043, \add that's how\add* it'll be: whoever is foundВҰ22048 with \add the stolen cup\add* will become my slaveВҰ22053, \add butВҰ22039\add* you others will be \add free to go\add*.вҖқ
\v 11 SoВҰ22061 each \add of the brothers\add* quicklyВҰ22058 loweredВҰ22059 his sack to the groundВҰ22064, andВҰ22058 each one openedВҰ22065 his sack.
\v 12 ThenВҰ22069 \add Yosef's servant\add* searchedВҰ22069 beginning with the oldestВҰ22070 and ending with the youngestВҰ22072, and the cup was foundВҰ22074 inВҰ22070 Benyamin'sВҰ22077 sack.
\v 13 \add Seeing this, the brothers\add* tore their clothesВҰ22080 \add (as a sign of their distress)\add*, and each one loadedВҰ22081 up his donkeyВҰ22085, and they \add all\add* returnedВҰ22086 to the cityВҰ22087.
\p
\v 14 \add WhenВҰ22089\add* YehudahВҰ22090 and his brothersВҰ22091 \add got\add* to Yosef'sВҰ22093 houseВҰ22092, he was stillВҰ22095 thereВҰ22096, and they fell \add to their knees and bowed\add* to the groundВҰ22099 in front of him.
\v 15 вҖңWhat's this that you've done?вҖқ YosefВҰ22103 \add demanded\add*. вҖңDidn't you knowВҰ22111 that a manВҰ22116 like me can certainly divineВҰ22114 \add the truth\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңWhat can we say to my master?вҖқ YehudahВҰ22121 \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңWhat \add words\add* could we speakВҰ22128? How could we \add possibly\add* justifyВҰ22131 ourselvesВҰ22131? GodВҰ22132 has exposed the sin of your servantsВҰ22137. \add SoВҰ22120 now\add*, we are slavesВҰ22139 for my masterвҖ”both we andВҰ22120 the one who was found with the cup.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңFar be it from me to do that.вҖқ Yosef \add corrected them\add*. вҖң\add Only\add* the manВҰ22156 who had the cup will become my slaveВҰ22165, andВҰ22151 \add the rest of\add* you can goВҰ22167 \add back\add* to your fatherВҰ22171 in peaceВҰ22168.вҖқ
\s1 Yehudah pleads to Yosef
\rem /s1 Judah Speaks for His Brothers; Judah Pleads for Benjamin's Release; Judah Pleads for Benjamin
\p
\v 18 Then YehudahВҰ22176 went closer to \add Yosef\add* and said \add quietly\add*, вҖңPlease, my master, pleaseВҰ22182 let your servant speakВҰ22180 a word inВҰ22185 my master's earsВҰ22185, and don'tВҰ22187 \add get angry withВҰ22185 me\add*, since you're \add as powerful as\add* Far'ohВҰ22194.
\v 19 MyВҰ22198 masterВҰ22196 \add previously\add* askedВҰ22197 his servantsВҰ22200 \add if we had\add* a fatherВҰ22205 or another brotherВҰ22208?
\v 20 And we answered to my masterВҰ22213, вҖҳ\add Yes,\add* we have an elderly father and \add also\add* the youngestВҰ22221 son of his old age. ButВҰ22210 \add that son's\add* brotherВҰ22222 is dead, so he \add aloneВҰ22226 is left of his mother'sВҰ22227 childrenВҰ22219\add*, and his father lovesВҰ22229 him.вҖҷ
\v 21 ThenВҰ22231 you told yourВҰ22234 servantsВҰ22234, вҖҳBring \add the other son here so I can see\add* himВҰ22235 \add myself\add*.вҖҷ
\v 22 And we said to my masterВҰ22244, вҖҳThe young man isn'tВҰ22245 able to leave his father, because if he \add does\add*, thenВҰ22241 \add the old man\add* will die.вҖҷ
\v 23 ButВҰ22259 \add thenВҰ22259\add* you saidВҰ22259 to your servantsВҰ22262, вҖҳIf your youngest brotherВҰ22267 doesn't comeВҰ22266 with you, you won'tВҰ22265 \add get access to me\add* againВҰ22271.вҖҷ
\p
\v 24 вҖң\add AfterВҰ22285 all that,\add* when we wentВҰ22277 \add back\add* to your servantВҰ22280 my fatherВҰ22281, we explained your wordsВҰ22286 to him, my masterВҰ22287.
\v 25 \add Eventually,\add* ourВҰ22290 fatherВҰ22290 \add вүҲtold us\add*, вҖҳReturn \add there to\add* buy \add some\add* food for us.вҖҷ
\v 26 ButВҰ22299 we \add вүҲtold him\add*, вҖҳWe can'tВҰ22300 go \add back unless\add* our youngest brother is with us, because we wouldn't be able to \add get access to that\add* man if our youngest brother wasn't with us.вҖҷ
\v 27 ThenВҰ22322 yourВҰ22323 servantВҰ22323 my fatherВҰ22324 told us, вҖҳYou knowВҰ22327 that my wifeВҰ22333 gave birth to twoВҰ22329 sonsВҰ22329 for me.
\v 28 \add One of them\add* wentВҰ22335 away from me, and I've \add assumed that\add* he was torn to piecesВҰ22341, and I've never seenВҰ22343 him \add again\add*.
\v 29 SoВҰ22348 if you also takeВҰ22348 this \add son away\add* andВҰ22348 \add something happened to\add* himВҰ22356, thenВҰ22348 you'd bringВҰ22358 myВҰ22355 gray head down to \add the grave\add* inВҰ22362 misery.вҖҷ
\p
\v 30 вҖң\add SoВҰ22365\add* now, \add if IВҰ22366 was to return home\add* to yourВҰ22369 servantВҰ22369 my father \add without that\add* young man, since his \add father's\add* soul is boundВҰ22375 to his soul,
\v 31 then \add as soon as\add* he seesВҰ22379 that the young man isn'tВҰ22382 \add will us\add*, then he'll \add have a heart attack\add* andВҰ22378 \add so\add* your servantsВҰ22386 will bringВҰ22385 the gray head of your servantВҰ22390 our fatherВҰ22391 down to \add the grave\add* inВҰ22392 misery.
\v 32 \add ButВҰ22409\add* your servantВҰ22396 guaranteed the young man to my father, saying, вҖҳIf I don'tВҰ22406 \add get\add* him back to you, then I will have sinned against my father all \add my life\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 33 вҖң\add SoВҰ22415\add* now, pleaseВҰ22418 let yourВҰ22419 servantВҰ22419 stay as a slaveВҰ22422 for my masterВҰ22423 instead of the young man, andВҰ22424 let the young man goВҰ22425 \add home\add* with his brothersВҰ22428.
\v 34 \add So now,\add* how could I \add possibly\add* go \add home\add* to my father if \add thatВҰ22443\add* young man isn'tВҰ22438 with me? I \add wouldn't be able to cope with\add* my father's miseryВҰ22442.вҖқ
\c 45
\s1 Yosef reveals himself to his brothers
\rem /s1 Joseph Tells His Brothers Who He Is; Joseph Reveals Himself to His Brothers; Joseph Makes Himself Known; Joseph Reveals His Identity
\p
\v 1 \add By now,\add* Yosef wasn't able to controlВҰ22453 himself \add inВҰ22468 front of everyone who was standing around\add*, andВҰ22449 he calledВҰ22457 out, вҖң\add Send everyone else out!\add*вҖқ \add SoВҰ22449 Yosef was alone when he\add* revealed himself to his brothersВҰ22472,\x + \xo 45:1: \xt Acts 7:13.\x*
\v 2 \add butВҰ22474\add* he cried so loudly that \add many\add* Egyptians heardВҰ22479 \add it\add* andВҰ22474 Far'oh's householdВҰ22482 listenedВҰ22481.
\v 3 вҖңI'm YosefВҰ22486!вҖқ he told his brothers. вҖңIs my fatherВҰ22493 stillВҰ22492 alive?вҖқ ButВҰ22485 his brothers weren't able to answerВҰ22499 him because they were terrifiedВҰ22502 \add there in front of him\add*.
\v 4 вҖңPlease come close to me,вҖқ he said. \add SoВҰ22505\add* they cameВҰ22514 close, andВҰ22505 he \add explained\add*, вҖңI'm your brotherВҰ22518 YosefВҰ22506 that you sold \add to be taken to\add* EgyptВҰ22523.
\v 5 \add ButВҰ22537\add* don'tВҰ22527 be upset now or troubled that you sold me here, because \add itВҰ22532 was\add* GodВҰ22542 \add who\add* sentВҰ22541 me aheadВҰ22543 of you \add so that lives would be saved\add*.
\v 6 There's \add already\add* been two years of famineВҰ22549 inВҰ22550 this region, \add butВҰ22552\add* there'sВҰ22556 still five more years to come without any ploughing or harvestingВҰ22559.
\v 7 \add So\add* GodВҰ22563 sentВҰ22562 me aheadВҰ22564 of you all \add so that some of you would be kept aliveВҰ22569 by this miracle and yourВҰ22564 children would be\add* preservedВҰ22565.
\v 8 \add You see\add*, it wasn't you who sentВҰ22578 me here, butВҰ22574 GodВҰ22582. And he's made me \add like a\add* fatherВҰ22584 to Far'ohВҰ22585, and masterВҰ22586 over all his houseВҰ22589 and the rulerВҰ22590 in all the land of EgyptВҰ22594.
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add So\add* hurry \add back\add* to my fatherВҰ22600 and tell him, вҖҳThis is what yourВҰ22605 son YosefВҰ22606 saysВҰ22604, вҖңGodВҰ22608 has made me masterВҰ22609 over all EgyptВҰ22612. Come down to meвҖ”don'tВҰ22615 delayВҰ22617.\x + \xo 45:9-11: \xt Acts 7:14.\x*
\v 10 You can live inВҰ22620 the GoshenВҰ22622 regionВҰ22620 so that you'll be near to meвҖ”you and your children and your children's children and your flocksВҰ22630 and your herdsВҰ22631 and everything that belongs to you.
\v 11 I'll provideВҰ22638 for you \add here\add* because there'sВҰ22640 stillВҰ22643 fiveВҰ22644 yearsВҰ22645 of famineВҰ22646 \add to come\add*. \add That way\add*, you won't \add end up poor\add*вҖ”you and your householdВҰ22651 and \add everyone with\add* you.вҖқ вҖҷ
\v 12 \add Look at me!\add* You \add yourselves\add* andВҰ22661 \add even\add* my brotherВҰ22662 BenyaminВҰ22663 \add can\add* see that it's \add really me who's\add* speakingВҰ22667 to youВҰ22668.
\v 13 \add SoВҰ22670 go and\add* tell my father about all my \add very high position\add* inВҰ22677 EgyptВҰ22677 and everything \add else\add* that you've seen. ThenВҰ22670 hurryВҰ22683 and bringВҰ22684 my father down here.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ22690 he \add hugged\add* his brother Benyamin and cried, and Benyamin cried \add too while they hugged\add*.
\v 15 ThenВҰ22704 he kissedВҰ22704 all his brothers and cried over them, and afterВҰ22710 that his brothers talked with him.
\rem /s1 Pharaoh Invites Jacob to Egypt
\p
\v 16 \add WhenВҰ22716\add* the report about the arrival of Yosef's brothersВҰ22722 \add reached\add* Far'oh's houseВҰ22718, both him andВҰ22716 his servantsВҰ22728 \add were pleasedВҰ22724\add*.
\v 17 ThenВҰ22730 Far'ohВҰ22731 \add instructed\add* YosefВҰ22734, вҖңTell your brothersВҰ22738, вҖҳDo this: Load your animalsВҰ22744 andВҰ22730 leave. Go to CanaanВҰ22749
\v 18 and get your fatherВҰ22754 and your householdsВҰ22757, and comeВҰ22758 \add back here\add* to me, and I'll giveВҰ22760 to you the best of the land in EgyptВҰ22766, and you'll eatВҰ22767 the \add best\add* of the \add country\add*.вҖҷ
\v 19 And you'reВҰ22774 commandedВҰ22774, вҖҳDo this: Take cartsВҰ22782 with you from \add here\add* for your littleВҰ22783 ones and for your wivesВҰ22784, and get your fatherВҰ22788 and comeВҰ22789.
\v 20 Don't \add be upset about anything youВҰ22805 have to leave behind\add*, because the best of all the land in EgyptВҰ22804 \add will be yoursВҰ22791\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ22808 Yisra'el's sonsВҰ22811 did \add what they had been instructed\add* andВҰ22808 YosefВҰ22815 gave them cartsВҰ22816 as per Far'oh's orders \add as well as\add* provisionsВҰ22823 for the \add journeyВҰ22824\add*.
\v 22 \add ThenВҰ22828\add* he gave changes of clothes to each of them, butВҰ22831 he gave threeВҰ22833 hundredВҰ22834 pieces of silverВҰ22835 and five changes of clothes to BenyaminВҰ22831.
\v 23 To his father he sent ten male donkeys loaded with the best of EgyptВҰ22847, and ten femaleВҰ22849 donkeys loaded with grainВҰ22851 and breadВҰ22852 and provisionsВҰ22853 for his father for the road.
\v 24 ThenВҰ22857 he sentВҰ22857 off his brothersВҰ22860, andВҰ22857 as they left, thenВҰ22857 he told them, вҖңDon'tВҰ22858 quarrel onВҰ22867 the road.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 \add SoВҰ22869\add* theyВҰ22871 \add left\add* EgyptВҰ22870 andВҰ22869 \add wentВҰ22869 back home\add* to theirВҰ22877 fatherВҰ22877 YacobВҰ22876 in CanaanВҰ22873
\v 26 and told him, вҖңYosefВҰ22883 is stillВҰ22882 aliveВҰ22884! \add In fact,\add* he's the ruler over all of EgyptВҰ22892.вҖқ ButВҰ22879 \add Yacob was totally stunned and\add* he \add couldn't really\add* believeВҰ22898 them.
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ22901 they told him \add everything\add* that Yosef had told them. \add WhenВҰ22901\add* he sawВҰ22911 the carts that Yosef had sentВҰ22917 to carryВҰ22919 him, thenВҰ22901 \add he started to recover from the shock\add*.
\v 28 ThenВҰ22926 Yisra'el \add exclaimed\add*, вҖңEnough! \add I accept that\add* my son YosefВҰ22931 is stillВҰ22929 aliveВҰ22933. I'll goВҰ22934 andВҰ22935 seeВҰ22935 himВҰ22935 beforeВҰ22936 I dieВҰ22937.вҖқ
\c 46
\s1 Yacob moves to Egypt
\rem /s1 Jacob Brings His Whole Family to Egypt; Jacob's Journey to Egypt; Jacob and His Family Go to Egypt; Jacob Goes to Egypt; The Israelites in Egypt
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ22939 Yisra'el started his trip, \add taking\add* everything he had. \add WhenВҰ22939 they stopped in\add* BeerВҰ22947-Sheva, he offered sacrificesВҰ22949 to the godВҰ22951 of his fatherВҰ22952 Yitshak.
\v 2 During the nightВҰ22960, GodВҰ22956 spoke to Yisra'el inВҰ22959 visionsВҰ22959 sayings, вҖңYacob, Yacob.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'm \add listening\add*,вҖқ he answered.
\v 3 ThenВҰ22968 \add God\add* told \add him\add*, вҖңI'm God, the god of your father. Don't be afraidВҰ22975 to goВҰ22976 down to EgyptВҰ22977, because I'll make youВҰ22982 into a greatВҰ22981 nationВҰ22980 thereВҰ22983.
\v 4 I myself will go down with you to EgyptВҰ22988, and I myself will also surely bringВҰ22990 you \add back here\add*. And YosefВҰ22994 will \add be there with you when you die\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ23001 YacobВҰ23002 \add departed\add* from Be'er-Sheva, and \add his\add* sonsВҰ23006 carriedВҰ23005 their fatherВҰ23012 and their littleВҰ23015 ones and their wivesВҰ23018 inВҰ23019 the carts thatВҰ23020 Far'ohВҰ23023 had sentВҰ23022 to carryВҰ23024 him.
\v 6 They \add had also brought along all\add* their livestockВҰ23030 and their possessions thatВҰ23034 they had acquired in CanaanВҰ23037. ThenВҰ23027 they \add arrived in\add* EgyptВҰ23039вҖ”YacobВҰ23040 and all of his offspring with him:\x + \xo 46:6: \xt Acts 7:15.\x*
\v 7 his sons and his sons' sons with him, and his daughters and his sons' daughters. So he broughtВҰ23056 all his offspring with him to EgyptВҰ23058.
\p
\v 8 These are the namesВҰ23062 of Yisrael'sВҰ23065 sons who went to EgyptВҰ23067, \add that is\add* Yacob and his sons: \bd Yacob\bd*'s firstbornВҰ23070 was ReubenВҰ23072,
\v 9 and \bd Reuben\bd*'s sonsВҰ23074 were HanochВҰ23076 and PalluВҰ23077 and HezronВҰ23078 and CarmiВҰ23079.
\v 10 \bd Simeon\bd*'s sonsВҰ23081 were YemuelВҰ23083, YaminВҰ23084, Ohad, Yakin, ZoharВҰ23087, andВҰ23081 ShaulВҰ23088, the son of a CanaaniteВҰ23091 woman.
\v 11 \bd Levi\bd*'s sonsВҰ23093 were GershonВҰ23095, KohathВҰ23096, andВҰ23097 MerariВҰ23097.
\v 12 \bd Yehudah\bd*'s sons were Er, Onan, ShelahВҰ23103, Perez, and ZerahВҰ23105, butВҰ23099 Er and Onan had died in CanaanВҰ23110. Perez' sons were HezronВҰ23115 and HamulВҰ23116.
\v 13 \bd Yissakar\bd*'s sonsВҰ23118 were TolaВҰ23120, PuvahВҰ23121, Yob, andВҰ23118 ShimronВҰ23123.
\v 14 \bd Zebulun\bd*'s sonsВҰ23125 were SeredВҰ23127, ElonВҰ23128, andВҰ23125 YahleelВҰ23129.
\v 15 Those were \add all\add* Le'ah's sons that she bore for YacobВҰ23137 inВҰ23138 PaddanВҰ23138-Aram, \add along withВҰ23138\add* his daughterВҰ23142 DinahВҰ23141. \add The total number of those descendants\add* was thirty-threeВҰ23148.
\p
\v 16 \bd Gad\bd*'s sonsВҰ23151 were Zifion,Haggi, ShuniВҰ23155, EzbonВҰ23156, EriВҰ23157, ArodiВҰ23158, andВҰ23151 AreliВҰ23159.
\v 17 \bd Asher\bd*'s sons were ImnahВҰ23163, IshvahВҰ23164, IshviВҰ23165, Beriah, and theirВҰ23168 sisterВҰ23168 SerahВҰ23167. And Beriah'sВҰ23166 sons were HeberВҰ23171 and Malkiel.
\v 18 Those were \add all\add* Zilpah'sВҰ23176 sonsВҰ23175, \add the slave woman\add* that Lavan had givenВҰ23179 to his daughterВҰ23182 Le'ah, andВҰ23183 she gaveВҰ23183 birthВҰ23183 to those sixteen \add descendants\add* for YacobВҰ23187.
\p
\v 19 Yacob'sВҰ23195 wifeВҰ23194 Rahel'sВҰ23193 sonsВҰ23192 were YosefВҰ23196 andВҰ23197 BenyaminВҰ23197.
\v 20 \bd Yosef\bd*'s sons ManassehВҰ23216 andВҰ23199 EfrayimВҰ23219 were born in EgyptВҰ23202. AsenathВҰ23207, the daughterВҰ23208 of Potifera the priestВҰ23212 of On, gave birth to them for \add Yosef\add*.\x + \xo 46:20: \xt Gen 41:50-52.\x*
\v 21 \bd Benyamin\bd*'s sonsВҰ23221 were BelaВҰ23223, BekerВҰ23224, AshbelВҰ23225, GeraВҰ23226, NaamanВҰ23227, Ehi, Rosh, MuppimВҰ23230, HuppimВҰ23231, andВҰ23221 ArdВҰ23232.
\v 22 Those were \add all\add* Rahel's descendantsвҖ”a total of fourteen.
\p
\v 23 \bd Dan\bd*'s son was HushimВҰ23249.
\v 24 \bd Naftali\bd*'s sonsВҰ23251 were YahzeelВҰ23253, GuniВҰ23254, YezerВҰ23255, andВҰ23251 ShillemВҰ23256.
\v 25 Those \add two\add* were \add both\add* Bilhah'sВҰ23260 sonsВҰ23259, \add the slave woman\add* that Lavan had givenВҰ23263 to his daughterВҰ23266 Rahel, andВҰ23267 she gaveВҰ23267 birthВҰ23267 to those sevenВҰ23275 \add descendants\add* for YacobВҰ23271.
\p
\v 26 \add TheВҰ23289 total count of those\add* who wentВҰ23280 to EgyptВҰ23282 with YacobВҰ23281 who \add were his descendants\add* (not counting \add his daughters-in-law\add*) was sixty-sixВҰ23293.
\v 27 \add As well as that\add*, Yosef's twoВҰ23305 sonsВҰ23296 were born inВҰ23303 EgyptВҰ23303 so that \add added up to a grand total of\add* seventyВҰ23314.\x + \xo 46:27: \xt Acts 7:14.\x*
\s1 Yacob's arrival in Egypt
\rem /s1 Jacob and His Family in Egypt; Jacob Settles in Goshen; Jacob's Family Arrives in Goshen
\p
\v 28 \add As they all approached Egypt, Yacob\add* sentВҰ23320 YehudahВҰ23319 ahead \add of the others\add* to find out from YosefВҰ23324 how to get to Goshen. \add As they all\add* arrived in the Goshen area,
\v 29 YosefВҰ23333 \add hooked up\add* his chariotВҰ23334 and went to meet his father Yisra'el \add there\add*. He \add went up to his father, and hugged him for a long time as he cried\add*.
\v 30 вҖңNow I can dieВҰ23358,вҖқ Yisra'el saidВҰ23353 to YosefВҰ23357, вҖңsince I've seen your faceВҰ23364вҖ”\add seen\add* that you'reВҰ23366 stillВҰ23366 aliveВҰ23367.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ23369 YosefВҰ23370 spoke to his brothers and to his father's household, вҖңI'llВҰ23378 go and report to Far'ohВҰ23380 and \add explain\add* to him that my brothers and my father's household who were living in CanaanВҰ23390 have come to \add join\add* me.
\v 32 \add I'llВҰ23397 tell him that you're\add* herders of sheepВҰ23396вҖ”livestockВҰ23400 \add farmers\add*вҖ”and \add that you've\add* broughtВҰ23408 your flocksВҰ23402 and herdsВҰ23403 and everything that \add you own\add*.
\v 33 SoВҰ23411 when Far'ohВҰ23415 calls for youВҰ23414 andВҰ23416 \add asks what yourВҰ23419 work is\add*,
\v 34 thenВҰ23421 you should \add answer\add*, вҖҳYourВҰ23436 servantsВҰ23425 have been livestockВҰ23423 menВҰ23422 from our youthВҰ23426 and until now, both weВҰ23432 and also our fathersВҰ23435,вҖҷ so that you can settle \add here\add* in GoshenВҰ23439, because EgyptiansВҰ23443 \add despise sheepВҰ23447 herders\add*.вҖқ
\c 47
\rem /s1 Jacob Blesses Pharaoh
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ23449 wentВҰ23449 YosefВҰ23450 to Far'ohВҰ23452 and told \add him\add*, вҖңMy fatherВҰ23454 and brothersВҰ23455 and their flocksВҰ23456 and herdsВҰ23457 and everything that \add belongs\add* to them, have comeВҰ23462 from CanaanВҰ23464 and they're \add here now\add* GoshenВҰ23467 \add area\add*.вҖқ
\v 2 ThenВҰ23469 he tookВҰ23471 fiveВҰ23472 of his brothersВҰ23470 andВҰ23469 presentedВҰ23474 them to Far'ohВҰ23476,
\v 3 andВҰ23486 Far'ohВҰ23479 \add asked them\add*, вҖңWhat's yourВҰ23492 occupationВҰ23485?вҖқ
\p вҖңYour servantsВҰ23492 have been shepherds \add for several generations\add*,вҖқ theyВҰ23486 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 4 ThenВҰ23500 theyВҰ23500 \add explained\add*, вҖңWe'veВҰ23503 comeВҰ23506 to \add stay here for a while\add* because in CanaanВҰ23519, there'sВҰ23509 no pastureВҰ23510 for our flocksВҰ23511 because \add the drought is very severe\add*. SoВҰ23500 now, pleaseВҰ23523 let your servantsВҰ23524 settle in the GoshenВҰ23526 \add area\add*.вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ23528 Far'ohВҰ23529 turned to YosefВҰ23532, вҖңYourВҰ23534 father andВҰ23535 yourВҰ23535 brothersВҰ23535 have comeВҰ23536 to youВҰ23537.
\v 6 The \add entire country\add* of EgyptВҰ23540 is in front of you. Settle your father and your brothersВҰ23551 in the best land, \add so\add* let them settle in the GoshenВҰ23554 \add area\add*. And if you're \add aware\add* thatВҰ23569 \add some of them have special talents\add*, then appoint them as overseersВҰ23565 of \add my own\add* livestockВҰ23566 \add as well\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ23573 YosefВҰ23574 broughtВҰ23573 his fatherВҰ23578 Yacob and presentedВҰ23579 himВҰ23579 to Far'oh, and Yacob blessedВҰ23582 Far'oh.
\v 8 вҖңHowВҰ23592 \add old are you\add*?вҖқ Far'ohВҰ23589 asked him.
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add I've been moving from place to place for\add* 130 years,вҖқ YacobВҰ23599 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add My lifeВҰ23614 has been short andВҰ23598 withВҰ23623 many difficulties, so I\add* haven't reachedВҰ23616 the longer \add ages of my ancestorsВҰ23622 inВҰ23623 theirВҰ23624 moving around\add*.вҖқ
\v 10 ThenВҰ23626 \add he\add* blessedВҰ23626 Far'ohВҰ23630 \add again\add* andВҰ23631 departed from \add his\add* presence.
\v 11 SoВҰ23635 YosefВҰ23636 gaveВҰ23643 his fatherВҰ23639 and his brothersВҰ23642 \add some of the best land\add* in EgyptВҰ23647 and \add helped\add* them settleВҰ23635 thereвҖ”in the RamesesВҰ23651 \add district just\add* as Far'ohВҰ23654 had commandedВҰ23653.
\v 12 \add HeВҰ23657 also\add* providedВҰ23656 his father and his brothersВҰ23663 and all his father's householdВҰ23667 with breadвҖ”each family accordingВҰ23670 to the \add numberВҰ23670 of children\add*.
\s1 Yosef's leadership through extreme famine
\rem /s1 Joseph's Leadership in the Famine; Joseph and the Famine; The Famine; The Famine in Egypt
\p
\v 13 \add ThenВҰ23673 the time came when\add* thereВҰ23674 was no bread in \add that entireВҰ23675 part of\add* the world, because the \add drought\add* was now extremely severe, and \add both\add* EgyptВҰ23685 and CanaanВҰ23687 were \add suffering from food shortages\add*.
\v 14 \add People all over came\add* to buy grain, and \add over time\add* YosefВҰ23692 had received \add in payment\add* all the silver thatВҰ23705 could be foundВҰ23698 in EgyptВҰ23701 and CanaanВҰ23703, and \add he in turn\add* took it to Far'oh's houseВҰ23714.
\v 15 SoВҰ23717 \add once there was no more silver left\add* in EgyptВҰ23720 andВҰ23717 in CanaanВҰ23722, all \add the Egyptians\add* demanded from YosefВҰ23729, вҖңGive us food. Why should weВҰ23736 dieВҰ23736 \add right here in front of\add* you? \add All our money\add* is gone!вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңBring your livestock,вҖқ YosefВҰ23743 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңandВҰ23742 I'll give grain to you inВҰ23748 exchange for \add them\add*, since the silver is gone.вҖқ
\v 17 So \add the people\add* broughtВҰ23754 their livestock to \add him\add*, and \add he\add* gaveВҰ23761 them grain \add in exchange for their\add* horsesВҰ23765 and sheepВҰ23767 and cattleВҰ23769 and donkeysВҰ23770. So he providedВҰ23771 them withВҰ23765 food that yearВҰ23776 \add in exchange\add* for all their livestock.
\p
\v 18 \add The next\add* year they came to \add Yosef\add* and \add begged\add*, вҖңWe can'tВҰ23788 hide it from our masterВҰ23791 that since \add there's no silver left\add* and \add since all \add* the livestock \add now\add* belongs to our lord, there's nothing left \add to offer other than\add* our bodiesВҰ23809 and our lands.
\v 19 Why should we die \add right in front of you\add*вҖ”both we and our land? Buy us and our land in exchange for food, and we and our land will be slavesВҰ23830 to Far'ohВҰ23831. And give us seed so that we'll live and not die, and so that the land won'tВҰ23836 be barren.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ23842 YosefВҰ23843 boughtВҰ23842 all the farmland of EgyptВҰ23849 for Far'oh, because everyВҰ23855 Egyptian sold his fieldВҰ23856. \add In that way, all\add* the land becameВҰ23862 Far'oh's because the famineВҰ23861 was \add so extreme\add*.
\v 21 \add As for\add* the people, he moved them to the cities\f + \fr 47:21 \ft TC: There's a variation here in different early copies and translations. Rather than moving the people into the cities (which might have been done to make food distribution more efficient), some translations choose the alternative вҖҳmade the people slavesвҖҷ.\f* from one endВҰ23872 of EgyptВҰ23875 to the otherВҰ23878.
\v 22 The only land he didn't buy was thatВҰ23894 of the priests, because they \add were given a regular allowanceВҰ23886\add* by Far'ohВҰ23889. Because they \add could live on what they were supplied with\add*, they didn't \add need to\add* sell their land.
\v 23 ThenВҰ23907 YosefВҰ23908 told the peopleВҰ23911, вҖңListen, now that I've boughtВҰ23913 you andВҰ23907 your land for Far'ohВҰ23919, here is seed for you so that you can \add work\add* the ground.
\v 24 \add Every time\add* you harvestВҰ23930 \add a crop\add*, you must giveВҰ23931 a fifthВҰ23932 \add of it\add* to Far'ohВҰ23933. The \add other\add* fourВҰ23934 partsВҰ23935 will be for you \add to use\add* as seed and as food for yourselvesВҰ23940 and your householdsВҰ23942 and your young children.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңYou've kept us alive,вҖқ theyВҰ23946 \add agreed\add*. вҖңMasterВҰ23952, \add continue to show us your favourВҰ23950\add*, andВҰ23953 we'll be slavesВҰ23954 for Far'ohВҰ23955.вҖқ
\v 26 SoВҰ23957 YosefВҰ23959 established it as a law to this dayВҰ23963 concerning the Egyptian farmland: that the fifthВҰ23970 belongsВҰ23976 to Far'oh. (Only the priests' land didn'tВҰ23975 become Far'oh's.)
\s1 Yacob's burial request
\rem /s1 Jacob's Last Request; The Last Days of Jacob
\p
\v 27 SoВҰ23979 Yisra'el \add (Yacob) and his descendants\add* settled in the GoshenВҰ23984 regionВҰ23981 of EgyptВҰ23982 and \add prospered\add*. The \add had many children\add* and \add quickly increased in number\add*.
\v 28 YacobВҰ23992 resided \add there\add* for seventeenВҰ23995 years, andВҰ23991 \add by thenВҰ23991\add* he was 147 years old
\v 29 and he was getting close to death, so he calledВҰ24016 for his son YosefВҰ24019 and asked him, вҖңIf, please, I have foundВҰ24025 favourВҰ24026 in your eyesВҰ24027, please \add give me your handВҰ24031 and promise to\add* deal withВҰ24027 me in kindness and faithfulnessВҰ24037. Please don'tВҰ24038 buryВҰ24041 me in EgyptВҰ24042.\x + \xo 47:29-30: \xt Gen 49:29-32; 50:6.\x*
\v 30 WhenВҰ24044 I \add die\add*, I want to be buried withВҰ24051 my ancestorsВҰ24047, so carryВҰ24048 me out of EgyptВҰ24049 andВҰ24044 buryВҰ24050 me inВҰ24051 theirВҰ24051 tomb.вҖқ
\p вҖңI'll do \add what you've requested\add*,вҖқ Yosef \add agreed\add*.
\p
\v 31 вҖңPromise me,вҖқ he \add insisted\add*. SoВҰ24057 \add Yosef promised\add* him andВҰ24057 Yisra'el bowed at the head of the bed.\f + \fr 47:31 \ft Some translations assume that elderly Yacob/Yisra'el bowed to God in worship after speaking with Yosef, but it's not impossible that he bowed to Yosef in acknowledgement of the high position that God had brought Yosef to as foretold by his dreams.\f*
\c 48
\s1 Yacob blesses Efrayim and Menashsheh
\rem /s1 Jacob Blesses Manasseh and Ephraim; Jacob Blesses Joseph's Sons; Jacob Blesses Ephraim and Manasseh; Manasseh and Ephraim
\p
\v 1 Some time afterВҰ24071 that, Yosef was told, вҖңListen, your father is sickВҰ24078.вҖқ So Yosef \add went to him\add*, taking his twoВҰ24082 sonsВҰ24083 with himвҖ”ManassehВҰ24087 and EfrayimВҰ24090.
\v 2 WhenВҰ24101 someone told YacobВҰ24093 that YosefВҰ24097 had arrived, \add he\add* exerted himself andВҰ24092 satВҰ24102 up in bed,
\v 3 thenВҰ24107 he told him, вҖңGodВҰ24112 the provider appearedВҰ24114 to me atВҰ24117 LuzВҰ24117 inВҰ24117 CanaanВҰ24119, andВҰ24107 he blessedВҰ24120 me\x + \xo 48:3-4: \xt Gen 28:13-14.\x*
\v 4 and saidВҰ24123 to me, вҖҳListen, I'll make you fruitfulВҰ24126, and I'll multiply you and make you into a community of peoplesВҰ24130. And I'll giveВҰ24131 this land to yourВҰ24126 offspring afterВҰ24137 you to be their possessionВҰ24138 forever.вҖҷ
\v 5 вҖңAnd now, yourВҰ24144 twoВҰ24142 sonsВҰ24144, who were born for youВҰ24152 \add here\add* in EgyptВҰ24148 before I cameВҰ24151 \add here\add*, I \add adopt\add* them as my ownвҖ”EfrayimВҰ24157 and ManassehВҰ24158вҖ”just as ReubenВҰ24159 and SimeonВҰ24160 are mine.
\v 6 \add Any other\add* childrenВҰ24165 that you fatherВҰ24168 afterВҰ24169 them will be yoursВҰ24170. Their inheritanceВҰ24176 will \add only be through their older\add* brothersВҰ24174.
\v 7 As for me, \add when\add* I was coming into CanaanВҰ24186 from PaddanВҰ24181, Rahel died beside onВҰ24180 the way when we were stillВҰ24188 quite some distanceВҰ24189 from Efrath, andВҰ24178 I buriedВҰ24194 her thereВҰ24195 beside the road of Efrath (which is Bethlehem).вҖқ\x + \xo 48:7: \xt Gen 35:16-19.\x*
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ24202 Yisra'el \add noticedВҰ24202\add* Yosef'sВҰ24207 \add two\add* sonsВҰ24206 andВҰ24208 \add asked\add*, вҖңWho are theseВҰ24211?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңThey are my sonsВҰ24218 that GodВҰ24225 has givenВҰ24222 me \add here\add* inВҰ24226 this place.вҖқ YosefВҰ24214 \add вүҲreplied\add* to his fatherВҰ24217.
\p вҖңPlease bringВҰ24228 them to me, andВҰ24213 I will blessВҰ24232 them,вҖқ \add Yacob requested\add*.
\v 10 Now Yisra'el's sight was poor in his old age, so heВҰ24239 wasn't able to seeВҰ24240 \add much\add*. SoВҰ24234 \add Yosef\add* broughtВҰ24241 them over to him, and \add Yisra'el\add* kissedВҰ24244 them and embracedВҰ24246 them.
\v 11 вҖңI \add never expected to see you again\add*вҖқ \add he\add* saidВҰ24249 to YosefВҰ24253, вҖңbutВҰ24249 wowВҰ24254, GodВҰ24261 has \add even\add* let me see your childrenВҰ24265 as well.вҖқ
\v 12 ThenВҰ24269 YosefВҰ24268 removedВҰ24267 \add his sons\add* from his \add father's\add* kneesВҰ24271 andВҰ24272 bowedВҰ24272 with his faceВҰ24273 to the groundВҰ24274.
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ24276 YosefВҰ24277 tookВҰ24276 both of themвҖ”EfrayimВҰ24283 on his right toward Yisra'el's left and ManassehВҰ24289 \add (the eldest)\add* on his left toward Yisra'el's rightвҖ”and broughtВҰ24293 them close to him.
\v 14 ButВҰ24296 Yisra'el intentionally extended his rightВҰ24300 hand and placed it on the Efrayim'sВҰ24305 head (the youngerВҰ24307 one), and \add crossingВҰ24315 his arms,\add* he placed his left hand on Manasseh'sВҰ24314 head.
\v 15 ThenВҰ24323 he blessedВҰ24323 YosefВҰ24326 saying,
\q1 вҖңMay the god who my \add grandfather\add* AbrahamВҰ24333 andВҰ24323 my fatherВҰ24331 Yitshak \add served\add*,
\q1 the god who has been shepherdingВҰ24336 me \add for my entireВҰ24338 lifeВҰ24338\add*,
\q1
\v 16 the messengerВҰ24344 who's \add turned all harm intended for me into good\add*,
\q2 may he blessВҰ24350 these young men.
\q1 May they be recognised \add as my descendants\add*,
\q2 and as \add descendants\add* of AbrahamВҰ24359 and Yitshak,
\q1 and grow to increaseВҰ24362 inВҰ24363 numberВҰ24362 onВҰ24363 the earthВҰ24364.
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ24366 YosefВҰ24367 noticedВҰ24366 that his father had placed his rightВҰ24374 hand onВҰ24380 Efrayim'sВҰ24378 head andВҰ24366 he was upset about it, so he picked up his father's hand to move it across to Manasseh'sВҰ24394 head,
\v 18 telling his father, вҖңMy father, that's wrong because that one is my oldest son. Put your rightВҰ24410 hand on \em his\em* head.вҖқ
\v 19 ButВҰ24415 his fatherВҰ24416 \add pushed back\add*, вҖңI know, my son, I know. \add Manasseh\add* will also become a peopleВҰ24426, and he will also be great. NeverthelessВҰ24431 his younger brother will be the greater one, and his descendants will become a multitude of nationsВҰ24440.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ24442 \add Yisra'el\add* blessed EfrayimВҰ24452 and ManassehВҰ24453 that dayВҰ24443 saying,\x + \xo 48:20: \xt Heb 11:21.\x*
\q1 вҖң\add After this, my descendants\add* will bless \add people\add* by saying,
\q1 вҖҳMay GodВҰ24451 make you like Efrayim and like Manasseh.вҖҷ вҖқ
\m (Notice that he put Efrayim before Manasseh.)
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ24461 Yisra'el told YosefВҰ24465, вҖңListen, I'm aboutВҰ24468 to dieВҰ24468, and GodВҰ24470 will be with you and take you back to the land of your ancestorsВҰ24477.
\v 22 I'm giving Shekem to you as an additional inheritance over thatВҰ24487 of yourВҰ24486 brothersВҰ24486. I captured it withВҰ24491 my swordВҰ24491 and my bow from the descendants of Amor \add and it's now yoursВҰ24481\add*.вҖқ
\c 49
\s1 Yacob's individual words for his sons
\rem /s1 Jacob Blesses His Sons; The Last Words of Jacob; Jacob's Last Words to His Sons
\p
\v 1 Then YacobВҰ24496 calledВҰ24495 for \add all\add* his sonsВҰ24499 and saidВҰ24500, вҖңGather together, and I'll reveal to you what will \add happenВҰ24507 to\add* you \add all in the years ahead\add*.
\q1
\v 2 Gather around and listen you sonsВҰ24514 of YacobВҰ24515,
\q1 вүҲlisten to your fatherВҰ24520 Yisra'el.
\b
\q1
\v 3 \bd ReubenВҰ24522\bd* you'reВҰ24524 my eldest,
\q1 вүҲmy power and the beginning of my strengthВҰ24527.
\q1 With excellence in dignityВҰ24529,
\q1 вүҲand excelling in power.
\q1
\v 4 \add But\add* you're destructive like \add strong\add* watersВҰ24534.
\q1 You climbed into my bed \add (with my slave-wife)\add*.
\q1 вүҲYou got onto my couchВҰ24544 and defiled it.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \bd SimeonВҰ24548 andВҰ24549 LeviВҰ24549\bd* are \add alike\add*.
\q1 Their swordsВҰ24553 are weaponsВҰ24551 of violenceВҰ24552.
\q1
\v 6 Don'tВҰ24565 let \em my\em* thoughts enterВҰ24558 into their discussion.
\q1 вүҲDon't let \em my\em* honour join in their assemblyВҰ24560.
\q1 They killed a manВҰ24568 in their angerВҰ24566,
\q1 вүҲand they hamstrungВҰ24570 an ox \add just\add* for their pleasure.
\q1
\v 7 Their fierceВҰ24577 anger is cursedВҰ24574,
\q1 вүҲand their severeВҰ24578 anger is determined.
\q1 I will divideВҰ24581 them out among Yacob'sВҰ24582 \add descendants\add*,
\q1 вүҲand scatterВҰ24583 them \add across\add* Yisra'el.
\b
\q1
\v 8 \bd YehudahВҰ24587\bd*, you'll be praisedВҰ24589 by your brothersВҰ24590.
\q1 You'll be a \add powerful force\add* against your enemiesВҰ24593.
\q1 Your father's sonsВҰ24597 will bow down to you.
\q1
\v 9 YehudahВҰ24602 is a lion cub.\x + \xo 49:9: \xt Num 24:9; Rev 5:5.\x*
\q1 My son, you've stood up after \add feasting on\add* your prey.
\q1 He \add stretches\add* and lies down like a lion.
\q1 As with a lionessВҰ24609, who will dare wake him?
\q1
\v 10 YehudahВҰ24617 will never leave the ruling position,
\q1 вүҲnor will his descendants be without the ruler'sВҰ24618 staffВҰ24618,
\q1 untilВҰ24621 \add the messiah\add* arrives
\q2 and the peopleВҰ24629 \add groups\add* obey him.
\q1
\v 11 He'll tie his donkeyВҰ24633 to the grapevineВҰ24632,\f + \fr 49:11 \ft This likely suggests such a surplus of fruit that it doesn't even matter what the animals eat.\f*
\q1 вүҲand the donkey's colt to the best branch.
\q1 He'll wash his clothes in wine
\q1 вүҲand his robesВҰ24644 in the bloodВҰ24641 of grapesВҰ24643.
\q1
\v 12 His eyesВҰ24648 \add will be\add* darker than wine,
\q1 вүҲandВҰ24650 his teethВҰ24652 \add will be\add* whiteВҰ24650 from milk.
\b
\q1
\v 13 \bd ZebulunВҰ24656\bd* will settle near the coast,
\q2 and be like a safe harbour for shipsВҰ24662.
\q1 His borderВҰ24663 will extend up to Tsidon.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \bd YissakarВҰ24669\bd* (Issachar) is a strong donkeyВҰ24670
\q1 lyingВҰ24672 down between the sheepВҰ24674 pens.\f + \fr 49:14 \ft Or вҖҳbetween two saddlebagsвҖҷ.\f*
\q1
\v 15 He'll see that his restingВҰ24677 placeВҰ24677 is goodВҰ24679
\q2 andВҰ24676 that the land is pleasantВҰ24684.
\q1 He'll strain his shouldersВҰ24686 to carry a burdenВҰ24687.
\q1 вүҲHe'll be forcedВҰ24689 to labourВҰ24689 \add for others\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 16 \bd DanВҰ24694\bd* \add (which means вҖҳjudgeвҖҷ)\add* will judge his peopleВҰ24696
\q2 like one of Yisra'el'sВҰ24699 tribesВҰ24698.
\q1
\v 17 He'llВҰ24703 be a snakeВҰ24704 beside the roadВҰ24707,
\q1 вүҲa viperВҰ24708 on the pathВҰ24707,
\q1 that bitesВҰ24712 a horse'sВҰ24715 heelsВҰ24713
\q2 andВҰ24716 itsВҰ24717 riderВҰ24717 fallsВҰ24716 backwardsВҰ24718.
\b
\q1
\v 18 YahwehВҰ24722, I'mВҰ24721 waiting for you to save \add us\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 19 \bd GadВҰ24724\bd* will be attackedВҰ24726 by riders,
\q2 butВҰ24727 he'll attackВҰ24728 them from behind.
\b
\q1
\v 20 \bd AsherВҰ24732\bd* will enjoy delicious food,
\q2 andВҰ24735 he'll provideВҰ24736 delicacies for a kingВҰ24739.
\b
\q1
\v 21 \bd NaftaliВҰ24742\bd* is a doe that's been untiedВҰ24744.
\q1 He says beautiful wordsВҰ24746.\f + \fr 49:21 \ft Or вҖҳhas beautiful fawnsвҖҷ.\f*
\b
\q1
\v 22 \bd YosefВҰ24753\bd* is \add part\add* of a fruit-bearing vineвҖ”
\q1 вүҲpart of a fruit-bearing \add vine\add* at a springВҰ24758.
\q1 His branches will climbВҰ24760 over the wall.
\q1
\v 23 Expert archers will attackВҰ24765 him,
\q2 and shoot and harassВҰ24767 him.
\q1
\v 24 \add ButВҰ24771\add* his bow will stay steadyВҰ24772
\q2 вүҲandВҰ24774 his arms will be made agileВҰ24774
\q1 by the handsВҰ24777 of the mightyВҰ24778 one of YacobВҰ24779,
\q2 вүҲ\add because\add* of the shepherdВҰ24781 who's Yisra'el'sВҰ24783 rockВҰ24782,
\q1
\v 25 by the godВҰ24785 of your father, and he will help you,
\q2 and with the provider,
\q1 and he will bless you with blessings \add from\add* the heavensВҰ24792 aboveВҰ24793
\q2 blessings of the deep thatВҰ24796 lies below,
\q2 \add and\add* blessings of breastsВҰ24799 and womb.
\q1
\v 26 I've been blessed more than my ancestorsВҰ24808 wereвҖ”
\q2 even with being gifted those ancient hillsВҰ24812.
\q1 May those blessings now transfer to YosefВҰ24817вҖ”
\q2 the one who was separated from all his brothersВҰ24820.
\b
\q1
\v 27 \bd BenyaminВҰ24823\bd* is a ravenous wolf.
\q1 In the morningВҰ24826 he devours his prey,
\q1 вүҲand inВҰ24826 the eveningВҰ24829 he dividesВҰ24830 the plunderВҰ24831.
\p
\v 28 Those are Yisra'el's \add twelve sons (that led to the\add* twelve tribesВҰ24836) and that's what theirВҰ24845 fatherВҰ24845 said to them \add from hisВҰ24850 bed\add* as he blessed each one of themвҖ”each one blessed appropriately.
\s1 Yacob's death and burial
\rem /s1 Jacob's Death and Burial; The Death of Jacob; The Death and Burial of Jacob
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ24854 Yacob instructedВҰ24854 them, вҖңI'm aboutВҰ24859 to go andВҰ24856 join my ancestorsВҰ24867. Bury me withВҰ24872 them in the cave in the fieldВҰ24872 \add thatВҰ24871 was bought from\add* EfronВҰ24873 the HittiteВҰ24874,
\v 30 in the cave that is in Makpelah'sВҰ24879 field in front of MamreВҰ24885 in CanaanВҰ24887. That's \add the cave that my grandfather\add* AbrahamВҰ24890 boughtВҰ24889 withВҰ24878 the field from EfronВҰ24895 the HittiteВҰ24896 as property for a burialВҰ24899 placeВҰ24897.\x + \xo 49:30: \xt Gen 23:3-20.\x*
\v 31 AbrahamВҰ24905 and his wife SarahВҰ24907 were buried there, along with \add their son\add* IsaacВҰ24913 and his wife RebekahВҰ24915, and I \add also\add* buried \add my wife\add* Le'ah there.\x + \xo 49:31: a \xt Gen 25:9-10; \xo b \xt Gen 35:29.\x*
\v 32 That fieldВҰ24924 andВҰ24925 the cave in it was bought from the descendants of HetВҰ24932.
\v 33 \add WhenВҰ24937\add* YacobВҰ24935 finished giving those instructions to his sonsВҰ24939, he pulled his feetВҰ24941 up into the bed \add and lay\add* and breathedВҰ24945 his last and \add his spirit joined his ancestors\add*.\x + \xo 49:33: \xt Acts 7:15.\x*
\c 50
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ24951 YosefВҰ24952 \add hugged\add* his fatherВҰ24956 and cried over him and kissedВҰ24959 him.
\v 2 ThenВҰ24963 \add he\add* commandedВҰ24963 \add those of\add* his servantsВҰ24967 \add who were\add* physicians to embalm his fatherВҰ24974. \add SoВҰ24963\add* Yisra'el's \add body\add* was embalmed
\v 3 over the next fortyВҰ24984 days (which is the normal time for embalmingВҰ24990), andВҰ24981 the EgyptiansВҰ24993 mourned for him for seventyВҰ24994 days.
\p
\v 4 After those mourningВҰ24999 daysВҰ24998 were over, YosefВҰ25001 spokeВҰ25000 to Far'oh's \add servants\add*, saying, вҖңPlease, if I have foundВҰ25010 favourВҰ25011 inВҰ25012 yourВҰ25012 eyesВҰ25012, please tell Far'oh that
\v 5 my father made me swearВҰ25021, saying, вҖҳListen, I am dying. You must bury me in my grave thatВҰ25027 I dug for myself in CanaanВҰ25031.вҖҷ So now, pleaseВҰ25037 \add ask Far'oh to\add* let me go up thereВҰ25032 and bury my father, then I'll returnВҰ25042.вҖқ\x + \xo 50:5: \xt Gen 47:29-31.\x*
\p
\v 6 вҖңGoВҰ25050 up andВҰ25047 buryВҰ25047 your father just like he made youВҰ25052 promise.вҖқ was the reply back from Far'ohВҰ25045.
\p
\v 7 SoВҰ25054 YosefВҰ25055 went up \add to Canaan\add* to buryВҰ25056 his fatherВҰ25059. Far'oh's servantsВҰ25064 went with him, along with the elders from Far'oh's householdВҰ25067 andВҰ25054 all the elders of the land of EgyptВҰ25072.
\v 8 Yosef's own household also went, along with his brothersВҰ25077 and his father'sВҰ25079 household. They only left their childrenВҰ25081 and their livestock behind in GoshenВҰ25086.
\v 9 There were chariotsВҰ25092 as well as \add soldiers\add* mounted on horsesВҰ25095 so it was a very large procession.
\p
\v 10 After they crossed the YordanВҰ25108 river, they arrived atВҰ25107 Atad's threshingВҰ25104 floorВҰ25104, andВҰ25101 they mournedВҰ25118 thereВҰ25111 for sevenВҰ25119 daysВҰ25120 withВҰ25107 very loud wailing.
\v 11 The local CanaaniteВҰ25125 people sawВҰ25122 the mourning atВҰ25129 Atad's threshingВҰ25129 floorВҰ25129, andВҰ25122 they saidВҰ25131, вҖңThis is \add very serious\add* mourning for the Egyptians.вҖқ That's why they thenВҰ25122 named thatВҰ25144 place across the YordanВҰ25146 вҖҳHevelВҰ25142-MizraimВҰ25143вҖҷ \add (whichВҰ25144 means вҖҳthe Egyptians mourned hereвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 12 \add SoВҰ25148\add* Yacob's sonsВҰ25149 did everything just how he'd instructedВҰ25153 them.
\v 13 \add They\add* carriedВҰ25155 \add his embalmed body\add* to CanaanВҰ25159 andВҰ25155 buriedВҰ25160 him in the cave in Makpelah'sВҰ25164 field. AbrahamВҰ25167 had boughtВҰ25166 with the field with the included cave from EfronВҰ25175 the HittiteВҰ25176 as property for a burialВҰ25173 placeВҰ25171, in front of MamreВҰ25180.\x + \xo 50:13: \xt Acts 7:16.\x*
\rem /s1 Joseph Reassures His Brothers
\v 14 ThenВҰ25182 afterВҰ25195 his father's burial was completed, YosefВҰ25183 returnedВҰ25182 to EgyptВҰ25184 along with his brothersВҰ25186 andВҰ25182 everyone who had gone up with him to buryВҰ25191 \add him\add*.
\s1 Yosef forgives his brothers
\rem /s1 Joseph Forgives His Brothers; Joseph Reassures His Brothers
\p
\v 15 \add Now that theirВҰ25208 fatherВҰ25208 was no longer alive\add*, Yosef's brothersВҰ25202 saidВҰ25209 \add to each other\add*, вҖңWhat if Yosef hates us \add andВҰ25201 now he decides to\add* repay us for all the evil \add things\add* that we did to him?вҖқ
\v 16 SoВҰ25224 they sentВҰ25224 a messenger to YosefВҰ25227 to tell him, вҖңBeforeВҰ25229 he diedВҰ25232, your father orderedВҰ25230 that
\v 17 you be given this message: вҖҳI beg you, please forgive your brothers' crime and their sinВҰ25244, because they did evil \add things\add* to you.вҖҷ So now, please forgive the crime of the servantsВҰ25253 of your father's godВҰ25254.вҖқ When YosefВҰ25238 heard their message, he \add started\add* crying.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ25261 his brothersВҰ25264 also cameВҰ25261 and \add bowed to the ground in front of\add* himВҰ25266 and \add pleaded\add*, вҖңHere weВҰ25268 are. We belong to you as slavesВҰ25270.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңDon't be afraid,вҖқ YosefВҰ25274 answered. вҖң\add I'm not GodВҰ25280 andВҰ25272 it's not my job to decide on your punishment\add*.
\v 20 You all plotted evil things againstВҰ25285 me, butВҰ25283 GodВҰ25287 intended itВҰ25288 for goodВҰ25289 in order to do what he's doing this \add very\add* dayВҰ25292: to save many peopleВҰ25295.
\v 21 So now, don'tВҰ25300 be afraid. I'll support youВҰ25305 and yourВҰ25308 littleВҰ25308 ones.вҖқ So he reassured them and he spokeВҰ25311 \add kindly to them\add*.
\s1 Yosef's death
\rem /s1 Joseph's Last Days and Death; The Death of Joseph
\p
\v 22 YosefВҰ25317 continued to live inВҰ25318 EgyptВҰ25318, along withВҰ25318 \add the rest of\add* his fatherВҰ25321 Yacob'sВҰ25323 familyВҰ25320, until heВҰ25319 was 110 yearsВҰ25326 old.
\v 23 He lived long enough to see his son Efrayim'sВҰ25330 children, grandchildren, andВҰ25328 great-grandchildren. The children of his grandson MachirВҰ25335, who was Manasseh'sВҰ25338 son, also grew up around him.
\v 24 ThenВҰ25345 \add one day\add* YosefВҰ25346 saidВҰ25345 to his brothersВҰ25349, вҖңI'm aboutВҰ25351 to dieВҰ25351, butВҰ25345 GodВҰ25352 will definitely help you all and take you \add and your descendants\add* from this country to the land thatВҰ25365 he vowed to give to AbrahamВҰ25367, Yitshak, and YacobВҰ25369.
\v 25 WhenВҰ25371 GodВҰ25380 does that, you must take my body \add back to Canaan with you and bury it there\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ25371 YosefВҰ25372 had \add his brothers and the rest of the descendants of Yisra'el\add* vow \add that they would do that\add*.\x + \xo 50:25: \xt Exo 13:19; Josh 24:32; Heb 11:22.\x*
\v 26 ThenВҰ25388 YosefВҰ25389 diedВҰ25388 atВҰ25398 the age of 110, and \add the specialists\add* embalmedВҰ25395 \add his body\add* and it was put in a coffinВҰ25398 in \add a tomb in\add* EgyptВҰ25399.
